v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

47// Scoped class tracking context objects created by the visitor. Represents
48// mutations of the context chain within the function body, allowing pushing and
49// popping of the current {context_register} during visitation.
50class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ContextScope {
51 public:
52 ContextScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Scope* scope,
53 Register outer_context_reg = Register())
54 : generator_(generator),
55 scope_(scope),
56 outer_(generator_->execution_context()),
57 register_(Register::current_context()),
58 depth_(0) {
59 DCHECK(scope->NeedsContext() || outer_ == nullptr);
60 if (outer_) {
61 depth_ = outer_->depth_ + 1;
62
63 // Push the outer context into a new context register.
64 if (!outer_context_reg.is_valid()) {
65 outer_context_reg = generator_->register_allocator()->NewRegister();
66 }
67 outer_->set_register(outer_context_reg);
68 generator_->builder()->PushContext(outer_context_reg);
69 }
70 generator_->set_execution_context(this);
71 }
72
73 ~ContextScope() {
74 if (outer_) {
75 DCHECK_EQ(register_.index(), Register::current_context().index());
76 generator_->builder()->PopContext(outer_->reg());
77 outer_->set_register(register_);
78 }
79 generator_->set_execution_context(outer_);
80 }
81
82 ContextScope(const ContextScope&) = delete;
83 ContextScope& operator=(const ContextScope&) = delete;
84
85 // Returns the depth of the given |scope| for the current execution context.
86 int ContextChainDepth(Scope* scope) {
87 return scope_->ContextChainLength(scope);
88 }
89
90 // Returns the execution context at |depth| in the current context chain if it
91 // is a function local execution context, otherwise returns nullptr.
92 ContextScope* Previous(int depth) {
93 if (depth > depth_) {
94 return nullptr;
95 }
96
97 ContextScope* previous = this;
98 for (int i = depth; i > 0; --i) {
99 previous = previous->outer_;
100 }
101 return previous;
102 }
103
104 Register reg() const { return register_; }
105
106 private:
107 const BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder() const { return generator_->builder(); }
108
109 void set_register(Register reg) { register_ = reg; }
110
111 BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
112 Scope* scope_;
113 ContextScope* outer_;
114 Register register_;
115 int depth_;
116};

118// Scoped class for tracking control statements entered by the
119// visitor.
120class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
121 public:
122 explicit ControlScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator)
123 : generator_(generator),
124 outer_(generator->execution_control()),
125 context_(generator->execution_context()) {
126 generator_->set_execution_control(this);
127 }
128 ~ControlScope() { generator_->set_execution_control(outer()); }
129 ControlScope(const ControlScope&) = delete;
130 ControlScope& operator=(const ControlScope&) = delete;
131
132 void Break(Statement* stmt) {
133 PerformCommand(CMD_BREAK, stmt, kNoSourcePosition);
134 }
135 void Continue(Statement* stmt) {
136 PerformCommand(CMD_CONTINUE, stmt, kNoSourcePosition);
137 }
138 void ReturnAccumulator(int source_position) {
139 PerformCommand(CMD_RETURN, nullptr, source_position);
140 }
141 void AsyncReturnAccumulator(int source_position) {
142 PerformCommand(CMD_ASYNC_RETURN, nullptr, source_position);
143 }
144
145 class DeferredCommands;
146
147 protected:
148 enum Command {
149 CMD_BREAK,
150 CMD_CONTINUE,
151 CMD_RETURN,
152 CMD_ASYNC_RETURN,
153 CMD_RETHROW
154 };
155 static constexpr bool CommandUsesAccumulator(Command command) {
156 return command != CMD_BREAK && command != CMD_CONTINUE;
157 }
158
159 void PerformCommand(Command command, Statement* statement,
160 int source_position);
161 virtual bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
162 int source_position) = 0;
163
164 // Helper to pop the context chain to a depth expected by this control scope.
165 // Note that it is the responsibility of each individual {Execute} method to
166 // trigger this when commands are handled and control-flow continues locally.
167 void PopContextToExpectedDepth();
168
169 BytecodeGenerator* generator() const { return generator_; }
170 ControlScope* outer() const { return outer_; }
171 ContextScope* context() const { return context_; }
172
173 private:
174 BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
175 ControlScope* outer_;
176 ContextScope* context_;
177};

179// Helper class for a try-finally control scope. It can record intercepted
180// control-flow commands that cause entry into a finally-block, and re-apply
181// them after again leaving that block. Special tokens are used to identify
182// paths going through the finally-block to dispatch after leaving the block.
183class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope::DeferredCommands final {
184 public:
185 DeferredCommands(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Register token_register,
186 Register result_register, Register message_register)
187 : generator_(generator),
188 deferred_(generator->zone()),
189 token_register_(token_register),
190 result_register_(result_register),
191 message_register_(message_register),
192 return_token_(-1),
193 async_return_token_(-1),
194 fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_(false) {
195 // There's always a rethrow path.
196 // TODO(leszeks): We could decouple deferred_ index and token to allow us
197 // to still push this lazily.
198 static_assert(
199 static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken) == 0);
200 deferred_.push_back(
201 {CMD_RETHROW, nullptr,
202 static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken)});
203 }
204
205 // One recorded control-flow command.
206 struct Entry {
207 Command command; // The command type being applied on this path.
208 Statement* statement; // The target statement for the command or {nullptr}.
209 int token; // A token identifying this particular path.
210 };
211
212 // Records a control-flow command while entering the finally-block. This also
213 // generates a new dispatch token that identifies one particular path. This
214 // expects the result to be in the accumulator.
215 void RecordCommand(Command command, Statement* statement) {
216 int token = GetTokenForCommand(command, statement);
217
218 DCHECK_LT(token, deferred_.size());
219 DCHECK_EQ(deferred_[token].command, command);
220 DCHECK_EQ(deferred_[token].statement, statement);
221 DCHECK_EQ(deferred_[token].token, token);
222
223 if (CommandUsesAccumulator(command)) {
224 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
225 }
226 builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(token));
227 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(token_register_);
228 if (!CommandUsesAccumulator(command)) {
229 // If we're not saving the accumulator in the result register, shove a
230 // harmless value there instead so that it is still considered "killed" in
231 // the liveness analysis. Normally we would LdaUndefined first, but the
232 // Smi token value is just as good, and by reusing it we save a bytecode.
233 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
234 }
235 if (command == CMD_RETHROW) {
236 // Clear message object as we enter the catch block. It will be restored
237 // if we rethrow.
238 builder()->LoadTheHole().SetPendingMessage().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
239 message_register_);
240 }
241 }
242
243 // Records the dispatch token to be used to identify the re-throw path when
244 // the finally-block has been entered through the exception handler. This
245 // expects the exception to be in the accumulator.
246 void RecordHandlerReThrowPath() {
247 // The accumulator contains the exception object.
248 RecordCommand(CMD_RETHROW, nullptr);
249 }
250
251 // Records the dispatch token to be used to identify the implicit fall-through
252 // path at the end of a try-block into the corresponding finally-block.
253 void RecordFallThroughPath() {
254 fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_ = true;
255 builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(
256 static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kFallthroughToken)));
257 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(token_register_);
258 // Since we're not saving the accumulator in the result register, shove a
259 // harmless value there instead so that it is still considered "killed" in
260 // the liveness analysis. Normally we would LdaUndefined first, but the Smi
261 // token value is just as good, and by reusing it we save a bytecode.
262 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
263 }
264
265 void ApplyDeferredCommand(const Entry& entry) {
266 if (entry.command == CMD_RETHROW) {
267 // Pending message object is restored on exit.
268 builder()
269 ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(message_register_)
270 .SetPendingMessage();
271 }
272
273 if (CommandUsesAccumulator(entry.command)) {
274 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(result_register_);
275 }
276 execution_control()->PerformCommand(entry.command, entry.statement,
277 kNoSourcePosition);
278 }
279
280 // Applies all recorded control-flow commands after the finally-block again.
281 // This generates a dynamic dispatch on the token from the entry point.
282 void ApplyDeferredCommands() {
283 if (deferred_.empty()) return;
284
285 BytecodeLabel fall_through_from_try_block;
286
287 if (deferred_.size() == 1) {
288 // For a single entry, just jump to the fallthrough if we don't match the
289 // entry token.
290 const Entry& entry = deferred_[0];
291
292 if (fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_) {
293 builder()
294 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(entry.token))
295 .CompareReference(token_register_)
296 .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
297 &fall_through_from_try_block);
298 }
299
300 ApplyDeferredCommand(entry);
301 } else {
302 // For multiple entries, build a jump table and switch on the token,
303 // jumping to the fallthrough if none of them match.
304 //
305 // If fallthrough from the try block is not needed, generate a jump table
306 // with one (1) fewer entries and reuse the fallthrough path for the final
307 // entry.
308 const int jump_table_base_value =
309 fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_ ? 0 : 1;
310 const int jump_table_size =
311 static_cast<int>(deferred_.size() - jump_table_base_value);
312
313 if (jump_table_size == 1) {
314 DCHECK_EQ(2, deferred_.size());
315 BytecodeLabel fall_through_to_final_entry;
316 const Entry& first_entry = deferred_[0];
317 const Entry& final_entry = deferred_[1];
318 builder()
319 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(first_entry.token))
320 .CompareReference(token_register_)
321 .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
322 &fall_through_to_final_entry);
323 ApplyDeferredCommand(first_entry);
324 builder()->Bind(&fall_through_to_final_entry);
325 ApplyDeferredCommand(final_entry);
326 } else {
327 BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table = builder()->AllocateJumpTable(
328 jump_table_size, jump_table_base_value);
329 builder()
330 ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(token_register_)
331 .SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback(jump_table);
332
333 const Entry& first_entry = deferred_.front();
334 if (fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_) {
335 builder()->Jump(&fall_through_from_try_block);
336 builder()->Bind(jump_table, first_entry.token);
337 }
338 ApplyDeferredCommand(first_entry);
339
340 for (const Entry& entry : base::IterateWithoutFirst(deferred_)) {
341 builder()->Bind(jump_table, entry.token);
342 ApplyDeferredCommand(entry);
343 }
344 }
345 }
346
347 if (fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_) {
348 builder()->Bind(&fall_through_from_try_block);
349 }
350 }
351
352 BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder() { return generator_->builder(); }
353 ControlScope* execution_control() { return generator_->execution_control(); }
354
355 private:
356 int GetTokenForCommand(Command command, Statement* statement) {
357 switch (command) {
358 case CMD_RETURN:
359 return GetReturnToken();
360 case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
361 return GetAsyncReturnToken();
362 case CMD_RETHROW:
363 return static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken);
364 default:
365 // TODO(leszeks): We could also search for entries with the same
366 // command and statement.
367 return GetNewTokenForCommand(command, statement);
368 }
369 }
370
371 int GetReturnToken() {
372 if (return_token_ == -1) {
373 return_token_ = GetNewTokenForCommand(CMD_RETURN, nullptr);
374 }
375 return return_token_;
376 }
377
378 int GetAsyncReturnToken() {
379 if (async_return_token_ == -1) {
380 async_return_token_ = GetNewTokenForCommand(CMD_ASYNC_RETURN, nullptr);
381 }
382 return async_return_token_;
383 }
384
385 int GetNewTokenForCommand(Command command, Statement* statement) {
386 int token = static_cast<int>(deferred_.size());
387 deferred_.push_back({command, statement, token});
388 return token;
389 }
390
391 BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
392 ZoneVector<Entry> deferred_;
393 Register token_register_;
394 Register result_register_;
395 Register message_register_;
396
397 // Tokens for commands that don't need a statement.
398 int return_token_;
399 int async_return_token_;
400
401 // Whether a fallthrough is possible.
402 bool fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_;
403};

405// Scoped class for dealing with control flow reaching the function level.
406class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForTopLevel final
407 : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
408 public:
409 explicit ControlScopeForTopLevel(BytecodeGenerator* generator)
410 : ControlScope(generator) {}
411
412 protected:
413 bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
414 int source_position) override {
415 switch (command) {
416 case CMD_BREAK: // We should never see break/continue in top-level.
417 case CMD_CONTINUE:
418 UNREACHABLE();
419 case CMD_RETURN:
420 // No need to pop contexts, execution leaves the method body.
421 generator()->BuildReturn(source_position);
422 return true;
423 case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
424 // No need to pop contexts, execution leaves the method body.
425 generator()->BuildAsyncReturn(source_position);
426 return true;
427 case CMD_RETHROW:
428 // No need to pop contexts, execution leaves the method body.
429 generator()->BuildReThrow();
430 return true;
431 }
432 return false;
433 }
434};

436// Scoped class for enabling break inside blocks and switch blocks.
437class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForBreakable final
438 : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
439 public:
440 ControlScopeForBreakable(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
441 BreakableStatement* statement,
442 BreakableControlFlowBuilder* control_builder)
443 : ControlScope(generator),
444 statement_(statement),
445 control_builder_(control_builder) {}
446
447 protected:
448 bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
449 int source_position) override {
450 if (statement != statement_) return false;
451 switch (command) {
452 case CMD_BREAK:
453 PopContextToExpectedDepth();
454 control_builder_->Break();
455 return true;
456 case CMD_CONTINUE:
457 case CMD_RETURN:
458 case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
459 case CMD_RETHROW:
460 break;
461 }
462 return false;
463 }
464
465 private:
466 Statement* statement_;
467 BreakableControlFlowBuilder* control_builder_;
468};

470// Scoped class for enabling 'break' and 'continue' in iteration
471// constructs, e.g. do...while, while..., for...
472class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForIteration final
473 : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
474 public:
475 ControlScopeForIteration(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
476 IterationStatement* statement,
477 LoopBuilder* loop_builder)
478 : ControlScope(generator),
479 statement_(statement),
480 loop_builder_(loop_builder) {}
481
482 protected:
483 bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
484 int source_position) override {
485 if (statement != statement_) return false;
486 switch (command) {
487 case CMD_BREAK:
488 PopContextToExpectedDepth();
489 loop_builder_->Break();
490 return true;
491 case CMD_CONTINUE:
492 PopContextToExpectedDepth();
493 loop_builder_->Continue();
494 return true;
495 case CMD_RETURN:
496 case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
497 case CMD_RETHROW:
498 break;
499 }
500 return false;
501 }
502
503 private:
504 Statement* statement_;
505 LoopBuilder* loop_builder_;
506};

508// Scoped class for enabling 'throw' in try-catch constructs.
509class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForTryCatch final
510 : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
511 public:
512 ControlScopeForTryCatch(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
513 TryCatchBuilder* try_catch_builder)
514 : ControlScope(generator) {}
515
516 protected:
517 bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
518 int source_position) override {
519 switch (command) {
520 case CMD_BREAK:
521 case CMD_CONTINUE:
522 case CMD_RETURN:
523 case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
524 break;
525 case CMD_RETHROW:
526 // No need to pop contexts, execution re-enters the method body via the
527 // stack unwinding mechanism which itself restores contexts correctly.
528 generator()->BuildReThrow();
529 return true;
530 }
531 return false;
532 }
533};

535// Scoped class for enabling control flow through try-finally constructs.
536class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForTryFinally final
537 : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
538 public:
539 ControlScopeForTryFinally(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
540 TryFinallyBuilder* try_finally_builder,
541 DeferredCommands* commands)
542 : ControlScope(generator),
543 try_finally_builder_(try_finally_builder),
544 commands_(commands) {}
545
546 protected:
547 bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
548 int source_position) override {
549 switch (command) {
550 case CMD_BREAK:
551 case CMD_CONTINUE:
552 case CMD_RETURN:
553 case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
554 case CMD_RETHROW:
555 PopContextToExpectedDepth();
556 // We don't record source_position here since we don't generate return
557 // bytecode right here and will generate it later as part of finally
558 // block. Each return bytecode generated in finally block will get own
559 // return source position from corresponded return statement or we'll
560 // use end of function if no return statement is presented.
561 commands_->RecordCommand(command, statement);
562 try_finally_builder_->LeaveTry();
563 return true;
564 }
565 return false;
566 }
567
568 private:
569 TryFinallyBuilder* try_finally_builder_;
570 DeferredCommands* commands_;
571};

573// Scoped class for collecting 'return' statments in a derived constructor.
574// Derived constructors can only return undefined or objects, and this check
575// must occur right before return (e.g., after `finally` blocks execute).
576class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForDerivedConstructor final
577 : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
578 public:
579 ControlScopeForDerivedConstructor(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
580 Register result_register,
581 BytecodeLabels* check_return_value_labels)
582 : ControlScope(generator),
583 result_register_(result_register),
584 check_return_value_labels_(check_return_value_labels) {}
585
586 protected:
587 bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
588 int source_position) override {
589 // Constructors are never async.
590 DCHECK_NE(CMD_ASYNC_RETURN, command);
591 if (command == CMD_RETURN) {
592 PopContextToExpectedDepth();
593 generator()->builder()->SetStatementPosition(source_position);
594 generator()->builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
595 generator()->builder()->Jump(check_return_value_labels_->New());
596 return true;
597 }
598 return false;
599 }
600
601 private:
602 Register result_register_;
603 BytecodeLabels* check_return_value_labels_;
604};

606// Allocate and fetch the coverage indices tracking NaryLogical Expressions.
607class BytecodeGenerator::NaryCodeCoverageSlots {
608 public:
609 NaryCodeCoverageSlots(BytecodeGenerator* generator, NaryOperation* expr)
610 : generator_(generator) {
611 if (generator_->block_coverage_builder_ == nullptr) return;
612 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length(); i++) {
613 coverage_slots_.push_back(
614 generator_->AllocateNaryBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(expr, i));
615 }
616 }
617
618 int GetSlotFor(size_t subsequent_expr_index) const {
619 if (generator_->block_coverage_builder_ == nullptr) {
620 return BlockCoverageBuilder::kNoCoverageArraySlot;
621 }
622 DCHECK(coverage_slots_.size() > subsequent_expr_index);
623 return coverage_slots_[subsequent_expr_index];
624 }
625
626 private:
627 BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
628 std::vector<int> coverage_slots_;
629};
630
631void BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope::PerformCommand(Command command,
632 Statement* statement,
633 int source_position) {
634 ControlScope* current = this;
635 do {
636 if (current->Execute(command, statement, source_position)) {
637 return;
638 }
639 current = current->outer();
640 } while (current != nullptr);
641 UNREACHABLE();
642}
643
644void BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope::PopContextToExpectedDepth() {
645 // Pop context to the expected depth. Note that this can in fact pop multiple
646 // contexts at once because the {PopContext} bytecode takes a saved register.
647 if (generator()->execution_context() != context()) {
648 generator()->builder()->PopContext(context()->reg());
649 }
650}

703// Scoped base class for determining how the result of an expression will be
704// used.
705class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ExpressionResultScope {
706 public:
707 ExpressionResultScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Expression::Context kind)
708 : outer_(generator->execution_result()),
709 allocator_(generator),
710 kind_(kind),
711 type_hint_(TypeHint::kUnknown) {
712 generator->set_execution_result(this);
713 }
714
715 ~ExpressionResultScope() {
716 allocator_.generator()->set_execution_result(outer_);
717 }
718
719 ExpressionResultScope(const ExpressionResultScope&) = delete;
720 ExpressionResultScope& operator=(const ExpressionResultScope&) = delete;
721
722 bool IsEffect() const { return kind_ == Expression::kEffect; }
723 bool IsValue() const { return kind_ == Expression::kValue; }
724 bool IsTest() const { return kind_ == Expression::kTest; }
725
726 TestResultScope* AsTest() {
727 DCHECK(IsTest());
728 return reinterpret_cast<TestResultScope*>(this);
729 }
730
731 // Specify expression always returns a Boolean result value.
732 void SetResultIsBoolean() {
733 DCHECK_EQ(type_hint_, TypeHint::kUnknown);
734 type_hint_ = TypeHint::kBoolean;
735 }
736
737 void SetResultIsString() {
738 DCHECK_EQ(type_hint_, TypeHint::kUnknown);
739 type_hint_ = TypeHint::kString;
740 }
741
742 void SetResultIsInternalizedString() {
743 DCHECK_EQ(type_hint_, TypeHint::kUnknown);
744 type_hint_ = TypeHint::kInternalizedString;
745 }
746
747 TypeHint type_hint() const { return type_hint_; }
748
749 private:
750 ExpressionResultScope* outer_;
751 RegisterAllocationScope allocator_;
752 Expression::Context kind_;
753 TypeHint type_hint_;
754};

774// Scoped class used when the result of the current expression to be
775// evaluated is only tested with jumps to two branches.
776class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::TestResultScope final
777 : public ExpressionResultScope {
778 public:
779 TestResultScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
780 BytecodeLabels* else_labels, TestFallthrough fallthrough)
781 : ExpressionResultScope(generator, Expression::kTest),
782 result_consumed_by_test_(false),
783 fallthrough_(fallthrough),
784 then_labels_(then_labels),
785 else_labels_(else_labels) {}
786
787 TestResultScope(const TestResultScope&) = delete;
788 TestResultScope& operator=(const TestResultScope&) = delete;
789
790 // Used when code special cases for TestResultScope and consumes any
791 // possible value by testing and jumping to a then/else label.
792 void SetResultConsumedByTest() { result_consumed_by_test_ = true; }
793 bool result_consumed_by_test() { return result_consumed_by_test_; }
794
795 // Inverts the control flow of the operation, swapping the then and else
796 // labels and the fallthrough.
797 void InvertControlFlow() {
798 std::swap(then_labels_, else_labels_);
799 fallthrough_ = inverted_fallthrough();
800 }
801
802 BytecodeLabel* NewThenLabel() { return then_labels_->New(); }
803 BytecodeLabel* NewElseLabel() { return else_labels_->New(); }
804
805 BytecodeLabels* then_labels() const { return then_labels_; }
806 BytecodeLabels* else_labels() const { return else_labels_; }
807
808 void set_then_labels(BytecodeLabels* then_labels) {
809 then_labels_ = then_labels;
810 }
811 void set_else_labels(BytecodeLabels* else_labels) {
812 else_labels_ = else_labels;
813 }
814
815 TestFallthrough fallthrough() const { return fallthrough_; }
816 TestFallthrough inverted_fallthrough() const {
817 switch (fallthrough_) {
818 case TestFallthrough::kThen:
819 return TestFallthrough::kElse;
820 case TestFallthrough::kElse:
821 return TestFallthrough::kThen;
822 default:
823 return TestFallthrough::kNone;
824 }
825 }
826 void set_fallthrough(TestFallthrough fallthrough) {
827 fallthrough_ = fallthrough;
828 }
829
830 private:
831 bool result_consumed_by_test_;
832 TestFallthrough fallthrough_;
833 BytecodeLabels* then_labels_;
834 BytecodeLabels* else_labels_;
835};

837// Used to build a list of toplevel declaration data.
838class BytecodeGenerator::TopLevelDeclarationsBuilder final : public ZoneObject {
839 public:
840 template <typename IsolateT>
841 Handle<FixedArray> AllocateDeclarations(UnoptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
842 BytecodeGenerator* generator,
843 Handle<Script> script,
844 IsolateT* isolate) {
845 DCHECK(has_constant_pool_entry_);
846
847 Handle<FixedArray> data =
848 isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(entry_slots_, AllocationType::kOld);
849
850 int array_index = 0;
851 if (info->scope()->is_module_scope()) {
852 for (Declaration* decl : *info->scope()->declarations()) {
853 Variable* var = decl->var();
854 if (!var->is_used()) continue;
855 if (var->location() != VariableLocation::MODULE) continue;
856#ifdef DEBUG
857 int start = array_index;
858#endif
859 if (decl->IsFunctionDeclaration()) {
860 FunctionLiteral* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl)->fun();
861 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi(
862 Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(f, script, isolate));
863 // Return a null handle if any initial values can't be created. Caller
864 // will set stack overflow.
865 if (sfi.is_null()) return Handle<FixedArray>();
866 data->set(array_index++, *sfi);
867 int literal_index = generator->GetCachedCreateClosureSlot(f);
868 data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(literal_index));
869 DCHECK(var->IsExport());
870 data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(var->index()));
871 DCHECK_EQ(start + kModuleFunctionDeclarationSize, array_index);
872 } else if (var->IsExport() && var->binding_needs_init()) {
873 data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(var->index()));
874 DCHECK_EQ(start + kModuleVariableDeclarationSize, array_index);
875 }
876 }
877 } else {
878 for (Declaration* decl : *info->scope()->declarations()) {
879 Variable* var = decl->var();
880 if (!var->is_used()) continue;
881 if (var->location() != VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED) continue;
882#ifdef DEBUG
883 int start = array_index;
884#endif
885 if (decl->IsVariableDeclaration()) {
886 data->set(array_index++, *var->raw_name()->string());
887 DCHECK_EQ(start + kGlobalVariableDeclarationSize, array_index);
888 } else {
889 FunctionLiteral* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl)->fun();
890 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi(
891 Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(f, script, isolate));
892 // Return a null handle if any initial values can't be created. Caller
893 // will set stack overflow.
894 if (sfi.is_null()) return Handle<FixedArray>();
895 data->set(array_index++, *sfi);
896 int literal_index = generator->GetCachedCreateClosureSlot(f);
897 data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(literal_index));
898 DCHECK_EQ(start + kGlobalFunctionDeclarationSize, array_index);
899 }
900 }
901 }
902 DCHECK_EQ(array_index, data->length());
903 return data;
904 }
905
906 size_t constant_pool_entry() {
907 DCHECK(has_constant_pool_entry_);
908 return constant_pool_entry_;
909 }
910
911 void set_constant_pool_entry(size_t constant_pool_entry) {
912 DCHECK(has_top_level_declaration());
913 DCHECK(!has_constant_pool_entry_);
914 constant_pool_entry_ = constant_pool_entry;
915 has_constant_pool_entry_ = true;
916 }
917
918 void record_global_variable_declaration() {
919 entry_slots_ += kGlobalVariableDeclarationSize;
920 }
921 void record_global_function_declaration() {
922 entry_slots_ += kGlobalFunctionDeclarationSize;
923 }
924 void record_module_variable_declaration() {
925 entry_slots_ += kModuleVariableDeclarationSize;
926 }
927 void record_module_function_declaration() {
928 entry_slots_ += kModuleFunctionDeclarationSize;
929 }
930 bool has_top_level_declaration() { return entry_slots_ > 0; }
931 bool processed() { return processed_; }
932 void mark_processed() { processed_ = true; }
933
934 private:
935 const int kGlobalVariableDeclarationSize = 1;
936 const int kGlobalFunctionDeclarationSize = 2;
937 const int kModuleVariableDeclarationSize = 1;
938 const int kModuleFunctionDeclarationSize = 3;
939
940 size_t constant_pool_entry_ = 0;
941 int entry_slots_ = 0;
942 bool has_constant_pool_entry_ = false;
943 bool processed_ = false;
944};

946class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::CurrentScope final {
947 public:
948 CurrentScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Scope* scope)
949 : generator_(generator), outer_scope_(generator->current_scope()) {
950 if (scope != nullptr) {
951 DCHECK_EQ(outer_scope_, scope->outer_scope());
952 generator_->set_current_scope(scope);
953 }
954 }
955 ~CurrentScope() {
956 if (outer_scope_ != generator_->current_scope()) {
957 generator_->set_current_scope(outer_scope_);
958 }
959 }

968class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::MultipleEntryBlockContextScope {
969 public:
970 MultipleEntryBlockContextScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Scope* scope)
971 : generator_(generator), scope_(scope), is_in_scope_(false) {
972 if (scope) {
973 inner_context_ = generator->register_allocator()->NewRegister();
974 outer_context_ = generator->register_allocator()->NewRegister();
975 generator->BuildNewLocalBlockContext(scope_);
976 generator->builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(inner_context_);
977 }
978 }
979
980 void SetEnteredIf(bool condition) {
981 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(generator_);
982 if (condition && scope_ != nullptr && !is_in_scope_) {
983 EnterScope();
984 } else if (!condition && is_in_scope_) {
985 ExitScope();
986 }
987 }
988
989 ~MultipleEntryBlockContextScope() { DCHECK(!is_in_scope_); }
990
991 MultipleEntryBlockContextScope(const MultipleEntryBlockContextScope&) =
992 delete;
993 MultipleEntryBlockContextScope& operator=(
994 const MultipleEntryBlockContextScope&) = delete;
995
996 private:
997 void EnterScope() {
998 DCHECK(inner_context_.is_valid());
999 DCHECK(outer_context_.is_valid());
1000 DCHECK(!is_in_scope_);
1001 generator_->builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(inner_context_);
1002 current_scope_.emplace(generator_, scope_);
1003 context_scope_.emplace(generator_, scope_, outer_context_);
1004 is_in_scope_ = true;
1005 }
1006
1007 void ExitScope() {
1008 DCHECK(inner_context_.is_valid());
1009 DCHECK(outer_context_.is_valid());
1010 DCHECK(is_in_scope_);
1011 context_scope_ = std::nullopt;
1012 current_scope_ = std::nullopt;
1013 is_in_scope_ = false;
1014 }
1015
1016 BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
1017 Scope* scope_;
1018 Register inner_context_;
1019 Register outer_context_;
1020 bool is_in_scope_;
1021 std::optional<CurrentScope> current_scope_;
1022 std::optional<ContextScope> context_scope_;
1023};

1025class BytecodeGenerator::FeedbackSlotCache : public ZoneObject {
1026 public:
1027 enum class SlotKind {
1028 kStoreGlobalSloppy,
1029 kStoreGlobalStrict,
1030 kSetNamedStrict,
1031 kSetNamedSloppy,
1032 kLoadProperty,
1033 kLoadSuperProperty,
1034 kLoadGlobalNotInsideTypeof,
1035 kLoadGlobalInsideTypeof,
1036 kClosureFeedbackCell
1037 };
1038
1039 explicit FeedbackSlotCache(Zone* zone) : map_(zone) {}
1040
1041 void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, Variable* variable, int slot_index) {
1042 PutImpl(slot_kind, 0, variable, slot_index);
1043 }
1044 void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, AstNode* node, int slot_index) {
1045 PutImpl(slot_kind, 0, node, slot_index);
1046 }
1047 void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, int variable_index, const AstRawString* name,
1048 int slot_index) {
1049 PutImpl(slot_kind, variable_index, name, slot_index);
1050 }
1051 void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, const AstRawString* name, int slot_index) {
1052 PutImpl(slot_kind, 0, name, slot_index);
1053 }
1054
1055 int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, Variable* variable) const {
1056 return GetImpl(slot_kind, 0, variable);
1057 }
1058 int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, AstNode* node) const {
1059 return GetImpl(slot_kind, 0, node);
1060 }
1061 int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, int variable_index,
1062 const AstRawString* name) const {
1063 return GetImpl(slot_kind, variable_index, name);
1064 }
1065 int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, const AstRawString* name) const {
1066 return GetImpl(slot_kind, 0, name);
1067 }
1068
1069 private:
1070 using Key = std::tuple<SlotKind, int, const void*>;
1071
1072 void PutImpl(SlotKind slot_kind, int index, const void* node,
1073 int slot_index) {
1074 Key key = std::make_tuple(slot_kind, index, node);
1075 auto entry = std::make_pair(key, slot_index);
1076 map_.insert(entry);
1077 }
1078
1079 int GetImpl(SlotKind slot_kind, int index, const void* node) const {
1080 Key key = std::make_tuple(slot_kind, index, node);
1081 auto iter = map_.find(key);
1082 if (iter != map_.end()) {
1083 return iter->second;
1084 }
1085 return -1;
1086 }
1087
1088 ZoneMap<Key, int> map_;
1089};

1091// Scoped class to help elide hole checks within a conditionally executed basic
1092// block. Each conditionally executed basic block must have a scope to emit
1093// hole checks correctly.
1094//
1095// The duration of the scope must correspond to a basic block. Numbered
1096// Variables (see Variable::HoleCheckBitmap) are remembered in the bitmap when
1097// the first hole check is emitted. Subsequent hole checks are elided.
1098//
1099// On scope exit, the hole check state at construction time is restored.
1100class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::HoleCheckElisionScope {
1101 public:
1102 explicit HoleCheckElisionScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator)
1103 : HoleCheckElisionScope(&bytecode_generator->hole_check_bitmap_) {}
1104
1105 ~HoleCheckElisionScope() { *bitmap_ = prev_bitmap_value_; }
1106
1107 protected:
1108 explicit HoleCheckElisionScope(Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* bitmap)
1109 : bitmap_(bitmap), prev_bitmap_value_(*bitmap) {}
1110
1111 Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* bitmap_;
1112 Variable::HoleCheckBitmap prev_bitmap_value_;
1113};
1114
1115// Scoped class to help elide hole checks within control flow that branch and
1116// merge.
1117//
1118// Each such control flow construct (e.g., if-else, ternary expressions) must
1119// have a scope to emit hole checks correctly. Additionally, each branch must
1120// have a Branch.
1121//
1122// The Merge or MergeIf method must be called to merge variables that have been
1123// hole-checked along every branch are marked as no longer needing a hole check.
1124//
1125// Example:
1126//
1127// HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
1128// {
1129// HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
1130// Visit(then_branch);
1131// }
1132// {
1133// HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
1134// Visit(else_branch);
1135// }
1136// merge_elider.Merge();
1137//
1138// Conversely, it is incorrect to use this class for control flow constructs
1139// that do not merge (e.g., if without else). HoleCheckElisionScope should be
1140// used for those cases.
1141class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::HoleCheckElisionMergeScope final {
1142 public:
1143 explicit HoleCheckElisionMergeScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator)
1144 : bitmap_(&bytecode_generator->hole_check_bitmap_) {}
1145
1146 ~HoleCheckElisionMergeScope() {
1147 // Did you forget to call Merge or MergeIf?
1148 DCHECK(merge_called_);
1149 }
1150
1151 void Merge() {
1152 DCHECK_NE(UINT64_MAX, merge_value_);
1153 *bitmap_ = merge_value_;
1154#ifdef DEBUG
1155 merge_called_ = true;
1156#endif
1157 }
1158
1159 void MergeIf(bool cond) {
1160 if (cond) Merge();
1161#ifdef DEBUG
1162 merge_called_ = true;
1163#endif
1164 }
1165
1166 class V8_NODISCARD Branch final : public HoleCheckElisionScope {
1167 public:
1168 explicit Branch(HoleCheckElisionMergeScope& merge_into)
1169 : HoleCheckElisionScope(merge_into.bitmap_),
1170 merge_into_bitmap_(&merge_into.merge_value_) {}
1171
1172 ~Branch() { *merge_into_bitmap_ &= *bitmap_; }
1173
1174 private:
1175 Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* merge_into_bitmap_;
1176 };
1177
1178 private:
1179 Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* bitmap_;
1180 Variable::HoleCheckBitmap merge_value_ = UINT64_MAX;
1181
1182#ifdef DEBUG
1183 bool merge_called_ = false;
1184#endif
1185};

1226// LoopScope delimits the scope of {loop}, from its header to its final jump.
1227// It should be constructed iff a (conceptual) back edge should be produced. In
1228// the case of creating a LoopBuilder but never emitting the loop, it is valid
1229// to skip the creation of LoopScope.
1230class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::LoopScope final {
1231 public:
1232 explicit LoopScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator, LoopBuilder* loop)
1233 : bytecode_generator_(bytecode_generator),
1234 parent_loop_scope_(bytecode_generator_->current_loop_scope()),
1235 loop_builder_(loop) {
1236 loop_builder_->LoopHeader();
1237 bytecode_generator_->set_current_loop_scope(this);
1238 bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_++;
1239 }
1240
1241 ~LoopScope() {
1242 bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_--;
1243 bytecode_generator_->set_current_loop_scope(parent_loop_scope_);
1244 DCHECK_GE(bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_, 0);
1245 loop_builder_->JumpToHeader(
1246 bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_,
1247 parent_loop_scope_ ? parent_loop_scope_->loop_builder_ : nullptr);
1248 }
1249
1250 private:
1251 BytecodeGenerator* const bytecode_generator_;
1252 LoopScope* const parent_loop_scope_;
1253 LoopBuilder* const loop_builder_;
1254};

1256class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ForInScope final {
1257 public:
1258 explicit ForInScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator,
1259 ForInStatement* stmt, Register enum_index,
1260 Register cache_type)
1261 : bytecode_generator_(bytecode_generator),
1262 parent_for_in_scope_(bytecode_generator_->current_for_in_scope()),
1263 each_var_(nullptr),
1264 enum_index_(enum_index),
1265 cache_type_(cache_type) {
1266 if (v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode) {
1267 Expression* each = stmt->each();
1268 if (each->IsVariableProxy()) {
1269 Variable* each_var = each->AsVariableProxy()->var();
1270 if (each_var->IsStackLocal()) {
1271 each_var_ = each_var;
1272 bytecode_generator_->SetVariableInRegister(
1273 each_var_,
1274 bytecode_generator_->builder()->Local(each_var_->index()));
1275 }
1276 }
1277 bytecode_generator_->set_current_for_in_scope(this);
1278 }
1279 }
1280
1281 ~ForInScope() {
1282 if (v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode) {
1283 bytecode_generator_->set_current_for_in_scope(parent_for_in_scope_);
1284 }
1285 }
1286
1287 // Get corresponding {ForInScope} for a given {each} variable.
1288 ForInScope* GetForInScope(Variable* each) {
1289 DCHECK(v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode);
1290 ForInScope* scope = this;
1291 do {
1292 if (each == scope->each_var_) break;
1293 scope = scope->parent_for_in_scope_;
1294 } while (scope != nullptr);
1295 return scope;
1296 }
1297
1298 Register enum_index() { return enum_index_; }
1299 Register cache_type() { return cache_type_; }
1300
1301 private:
1302 BytecodeGenerator* const bytecode_generator_;
1303 ForInScope* const parent_for_in_scope_;
1304 Variable* each_var_;
1305 Register enum_index_;
1306 Register cache_type_;
1307};

1334template <typename PropertyT>
1335struct Accessors : public ZoneObject {
1336 Accessors() : getter(nullptr), setter(nullptr) {}
1337 PropertyT* getter;
1338 PropertyT* setter;
1339};
1340
1341// A map from property names to getter/setter pairs allocated in the zone that
1342// also provides a way of accessing the pairs in the order they were first
1343// added so that the generated bytecode is always the same.
1344template <typename PropertyT>
1345class AccessorTable
1346 : public base::TemplateHashMap<Literal, Accessors<PropertyT>,
1347 bool (*)(void*, void*),
1348 ZoneAllocationPolicy> {
1349 public:
1350 explicit AccessorTable(Zone* zone)
1351 : base::TemplateHashMap<Literal, Accessors<PropertyT>,
1352 bool (*)(void*, void*), ZoneAllocationPolicy>(
1353 Literal::Match, ZoneAllocationPolicy(zone)),
1354 zone_(zone) {}
1355
1356 Accessors<PropertyT>* LookupOrInsert(Literal* key) {
1357 auto it = this->find(key, true);
1358 if (it->second == nullptr) {
1359 it->second = zone_->New<Accessors<PropertyT>>();
1360 ordered_accessors_.push_back({key, it->second});
1361 }
1362 return it->second;
1363 }
1364
1365 const std::vector<std::pair<Literal*, Accessors<PropertyT>*>>&
1366 ordered_accessors() {
1367 return ordered_accessors_;
1368 }
1369
1370 private:
1371 std::vector<std::pair<Literal*, Accessors<PropertyT>*>> ordered_accessors_;
1372
1373 Zone* zone_;
1374};

1425 suspend_count_(0),
1426 loop_depth_(0),
1427 hole_check_bitmap_(0),
1428 current_loop_scope_(nullptr),
1429 current_for_in_scope_(nullptr),
1430 catch_prediction_(HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT) {
1431 DCHECK_EQ(closure_scope(), closure_scope()->GetClosureScope());
1432 if (info->has_source_range_map()) {
1433 block_coverage_builder_ = zone()->New<BlockCoverageBuilder>(
1434 zone(), builder(), info->source_range_map());
1435 }
1436}

1441struct NullContextScopeHelper;
1442

1444struct NullContextScopeHelper<Isolate> {
1445 using Type = NullContextScope;
1446};

1449struct NullContextScopeHelper<LocalIsolate> {

1451 public:
1452 explicit DummyNullContextScope(LocalIsolate*) {}
1453 };

1455};

1462template <typename IsolateT>
1463Handle<BytecodeArray> BytecodeGenerator::FinalizeBytecode(
1464 IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Script> script) {
1465 DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
1466#ifdef DEBUG
1467 // Unoptimized compilation should be context-independent. Verify that we don't
1468 // access the native context by nulling it out during finalization.
1469 NullContextScopeFor<IsolateT> null_context_scope(isolate);
1470#endif
1471
1472 AllocateDeferredConstants(isolate, script);
1473
1474 if (block_coverage_builder_) {
1475 Handle<CoverageInfo> coverage_info =
1476 isolate->factory()->NewCoverageInfo(block_coverage_builder_->slots());
1477 info()->set_coverage_info(coverage_info);
1478 if (v8_flags.trace_block_coverage) {
1479 StdoutStream os;
1480 coverage_info->CoverageInfoPrint(os, info()->literal()->GetDebugName());
1481 }
1482 }
1483
1484 if (HasStackOverflow()) return Handle<BytecodeArray>();
1485 Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array = builder()->ToBytecodeArray(isolate);
1486
1487 if (incoming_new_target_or_generator_.is_valid()) {
1488 bytecode_array->set_incoming_new_target_or_generator_register(
1489 incoming_new_target_or_generator_);
1490 }
1491
1492 return bytecode_array;
1493}

1496 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
1497template Handle<BytecodeArray> BytecodeGenerator::FinalizeBytecode(
1498 LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);

1500template <typename IsolateT>
1501Handle<TrustedByteArray> BytecodeGenerator::FinalizeSourcePositionTable(
1502 IsolateT* isolate) {
1503 DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
1504#ifdef DEBUG
1505 // Unoptimized compilation should be context-independent. Verify that we don't
1506 // access the native context by nulling it out during finalization.
1507 NullContextScopeFor<IsolateT> null_context_scope(isolate);
1508#endif
1509
1510 Handle<TrustedByteArray> source_position_table =
1511 builder()->ToSourcePositionTable(isolate);
1512
1513 LOG_CODE_EVENT(isolate,
1514 CodeLinePosInfoRecordEvent(
1515 info_->bytecode_array()->GetFirstBytecodeAddress(),
1516 *source_position_table, JitCodeEvent::BYTE_CODE));
1517
1518 return source_position_table;
1519}

1524BytecodeGenerator::FinalizeSourcePositionTable(LocalIsolate* isolate);

1532template <typename IsolateT>
1533void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateDeferredConstants(IsolateT* isolate,
1534 Handle<Script> script) {
1535 if (top_level_builder()->has_top_level_declaration()) {
1536 // Build global declaration pair array.
1537 Handle<FixedArray> declarations = top_level_builder()->AllocateDeclarations(
1538 info(), this, script, isolate);
1539 if (declarations.is_null()) return SetStackOverflow();
1540 builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(
1541 top_level_builder()->constant_pool_entry(), declarations);
1542 }
1543
1544 // Find or build shared function infos.
1545 for (std::pair<FunctionLiteral*, size_t> literal : function_literals_) {
1546 FunctionLiteral* expr = literal.first;
1547 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1548 Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(expr, script, isolate);
1549 if (shared_info.is_null()) return SetStackOverflow();
1550 builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(
1551 literal.second, indirect_handle(shared_info, isolate));
1552 }
1553
1554 // Find or build shared function infos for the native function templates.
1555 for (std::pair<NativeFunctionLiteral*, size_t> literal :
1556 native_function_literals_) {
1557 // This should only happen for main-thread compilations.
1558 DCHECK((std::is_same<Isolate, v8::internal::Isolate>::value));
1559
1560 NativeFunctionLiteral* expr = literal.first;
1561 v8::Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate);
1562
1563 // Compute the function template for the native function.
1564 v8::Local<v8::FunctionTemplate> info =
1565 expr->extension()->GetNativeFunctionTemplate(
1566 v8_isolate, Utils::ToLocal(expr->name()));
1567 DCHECK(!info.IsEmpty());
1568
1569 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1570 FunctionTemplateInfo::GetOrCreateSharedFunctionInfo(
1571 isolate, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*info), expr->name());
1572 DCHECK(!shared_info.is_null());
1573 builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, shared_info);
1574 }
1575
1576 // Build object literal constant properties
1577 for (std::pair<ObjectLiteralBoilerplateBuilder*, size_t> literal :
1578 object_literals_) {
1579 ObjectLiteralBoilerplateBuilder* object_literal_builder = literal.first;
1580 if (object_literal_builder->properties_count() > 0) {
1581 // If constant properties is an empty fixed array, we've already added it
1582 // to the constant pool when visiting the object literal.
1583 Handle<ObjectBoilerplateDescription> constant_properties =
1584 object_literal_builder->GetOrBuildBoilerplateDescription(isolate);
1585
1586 builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second,
1587 constant_properties);
1588 }
1589 }
1590
1591 // Build array literal constant elements
1592 for (std::pair<ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder*, size_t> literal :
1593 array_literals_) {
1594 ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder* array_literal_builder = literal.first;
1595 Handle<ArrayBoilerplateDescription> constant_elements =
1596 array_literal_builder->GetOrBuildBoilerplateDescription(isolate);
1597 builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, constant_elements);
1598 }
1599
1600 // Build class literal boilerplates.
1601 for (std::pair<ClassLiteral*, size_t> literal : class_literals_) {
1602 ClassLiteral* class_literal = literal.first;
1603 Handle<ClassBoilerplate> class_boilerplate =
1604 ClassBoilerplate::New(isolate, class_literal, AllocationType::kOld);
1605 builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, class_boilerplate);
1606 }
1607
1608 // Build template literals.
1609 for (std::pair<GetTemplateObject*, size_t> literal : template_objects_) {
1610 GetTemplateObject* get_template_object = literal.first;
1611 Handle<TemplateObjectDescription> description =
1612 get_template_object->GetOrBuildDescription(isolate);
1613 builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, description);
1614 }
1615}
1616
1617template void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateDeferredConstants(
1618 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
1619template void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateDeferredConstants(
1620 LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
1621
1622namespace {
1623bool NeedsContextInitialization(DeclarationScope* scope) {
1624 return scope->NeedsContext() && !scope->is_script_scope() &&
1625 !scope->is_module_scope();
1626}
1627} // namespace
1628
1629void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBytecode(uintptr_t stack_limit) {
1630 InitializeAstVisitor(stack_limit);
1631 if (v8_flags.stress_lazy_compilation && local_isolate_->is_main_thread() &&
1632 !local_isolate_->AsIsolate()->bootstrapper()->IsActive()) {
1633 // Trigger stack overflow with 1/stress_lazy_compilation probability.
1634 // Do this only for the main thread compilations because querying random
1635 // numbers from background threads will make the random values dependent
1636 // on the thread scheduling and thus non-deterministic.
1637 stack_overflow_ = local_isolate_->fuzzer_rng()->NextInt(
1638 v8_flags.stress_lazy_compilation) == 0;
1639 }
1640
1641 // Initialize the incoming context.
1642 ContextScope incoming_context(this, closure_scope());
1643
1644 // Initialize control scope.
1645 ControlScopeForTopLevel control(this);
1646
1647 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
1648
1649 AllocateTopLevelRegisters();
1650
1651 builder()->EmitFunctionStartSourcePosition(
1652 info()->literal()->start_position());
1653
1654 if (info()->literal()->CanSuspend()) {
1655 BuildGeneratorPrologue();
1656 }
1657
1658 if (NeedsContextInitialization(closure_scope())) {
1659 // Push a new inner context scope for the function.
1660 BuildNewLocalActivationContext();
1661 ContextScope local_function_context(this, closure_scope());
1662 BuildLocalActivationContextInitialization();
1663 GenerateBytecodeBody();
1664 } else {
1665 GenerateBytecodeBody();
1666 }
1667
1668 // Reset variables with hole check bitmap indices for subsequent compilations
1669 // in the same parsing zone.
1670 for (Variable* var : vars_in_hole_check_bitmap_) {
1671 var->ResetHoleCheckBitmapIndex();
1672 }
1673
1674 // Check that we are not falling off the end.
1675 DCHECK(builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead());
1676}
1677
1678void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBytecodeBody() {
1679 GenerateBodyPrologue();
1680
1681 if (IsBaseConstructor(function_kind())) {
1682 GenerateBaseConstructorBody();
1683 } else if (function_kind() == FunctionKind::kDerivedConstructor) {
1684 GenerateDerivedConstructorBody();
1685 } else if (IsAsyncFunction(function_kind()) ||
1686 IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(function_kind())) {
1687 if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())) {
1688 GenerateAsyncGeneratorFunctionBody();
1689 } else {
1690 GenerateAsyncFunctionBody();
1691 }
1692 } else {
1693 GenerateBodyStatements();
1694 }
1695}
1696
1697void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBodyPrologue() {
1698 // Build the arguments object if it is used.
1699 VisitArgumentsObject(closure_scope()->arguments());
1700
1701 // Build rest arguments array if it is used.
1702 Variable* rest_parameter = closure_scope()->rest_parameter();
1703 VisitRestArgumentsArray(rest_parameter);
1704
1705 // Build assignment to the function name or {.this_function}
1706 // variables if used.
1707 VisitThisFunctionVariable(closure_scope()->function_var());
1708 VisitThisFunctionVariable(closure_scope()->this_function_var());
1709
1710 // Build assignment to {new.target} variable if it is used.
1711 VisitNewTargetVariable(closure_scope()->new_target_var());
1712
1713 // Create a generator object if necessary and initialize the
1714 // {.generator_object} variable.
1715 FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1716 if (IsResumableFunction(literal->kind())) {
1717 BuildGeneratorObjectVariableInitialization();
1718 }
1719
1720 // Emit tracing call if requested to do so.
1721 if (v8_flags.trace) builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kTraceEnter);
1722
1723 // Increment the function-scope block coverage counter.
1724 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(literal, SourceRangeKind::kBody);
1725
1726 // Visit declarations within the function scope.
1727 if (closure_scope()->is_script_scope()) {
1728 VisitGlobalDeclarations(closure_scope()->declarations());
1729 } else if (closure_scope()->is_module_scope()) {
1730 VisitModuleDeclarations(closure_scope()->declarations());
1731 } else {
1732 VisitDeclarations(closure_scope()->declarations());
1733 }
1734
1735 // Emit initializing assignments for module namespace imports (if any).
1736 VisitModuleNamespaceImports();
1737}
1738
1739void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBaseConstructorBody() {
1740 DCHECK(IsBaseConstructor(function_kind()));
1741
1742 FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1743
1744 // The derived constructor case is handled in VisitCallSuper.
1745 if (literal->class_scope_has_private_brand()) {
1746 ClassScope* scope = info()->scope()->outer_scope()->AsClassScope();
1747 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(scope->brand());
1748 BuildPrivateBrandInitialization(builder()->Receiver(), scope->brand());
1749 }
1750
1751 if (literal->requires_instance_members_initializer()) {
1752 BuildInstanceMemberInitialization(Register::function_closure(),
1753 builder()->Receiver());
1754 }
1755
1756 GenerateBodyStatements();
1757}
1758
1759void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateDerivedConstructorBody() {
1760 DCHECK_EQ(FunctionKind::kDerivedConstructor, function_kind());
1761
1762 FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1763
1764 // Per spec, derived constructors can only return undefined or an object;
1765 // other primitives trigger an exception in ConstructStub.
1766 //
1767 // Since the receiver is popped by the callee, derived constructors return
1768 // <this> if the original return value was undefined.
1769 //
1770 // Also per spec, this return value check is done after all user code (e.g.,
1771 // finally blocks) are executed. For example, the following code does not
1772 // throw.
1773 //
1774 // class C extends class {} {
1775 // constructor() {
1776 // try { throw 42; }
1777 // catch(e) { return; }
1778 // finally { super(); }
1779 // }
1780 // }
1781 // new C();
1782 //
1783 // This check is implemented by jumping to the check instead of emitting a
1784 // return bytecode in-place inside derived constructors.
1785 //
1786 // Note that default derived constructors do not need this check as they
1787 // just forward a super call.
1788
1789 BytecodeLabels check_return_value(zone());
1790 Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
1791 ControlScopeForDerivedConstructor control(this, result, &check_return_value);
1792
1793 {
1794 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
1795 GenerateBodyStatementsWithoutImplicitFinalReturn();
1796 }
1797
1798 if (check_return_value.empty()) {
1799 if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
1800 BuildThisVariableLoad();
1801 BuildReturn(literal->return_position());
1802 }
1803 } else {
1804 BytecodeLabels return_this(zone());
1805
1806 if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
1807 builder()->Jump(return_this.New());
1808 }
1809
1810 check_return_value.Bind(builder());
1811 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(result);
1812 builder()->JumpIfUndefined(return_this.New());
1813 BuildReturn(literal->return_position());
1814
1815 {
1816 return_this.Bind(builder());
1817 BuildThisVariableLoad();
1818 BuildReturn(literal->return_position());
1819 }
1820 }
1821}
1822
1823void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateAsyncFunctionBody() {
1824 DCHECK((IsAsyncFunction(function_kind()) &&
1825 !IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())) ||
1826 IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(function_kind()));
1827
1828 // Async functions always return promises. Return values fulfill that promise,
1829 // while synchronously thrown exceptions reject that promise. This is handled
1830 // by surrounding the body statements in a try-catch block as follows:
1831 //
1832 // try {
1833 // <inner_block>
1834 // } catch (.catch) {
1835 // return %_AsyncFunctionReject(.generator_object, .catch);
1836 // }
1837
1838 FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1839
1840 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction outer_catch_prediction = catch_prediction();
1841 // When compiling a REPL script, use UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT to preserve the
1842 // pending message so DevTools can inspect it.
1843 set_catch_prediction(literal->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope()
1844 ? HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT
1845 : HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT);
1846
1847 BuildTryCatch(
1848 [&]() {
1849 GenerateBodyStatements();
1850 set_catch_prediction(outer_catch_prediction);
1851 },
1852 [&](Register context) {
1853 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
1854 builder()
1855 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0])
1856 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]); // exception
1857 if (!literal->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope()) {
1858 builder()->LoadTheHole().SetPendingMessage();
1859 }
1860 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionReject, args);
1861 // TODO(358404372): Should this return have a statement position?
1862 // Without one it is not possible to apply a debugger breakpoint.
1863 BuildReturn(kNoSourcePosition);
1864 },
1865 catch_prediction());
1866}
1867
1868void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateAsyncGeneratorFunctionBody() {
1869 DCHECK(IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind()));
1870 set_catch_prediction(HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT);
1871
1872 // For ES2017 Async Generators, we produce:
1873 //
1874 // try {
1875 // InitialYield;
1876 // ...body...;
1877 // } catch (.catch) {
1878 // %AsyncGeneratorReject(generator, .catch);
1879 // } finally {
1880 // %_GeneratorClose(generator);
1881 // }
1882 //
1883 // - InitialYield yields the actual generator object.
1884 // - Any return statement inside the body will have its argument wrapped
1885 // in an iterator result object with a "done" property set to `true`.
1886 // - If the generator terminates for whatever reason, we must close it.
1887 // Hence the finally clause.
1888 // - BytecodeGenerator performs special handling for ReturnStatements in
1889 // async generator functions, resolving the appropriate Promise with an
1890 // "done" iterator result object containing a Promise-unwrapped value.
1891
1892 // In async generator functions, when parameters are not simple,
1893 // a parameter initialization block will be added as the first block to the
1894 // AST. Since this block can throw synchronously, it should not be wrapped
1895 // in the following try-finally. We visit this block outside the try-finally
1896 // and remove it from the AST.
1897 int start = 0;
1898 ZonePtrList<Statement>* statements = info()->literal()->body();
1899 Statement* stmt = statements->at(0);
1900 if (stmt->IsBlock()) {
1901 Block* block = static_cast<Block*>(statements->at(0));
1902 if (block->is_initialization_block_for_parameters()) {
1903 VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(block);
1904 start = 1;
1905 }
1906 }
1907
1908 BuildTryFinally(
1909 [&]() {
1910 BuildTryCatch(
1911 [&]() { GenerateBodyStatements(start); },
1912 [&](Register context) {
1913 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
1914 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
1915 builder()
1916 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0])
1917 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // exception
1918 .LoadTheHole()
1919 .SetPendingMessage()
1920 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorReject, args);
1921 execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
1922 },
1923 catch_prediction());
1924 },
1925 [&](Register body_continuation_token, Register body_continuation_result) {
1926 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
1927 Register arg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
1928 builder()
1929 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), arg)
1930 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineGeneratorClose, arg);
1931 },
1932 catch_prediction());
1933}
1934
1935void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBodyStatements(int start) {
1936 GenerateBodyStatementsWithoutImplicitFinalReturn(start);
1937
1938 // Emit an implicit return instruction in case control flow can fall off the
1939 // end of the function without an explicit return being present on all paths.
1940 //
1941 // ControlScope is used instead of building the Return bytecode directly, as
1942 // the entire body is wrapped in a try-finally block for async generators.
1943 if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
1944 builder()->LoadUndefined();
1945 const int pos = info()->literal()->return_position();
1946 if (IsAsyncFunction(function_kind()) ||
1947 IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(function_kind())) {
1948 execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(pos);
1949 } else {
1950 execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(pos);
1951 }
1952 }
1953}
1954
1955void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBodyStatementsWithoutImplicitFinalReturn(
1956 int start) {
1957 ZonePtrList<Statement>* body = info()->literal()->body();
1958 if (v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management && closure_scope() != nullptr &&
1959 (closure_scope()->has_using_declaration() ||
1960 closure_scope()->has_await_using_declaration())) {
1961 BuildDisposeScope([&]() { VisitStatements(body, start); },
1962 closure_scope()->has_await_using_declaration());
1963 } else {
1964 VisitStatements(body, start);
1965 }
1966}
1967
1968void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateTopLevelRegisters() {
1969 if (IsResumableFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) {
1970 // Either directly use generator_object_var or allocate a new register for
1971 // the incoming generator object.
1972 Variable* generator_object_var = closure_scope()->generator_object_var();
1973 if (generator_object_var->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
1974 incoming_new_target_or_generator_ =
1975 GetRegisterForLocalVariable(generator_object_var);
1976 } else {
1977 incoming_new_target_or_generator_ = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
1978 }
1979 } else if (closure_scope()->new_target_var()) {
1980 // Either directly use new_target_var or allocate a new register for
1981 // the incoming new target object.
1982 Variable* new_target_var = closure_scope()->new_target_var();
1983 if (new_target_var->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
1984 incoming_new_target_or_generator_ =
1985 GetRegisterForLocalVariable(new_target_var);
1986 } else {
1987 incoming_new_target_or_generator_ = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
1988 }
1989 }
1990}
1991
1992void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGeneratorPrologue() {
1993 DCHECK_GT(info()->literal()->suspend_count(), 0);
1994 DCHECK(generator_object().is_valid());
1995 generator_jump_table_ =
1996 builder()->AllocateJumpTable(info()->literal()->suspend_count(), 0);
1997
1998 // If the generator is not undefined, this is a resume, so perform state
1999 // dispatch.
2000 builder()->SwitchOnGeneratorState(generator_object(), generator_jump_table_);
2001
2002 // Otherwise, fall-through to the ordinary function prologue, after which we
2003 // will run into the generator object creation and other extra code inserted
2004 // by the parser.
2005}
2006
2007void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBlock(Block* stmt) {
2008 // Visit declarations and statements.
2009 CurrentScope current_scope(this, stmt->scope());
2010 if (stmt->scope() != nullptr && stmt->scope()->NeedsContext()) {
2011 BuildNewLocalBlockContext(stmt->scope());
2012 ContextScope scope(this, stmt->scope());
2013 VisitBlockMaybeDispose(stmt);
2014 } else {
2015 VisitBlockMaybeDispose(stmt);
2016 }
2017}
2018
2019void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBlockMaybeDispose(Block* stmt) {
2020 if (v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management && stmt->scope() != nullptr &&
2021 (stmt->scope()->has_using_declaration() ||
2022 stmt->scope()->has_await_using_declaration())) {
2023 BuildDisposeScope([&]() { VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(stmt); },
2024 stmt->scope()->has_await_using_declaration());
2025 } else {
2026 VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(stmt);
2027 }
2028}
2029
2030void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(Block* stmt) {
2031 BlockBuilder block_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt);
2032 ControlScopeForBreakable execution_control(this, stmt, &block_builder);
2033 if (stmt->scope() != nullptr) {
2034 VisitDeclarations(stmt->scope()->declarations());
2035 }
2036 if (V8_UNLIKELY(stmt->is_breakable())) {
2037 // Loathsome labeled blocks can be the target of break statements, which
2038 // causes unconditional blocks to act conditionally, and therefore to
2039 // require their own elision scope.
2040 //
2041 // lbl: {
2042 // if (cond) break lbl;
2043 // x;
2044 // }
2045 // x; <-- Cannot elide TDZ check
2046 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2047 VisitStatements(stmt->statements());
2048 } else {
2049 VisitStatements(stmt->statements());
2050 }
2051}
2052
2053void BytecodeGenerator::VisitVariableDeclaration(VariableDeclaration* decl) {
2054 Variable* variable = decl->var();
2055 // Unused variables don't need to be visited.
2056 if (!variable->is_used()) return;
2057
2058 switch (variable->location()) {
2059 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
2060 case VariableLocation::MODULE:
2061 UNREACHABLE();
2062 case VariableLocation::LOCAL:
2063 if (variable->binding_needs_init()) {
2064 Register destination(builder()->Local(variable->index()));
2065 builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
2066 }
2067 break;
2068 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
2069 if (variable->binding_needs_init()) {
2070 Register destination(builder()->Parameter(variable->index()));
2071 builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
2072 }
2073 break;
2074 case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL:
2075 // REPL let's are stored in script contexts. They get initialized
2076 // with the hole the same way as normal context allocated variables.
2077 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT:
2078 if (variable->binding_needs_init()) {
2079 DCHECK_EQ(0, execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope()));
2080 builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreContextSlot(execution_context()->reg(),
2081 variable, 0);
2082 }
2083 break;
2084 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
2085 DCHECK_EQ(VariableMode::kDynamic, variable->mode());
2086 DCHECK(!variable->binding_needs_init());
2087
2088 Register name = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2089
2090 builder()
2091 ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
2092 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name)
2093 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kDeclareEvalVar, name);
2094 break;
2095 }
2096 }
2097}
2098
2099void BytecodeGenerator::VisitFunctionDeclaration(FunctionDeclaration* decl) {
2100 Variable* variable = decl->var();
2101 DCHECK(variable->mode() == VariableMode::kLet ||
2102 variable->mode() == VariableMode::kVar ||
2103 variable->mode() == VariableMode::kDynamic);
2104 // Unused variables don't need to be visited.
2105 if (!variable->is_used()) return;
2106
2107 switch (variable->location()) {
2108 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
2109 case VariableLocation::MODULE:
2110 UNREACHABLE();
2111 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
2112 case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
2113 VisitFunctionLiteral(decl->fun());
2114 BuildVariableAssignment(variable, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
2115 break;
2116 }
2117 case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL:
2118 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
2119 DCHECK_EQ(0, execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope()));
2120 VisitFunctionLiteral(decl->fun());
2121 builder()->StoreContextSlot(execution_context()->reg(), variable, 0);
2122 break;
2123 }
2124 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
2125 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
2126 builder()
2127 ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
2128 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]);
2129 VisitFunctionLiteral(decl->fun());
2130 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]).CallRuntime(
2131 Runtime::kDeclareEvalFunction, args);
2132 break;
2133 }
2134 }
2135 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2136 eager_inner_literals_ != nullptr && decl->fun()->ShouldEagerCompile(),
2137 IsInEagerLiterals(decl->fun(), *eager_inner_literals_));
2138}
2139
2140void BytecodeGenerator::VisitModuleNamespaceImports() {
2141 if (!closure_scope()->is_module_scope()) return;
2142
2143 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2144 Register module_request = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2145
2146 SourceTextModuleDescriptor* descriptor =
2147 closure_scope()->AsModuleScope()->module();
2148 for (auto entry : descriptor->namespace_imports()) {
2149 builder()
2150 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(entry->module_request))
2151 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(module_request)
2152 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kGetModuleNamespace, module_request);
2153 Variable* var = closure_scope()->LookupInModule(entry->local_name);
2154 BuildVariableAssignment(var, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
2155 }
2156}
2157
2158void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDeclareCall(Runtime::FunctionId id) {
2159 if (!top_level_builder()->has_top_level_declaration()) return;
2160 DCHECK(!top_level_builder()->processed());
2161
2162 top_level_builder()->set_constant_pool_entry(
2163 builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry());
2164
2165 // Emit code to declare globals.
2166 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
2167 builder()
2168 ->LoadConstantPoolEntry(top_level_builder()->constant_pool_entry())
2169 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
2170 .MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), args[1])
2171 .CallRuntime(id, args);
2172
2173 top_level_builder()->mark_processed();
2174}
2175
2176void BytecodeGenerator::VisitModuleDeclarations(Declaration::List* decls) {
2177 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2178 for (Declaration* decl : *decls) {
2179 Variable* var = decl->var();
2180 if (!var->is_used()) continue;
2181 if (var->location() == VariableLocation::MODULE) {
2182 if (decl->IsFunctionDeclaration()) {
2183 DCHECK(var->IsExport());
2184 FunctionDeclaration* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl);
2185 AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(f->fun());
2186 top_level_builder()->record_module_function_declaration();
2187 } else if (var->IsExport() && var->binding_needs_init()) {
2188 DCHECK(decl->IsVariableDeclaration());
2189 top_level_builder()->record_module_variable_declaration();
2190 }
2191 } else {
2192 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
2193 Visit(decl);
2194 }
2195 }
2196 BuildDeclareCall(Runtime::kDeclareModuleExports);
2197}
2198
2199void BytecodeGenerator::VisitGlobalDeclarations(Declaration::List* decls) {
2200 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2201 for (Declaration* decl : *decls) {
2202 Variable* var = decl->var();
2203 DCHECK(var->is_used());
2204 if (var->location() == VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED) {
2205 // var or function.
2206 if (decl->IsFunctionDeclaration()) {
2207 top_level_builder()->record_global_function_declaration();
2208 FunctionDeclaration* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl);
2209 AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(f->fun());
2210 } else {
2211 top_level_builder()->record_global_variable_declaration();
2212 }
2213 } else {
2214 // let or const. Handled in NewScriptContext.
2215 DCHECK(decl->IsVariableDeclaration());
2216 DCHECK(IsLexicalVariableMode(var->mode()));
2217 }
2218 }
2219
2220 BuildDeclareCall(Runtime::kDeclareGlobals);
2221}
2222
2223void BytecodeGenerator::VisitDeclarations(Declaration::List* declarations) {
2224 for (Declaration* decl : *declarations) {
2225 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2226 Visit(decl);
2227 }
2228}

2231 const ZonePtrList<Statement>* statements, int start) {
2232 for (int i = start; i < statements->length(); i++) {
2233 // Allocate an outer register allocations scope for the statement.
2234 RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);

2236 Visit(stmt);
2237 if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) break;
2238 }

2247
2248void BytecodeGenerator::VisitIfStatement(IfStatement* stmt) {
2249 ConditionalControlFlowBuilder conditional_builder(
2250 builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt);
2251 builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt);
2252
2253 if (stmt->condition()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
2254 // Generate then block unconditionally as always true.
2255 conditional_builder.Then();
2256 Visit(stmt->then_statement());
2257 } else if (stmt->condition()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
2258 // Generate else block unconditionally if it exists.
2259 if (stmt->HasElseStatement()) {
2260 conditional_builder.Else();
2261 Visit(stmt->else_statement());
2262 }
2263 } else {
2264 // TODO(oth): If then statement is BreakStatement or
2265 // ContinueStatement we can reduce number of generated
2266 // jump/jump_ifs here. See BasicLoops test.
2267 VisitForTest(stmt->condition(), conditional_builder.then_labels(),
2268 conditional_builder.else_labels(), TestFallthrough::kThen);
2269
2270 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
2271 {
2272 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
2273 conditional_builder.Then();
2274 Visit(stmt->then_statement());
2275 }
2276
2277 {
2278 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
2279 if (stmt->HasElseStatement()) {
2280 conditional_builder.JumpToEnd();
2281 conditional_builder.Else();
2282 Visit(stmt->else_statement());
2283 }
2284 }
2285
2286 merge_elider.Merge();
2287 }
