2330
2331bool IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(Expression* expr) {
2332 if (expr->IsSmiLiteral() ||
2333 (expr->IsLiteral() && expr->AsLiteral()->IsNumber() &&
2334 expr->AsLiteral()->AsNumber() == 0.0)) {
2335 return true;
2336#ifdef DEBUG
2337 } else if (expr->IsLiteral() && expr->AsLiteral()->IsNumber()) {
2338 DCHECK(!IsSmiDouble(expr->AsLiteral()->AsNumber()));
2339#endif
2340 }
2341 return false;
2342}
2343
2344// Precondition: we called IsSmiLiteral to check this.
2345inline int ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(Expression* expr) {
2346 if (V8_LIKELY(expr->IsSmiLiteral())) {
2347 return expr->AsLiteral()->AsSmiLiteral().value();
2348 } else {
2349 // Only the zero case is possible otherwise.
2350 DCHECK(expr->IsLiteral() && expr->AsLiteral()->IsNumber() &&
2351 expr->AsLiteral()->AsNumber() == -0.0);
2352 return 0;
2353 }
2354}
2355
2356// Is the range of Smi's small enough relative to number of cases?
2357inline bool IsSpreadAcceptable(int spread, int ncases) {
2358 return spread < v8_flags.switch_table_spread_threshold * ncases;
2359}
2360
2361struct SwitchInfo {
2362 static const int kDefaultNotFound = -1;
2363
2364 std::map<int, CaseClause*> covered_cases;
2365 int default_case;
2366
2367 SwitchInfo() { default_case = kDefaultNotFound; }
2368
2369 bool DefaultExists() { return default_case != kDefaultNotFound; }
2370 bool CaseExists(int j) {
2371 return covered_cases.find(j) != covered_cases.end();
2372 }
2373 bool CaseExists(Expression* expr) {
2374 return IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(expr)
2375 ? CaseExists(ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(expr))
2376 : false;
2377 }
2378 CaseClause* GetClause(int j) { return covered_cases[j]; }
2379
2380 bool IsDuplicate(CaseClause* clause) {
2381 return IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(clause->label()) &&
2382 CaseExists(clause->label()) &&
2383 clause != GetClause(ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(clause->label()));
2384 }
2385 int MinCase() {
2386 return covered_cases.empty() ? INT_MAX : covered_cases.begin()->first;
2387 }
2388 int MaxCase() {
2389 return covered_cases.empty() ? INT_MIN : covered_cases.rbegin()->first;
2390 }
2391 void Print() {
2392 std::cout << "Covered_cases: " << '\n';
2393 for (auto iter = covered_cases.begin(); iter != covered_cases.end();
2394 ++iter) {
2395 std::cout << iter->first << "->" << iter->second << '\n';
2396 }
2397 std::cout << "Default_case: " << default_case << '\n';
2398 }
2399};
2400
2401// Checks whether we should use a jump table to implement a switch operation.
2402bool IsSwitchOptimizable(SwitchStatement* stmt, SwitchInfo* info) {
2403 ZonePtrList<CaseClause>* cases = stmt->cases();
2404
2405 for (int i = 0; i < cases->length(); ++i) {
2406 CaseClause* clause = cases->at(i);
2407 if (clause->is_default()) {
2408 continue;
2409 } else if (!(clause->label()->IsLiteral())) {
2410 // Don't consider Smi cases after a non-literal, because we
2411 // need to evaluate the non-literal.
2412 break;
2413 } else if (IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(clause->label())) {
2414 int value = ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(clause->label());
2415 info->covered_cases.insert({value, clause});
2416 }
2417 }
2418
2419 // GCC also jump-table optimizes switch statements with 6 cases or more.
2420 if (static_cast<int>(info->covered_cases.size()) >=
2421 v8_flags.switch_table_min_cases) {
2422 // Due to case spread will be used as the size of jump-table,
2423 // we need to check if it doesn't overflow by casting its
2424 // min and max bounds to int64_t, and calculate if the difference is less
2425 // than or equal to INT_MAX.
2426 int64_t min = static_cast<int64_t>(info->MinCase());
2427 int64_t max = static_cast<int64_t>(info->MaxCase());
2428 int64_t spread = max - min + 1;
2429
2430 DCHECK_GT(spread, 0);
2431
2432 // Check if casted spread is acceptable and doesn't overflow.
2433 if (spread <= INT_MAX &&
2434 IsSpreadAcceptable(static_cast<int>(spread), cases->length())) {
2435 return true;
2436 }
2437 }
2438 // Invariant- covered_cases has all cases and only cases that will go in the
2439 // jump table.
2440 info->covered_cases.clear();
2441 return false;
2442}
2443
2444} // namespace
2445
2446// This adds a jump table optimization for switch statements with Smi cases.
2447// If there are 5+ non-duplicate Smi clauses, and they are sufficiently compact,
2448// we generate a jump table. In the fall-through path, we put the compare-jumps
2449// for the non-Smi cases.
2450
2451// e.g.
2452//
2453// switch(x){
2454// case -0: out = 10;
2455// case 1: out = 11; break;
2456// case 0: out = 12; break;
2457// case 2: out = 13;
2458// case 3: out = 14; break;
2459// case 0.5: out = 15; break;
2460// case 4: out = 16;
2461// case y: out = 17;
2462// case 5: out = 18;
2463// default: out = 19; break;
2464// }
2465
2466// becomes this pseudo-bytecode:
2467
2468// lda x
2469// star r1
2470// test_type number
2471// jump_if_false @fallthrough
2472// ldar r1
2473// test_greater_than_or_equal_to smi_min
2474// jump_if_false @fallthrough
2475// ldar r1
2476// test_less_than_or_equal_to smi_max
2477// jump_if_false @fallthrough
2478// ldar r1
2479// bitwise_or 0
2480// star r2
2481// test_strict_equal r1
2482// jump_if_false @fallthrough
2483// ldar r2
2484// switch_on_smi {1: @case_1, 2: @case_2, 3: @case_3, 4: @case_4}
2485// @fallthrough:
2486// jump_if_strict_equal -0.0 @case_minus_0.0
2487// jump_if_strict_equal 0.5 @case_0.5
2488// jump_if_strict_equal y @case_y
2489// jump_if_strict_equal 5 @case_5
2490// jump @default
2491// @case_minus_0.0:
2492// <out = 10>
2493// @case_1
2494// <out = 11, break>
2495// @case_0:
2496// <out = 12, break>
2497// @case_2:
2498// <out = 13>
2499// @case_3:
2500// <out = 14, break>
2501// @case_0.5:
2502// <out = 15, break>
2503// @case_4:
2504// <out = 16>
2505// @case_y:
2506// <out = 17>
2507// @case_5:
2508// <out = 18>
2509// @default:
2510// <out = 19, break>
2511
2512void BytecodeGenerator::VisitSwitchStatement(SwitchStatement* stmt) {
2513 // We need this scope because we visit for register values. We have to
2514 // maintain an execution result scope where registers can be allocated.
2515 ZonePtrList<CaseClause>* clauses = stmt->cases();
2516
2517 SwitchInfo info;
2518 BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table = nullptr;
2519 bool use_jump_table = IsSwitchOptimizable(stmt, &info);
2520
2521 // N_comp_cases is number of cases we will generate comparison jumps for.
2522 // Note we ignore duplicate cases, since they are very unlikely.
2523
2524 int n_comp_cases = clauses->length();
2525 if (use_jump_table) {
2526 n_comp_cases -= static_cast<int>(info.covered_cases.size());
2527 jump_table = builder()->AllocateJumpTable(
2528 info.MaxCase() - info.MinCase() + 1, info.MinCase());
2529 }
2530
2531 // Are we still using any if-else bytecodes to evaluate the switch?
2532 bool use_jumps = n_comp_cases != 0;
2533
2534 // Does the comparison for non-jump table jumps need an elision scope?
2535 bool jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope = false;
2536
2537 SwitchBuilder switch_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
2538 n_comp_cases, jump_table);
2539 ControlScopeForBreakable scope(this, stmt, &switch_builder);
2540 builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt);
2541
2542 VisitForAccumulatorValue(stmt->tag());
2543
2544 if (use_jump_table) {
2545 // Release temps so that they can be reused in clauses.
2546 RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
2547 // This also fills empty slots in jump table.
2548 Register r2 = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2549
2550 Register r1 = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2551 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r1);
2552
2553 builder()->CompareTypeOf(TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kNumber);
2554 switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2555 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2556
2557 // TODO(leszeks): Note these are duplicated range checks with the
2558 // SwitchOnSmi handler for the most part.
2559
2560 builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::kMinValue);
2561 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r2);
2562 builder()->CompareOperation(
2563 Token::kGreaterThanEq, r1,
2564 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()));
2565
2566 switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2567 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2568
2569 builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::kMaxValue);
2570 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r2);
2571 builder()->CompareOperation(
2572 Token::kLessThanEq, r1,
2573 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()));
2574
2575 switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2576 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2577
2578 builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(
2579 Token::kBitOr, Smi::FromInt(0),
2580 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
2581
2582 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r2);
2583 builder()->CompareOperation(
2584 Token::kEqStrict, r1,
2585 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()));
2586
2587 switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2588 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r2);
2589
2590 switch_builder.EmitJumpTableIfExists(info.MinCase(), info.MaxCase(),
2591 info.covered_cases);
2592
2593 if (use_jumps) {
2594 // When using a jump table, the first jump comparison is conditionally
2595 // executed if the discriminant wasn't matched by anything in the jump
2596 // table, and so needs its own elision scope.
2597 jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope = true;
2598 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2599 }
2600 }
2601
2602 int case_compare_ctr = 0;
2603#ifdef DEBUG
2604 std::unordered_map<int, int> case_ctr_checker;
2605#endif
2606
2607 if (use_jumps) {
2608 Register tag_holder = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2609 FeedbackSlot slot = clauses->length() > 0
2610 ? feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()
2611 : FeedbackSlot::Invalid();
2612 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(tag_holder);
2613
2614 {
2615 // The comparisons linearly dominate, so no need to open a new elision
2616 // scope for each one.
2617 std::optional<HoleCheckElisionScope> elider;
2618 for (int i = 0; i < clauses->length(); ++i) {
2619 CaseClause* clause = clauses->at(i);
2620 if (clause->is_default()) {
2621 info.default_case = i;
2622 } else if (!info.CaseExists(clause->label())) {
2623 if (jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope && !elider) {
2624 elider.emplace(this);
2625 }
2626
2627 // Perform label comparison as if via '===' with tag.
2628 VisitForAccumulatorValue(clause->label());
2629 builder()->CompareOperation(Token::kEqStrict, tag_holder,
2630 feedback_index(slot));
2631#ifdef DEBUG
2632 case_ctr_checker[i] = case_compare_ctr;
2633#endif
2634 switch_builder.JumpToCaseIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
2635 case_compare_ctr++);
2636 // The second and subsequent non-default comparisons are always
2637 // conditionally executed, and need an elision scope.
2638 jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope = true;
2639 }
2640 }
2641 }
2642 register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(tag_holder);
2643 }
2644
2645 // For fall-throughs after comparisons (or out-of-range/non-Smi's for jump
2646 // tables).
2647 if (info.DefaultExists()) {
2648 switch_builder.JumpToDefault();
2649 } else {
2650 switch_builder.Break();
2651 }
2652
2653 // It is only correct to merge hole check states if there is a default clause,
2654 // as otherwise it's unknown if the switch is exhaustive.
2655 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
2656
2657 case_compare_ctr = 0;
2658 for (int i = 0; i < clauses->length(); ++i) {
2659 CaseClause* clause = clauses->at(i);
2660 if (i != info.default_case) {
2661 if (!info.IsDuplicate(clause)) {
2662 bool use_table = use_jump_table && info.CaseExists(clause->label());
2663 if (!use_table) {
2664// Guarantee that we should generate compare/jump if no table.
2665#ifdef DEBUG
2666 DCHECK(case_ctr_checker[i] == case_compare_ctr);
2667#endif
2668 switch_builder.BindCaseTargetForCompareJump(case_compare_ctr++,
2669 clause);
2670 } else {
2671 // Use jump table if this is not a duplicate label.
2672 switch_builder.BindCaseTargetForJumpTable(
2673 ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(clause->label()), clause);
2674 }
2675 }
2676 } else {
2677 switch_builder.BindDefault(clause);
2678 }
2679 // Regardless, generate code (in case of fall throughs).
2680 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
2681 VisitStatements(clause->statements());
2682 }
2683
2684 merge_elider.MergeIf(info.DefaultExists());
2685}
2686
2687template <typename TryBodyFunc, typename CatchBodyFunc>
2688void BytecodeGenerator::BuildTryCatch(
2689 TryBodyFunc try_body_func, CatchBodyFunc catch_body_func,
2690 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction catch_prediction,
2691 TryCatchStatement* stmt_for_coverage) {
2692 if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) return;
2693
2694 TryCatchBuilder try_control_builder(
2695 builder(),
2696 stmt_for_coverage == nullptr ? nullptr : block_coverage_builder_,
2697 stmt_for_coverage, catch_prediction);
2698
2699 // Preserve the context in a dedicated register, so that it can be restored
2700 // when the handler is entered by the stack-unwinding machinery.
2701 // TODO(ignition): Be smarter about register allocation.
2702 Register context = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2703 builder()->MoveRegister(Register::current_context(), context);
2704
2705 // Evaluate the try-block inside a control scope. This simulates a handler
2706 // that is intercepting 'throw' control commands.
2707 try_control_builder.BeginTry(context);
2708
2709 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
2710
2711 {
2712 ControlScopeForTryCatch scope(this, &try_control_builder);
2713 // The try-block itself, even though unconditionally executed, can throw
2714 // basically at any point, and so must be treated as conditional from the
2715 // perspective of the hole check elision analysis.
2716 //
2717 // try { x } catch (e) { }
2718 // use(x); <-- Still requires a TDZ check
2719 //
2720 // However, if both the try-block and the catch-block emit a hole check,
2721 // subsequent TDZ checks can be elided.
2722 //
2723 // try { x; } catch (e) { x; }
2724 // use(x); <-- TDZ check can be elided
2725 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
2726 try_body_func();
2727 }
2728 try_control_builder.EndTry();
2729
2730 {
2731 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
2732 catch_body_func(context);
2733 }
2734
2735 merge_elider.Merge();
2736
2737 try_control_builder.EndCatch();
2738}
2739
2740template <typename TryBodyFunc, typename FinallyBodyFunc>
2741void BytecodeGenerator::BuildTryFinally(
2742 TryBodyFunc try_body_func, FinallyBodyFunc finally_body_func,
2743 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction catch_prediction,
2744 TryFinallyStatement* stmt_for_coverage) {
2745 if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) return;
2746
2747 // We can't know whether the finally block will override ("catch") an
2748 // exception thrown in the try block, so we just adopt the outer prediction.
2749 TryFinallyBuilder try_control_builder(
2750 builder(),
2751 stmt_for_coverage == nullptr ? nullptr : block_coverage_builder_,
2752 stmt_for_coverage, catch_prediction);
2753
2754 // We keep a record of all paths that enter the finally-block to be able to
2755 // dispatch to the correct continuation point after the statements in the
2756 // finally-block have been evaluated.
2757 //
2758 // The try-finally construct can enter the finally-block in three ways:
2759 // 1. By exiting the try-block normally, falling through at the end.
2760 // 2. By exiting the try-block with a function-local control flow transfer
2761 // (i.e. through break/continue/return statements).
2762 // 3. By exiting the try-block with a thrown exception.
2763 //
2764 // The result register semantics depend on how the block was entered:
2765 // - ReturnStatement: It represents the return value being returned.
2766 // - ThrowStatement: It represents the exception being thrown.
2767 // - BreakStatement/ContinueStatement: Undefined and not used.
2768 // - Falling through into finally-block: Undefined and not used.
2769 Register token = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2770 Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2771 Register message = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2772 builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(message);
2773 ControlScope::DeferredCommands commands(this, token, result, message);
2774
2775 // Preserve the context in a dedicated register, so that it can be restored
2776 // when the handler is entered by the stack-unwinding machinery.
2777 // TODO(ignition): Be smarter about register allocation.
2778 Register context = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2779 builder()->MoveRegister(Register::current_context(), context);
2780
2781 // Evaluate the try-block inside a control scope. This simulates a handler
2782 // that is intercepting all control commands.
2783 try_control_builder.BeginTry(context);
2784 {
2785 ControlScopeForTryFinally scope(this, &try_control_builder, &commands);
2786 // The try-block itself, even though unconditionally executed, can throw
2787 // basically at any point, and so must be treated as conditional from the
2788 // perspective of the hole check elision analysis.
2789 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2790 try_body_func();
2791 }
2792 try_control_builder.EndTry();
2793
2794 // Record fall-through and exception cases.
2795 if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
2796 commands.RecordFallThroughPath();
2797 }
2798 try_control_builder.LeaveTry();
2799 try_control_builder.BeginHandler();
2800 commands.RecordHandlerReThrowPath();
2801
2802 try_control_builder.BeginFinally();
2803
2804 // Evaluate the finally-block.
2805 finally_body_func(token, result);
2806 try_control_builder.EndFinally();
2807
2808 // Dynamic dispatch after the finally-block.
2809 commands.ApplyDeferredCommands();
2810}
2811
2812template <typename WrappedFunc>
2813void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDisposeScope(WrappedFunc wrapped_func,
2814 bool has_await_using) {
2815 RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
2816 DisposablesStackScope disposables_stack_scope(this);
2817 if (has_await_using) {
2818 set_catch_prediction(info()->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope()
2819 ? HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT
2820 : HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT);
2821 }
2822
2823 BuildTryFinally(
2824 // Try block
2825 [&]() { wrapped_func(); },
2826 // Finally block
2827 [&](Register body_continuation_token, Register body_continuation_result) {
2828 if (has_await_using) {
2829 Register result_register = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2830 Register disposable_stack_register =
2831 register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2832 builder()->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack_,
2833 disposable_stack_register);
2834 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), nullptr, nullptr,
2835 feedback_spec());
2836 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2837
2838 {
2839 RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
2840 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
2841 builder()
2842 ->MoveRegister(disposable_stack_register, args[0])
2843 .MoveRegister(body_continuation_token, args[1])
2844 .MoveRegister(body_continuation_result, args[2])
2845 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(
2846 DisposableStackResourcesType::kAtLeastOneAsync))
2847 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[3]);
2848 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDisposeDisposableStack, args);
2849 }
2850
2851 builder()
2852 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register)
2853 .LoadTrue()
2854 .CompareReference(result_register);
2855
2856 loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
2857
2858 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(result_register);
2859 BuildTryCatch(
2860 [&]() { BuildAwait(); },
2861 [&](Register context) {
2862 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
2863 builder()
2864 ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack_, args[0])
2865 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // exception
2866 .LoadTheHole()
2867 .SetPendingMessage()
2868 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2])
2869 .CallRuntime(
2870 Runtime::kHandleExceptionsInDisposeDisposableStack,
2871 args);
2872
2873 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
2874 disposable_stack_register);
2875 },
2876 catch_prediction());
2877
2878 loop_builder.BindContinueTarget();
2879 } else {
2880 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
2881 builder()
2882 ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack_, args[0])
2883 .MoveRegister(body_continuation_token, args[1])
2884 .MoveRegister(body_continuation_result, args[2])
2885 .LoadLiteral(
2886 Smi::FromEnum(DisposableStackResourcesType::kAllSync))
2887 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[3]);
2888 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDisposeDisposableStack, args);
2889 }
2890 },
2891 catch_prediction());
2892}

2894void BytecodeGenerator::VisitIterationBody(IterationStatement* stmt,
2895 LoopBuilder* loop_builder) {
2896 loop_builder->LoopBody();
2897 ControlScopeForIteration execution_control(this, stmt, loop_builder);
2898 Visit(stmt->body());
2899 loop_builder->BindContinueTarget();
2900}
2901
2902void BytecodeGenerator::VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(
2903 IterationStatement* stmt, LoopBuilder* loop_builder) {
2904 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2905 VisitIterationBody(stmt, loop_builder);
2906}
2907
2908void BytecodeGenerator::VisitDoWhileStatement(DoWhileStatement* stmt) {
2909 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
2910 feedback_spec());
2911 if (stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
2912 // Since we know that the condition is false, we don't create a loop.
2913 // Therefore, we don't create a LoopScope (and thus we don't create a header
2914 // and a JumpToHeader). However, we still need to iterate once through the
2915 // body.
2916 VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2917 } else if (stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
2918 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2919 VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2920 } else {
2921 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2922 VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2923 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->cond());
2924 BytecodeLabels loop_backbranch(zone());
2925 if (!loop_builder.break_labels()->empty()) {
2926 // The test may be conditionally executed if there was a break statement
2927 // inside the loop body, and therefore requires its own elision scope.
2928 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2929 VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_backbranch, loop_builder.break_labels(),
2930 TestFallthrough::kThen);
2931 } else {
2932 VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_backbranch, loop_builder.break_labels(),
2933 TestFallthrough::kThen);
2934 }
2935 loop_backbranch.Bind(builder());
2936 }
2937}
2938
2939void BytecodeGenerator::VisitWhileStatement(WhileStatement* stmt) {
2940 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
2941 feedback_spec());
2942
2943 if (stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
2944 // If the condition is false there is no need to generate the loop.
2945 return;
2946 }
2947
2948 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2949 if (!stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
2950 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->cond());
2951 BytecodeLabels loop_body(zone());
2952 VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_body, loop_builder.break_labels(),
2953 TestFallthrough::kThen);
2954 loop_body.Bind(builder());
2955 }
2956 VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2957}
2958
2959void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForStatement(ForStatement* stmt) {
2960 if (stmt->init() != nullptr) {
2961 Visit(stmt->init());
2962 }
2963
2964 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
2965 feedback_spec());
2966 if (stmt->cond() && stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
2967 // If the condition is known to be false there is no need to generate
2968 // body, next or condition blocks. Init block should be generated.
2969 return;
2970 }
2971
2972 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2973 if (stmt->cond() && !stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
2974 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->cond());
2975 BytecodeLabels loop_body(zone());
2976 VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_body, loop_builder.break_labels(),
2977 TestFallthrough::kThen);
2978 loop_body.Bind(builder());
2979 }
2980
2981 // C-style for loops' textual order differs from dominator order.
2982 //
2983 // for (INIT; TEST; NEXT) BODY
2984 // REST
2985 //
2986 // has the dominator order of
2987 //
2988 // INIT dominates TEST dominates BODY dominates NEXT
2989 // and
2990 // INIT dominates TEST dominates REST
2991 //
2992 // INIT and TEST are always evaluated and so do not have their own
2993 // HoleCheckElisionScope. BODY, like all iteration bodies, can contain control
2994 // flow like breaks or continues, has its own HoleCheckElisionScope. NEXT is
2995 // therefore conditionally evaluated and also so has its own
2996 // HoleCheckElisionScope.
2997 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2998 VisitIterationBody(stmt, &loop_builder);
2999 if (stmt->next() != nullptr) {
3000 builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt->next());
3001 Visit(stmt->next());
3002 }
3003}
3004
3005void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForInStatement(ForInStatement* stmt) {
3006 if (stmt->subject()->IsNullLiteral() ||
3007 stmt->subject()->IsUndefinedLiteral()) {
3008 // ForIn generates lots of code, skip if it wouldn't produce any effects.
3009 return;
3010 }
3011
3012 BytecodeLabel subject_undefined_label;
3013 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddForInSlot();
3014
3015 // Prepare the state for executing ForIn.
3016 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->subject());
3017 VisitForAccumulatorValue(stmt->subject());
3018 builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&subject_undefined_label);
3019 Register receiver = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3020 builder()->ToObject(receiver);
3021
3022 // Used as kRegTriple and kRegPair in ForInPrepare and ForInNext.
3023 RegisterList triple = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
3024 Register cache_length = triple[2];
3025 builder()->ForInEnumerate(receiver);
3026 builder()->ForInPrepare(triple, feedback_index(slot));
3027
3028 // Set up loop counter
3029 Register index = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3030 builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::zero());
3031 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
3032
3033 // The loop
3034 {
3035 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
3036 feedback_spec());
3037 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
3038 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
3039 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->each());
3040 loop_builder.BreakIfForInDone(index, cache_length);
3041 builder()->ForInNext(receiver, index, triple.Truncate(2),
3042 feedback_index(slot));
3043 loop_builder.ContinueIfUndefined();
3044
3045 // Assign accumulator value to the 'each' target.
3046 {
3047 EffectResultScope scope(this);
3048 // Make sure to preserve the accumulator across the PrepareAssignmentLhs
3049 // call.
3050 AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(
3051 stmt->each(), AccumulatorPreservingMode::kPreserve);
3052 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(stmt->each());
3053 BuildAssignment(lhs_data, Token::kAssign, LookupHoistingMode::kNormal);
3054 }
3055
3056 {
3057 Register cache_type = triple[0];
3058 ForInScope scope(this, stmt, index, cache_type);
3059 VisitIterationBody(stmt, &loop_builder);
3060 builder()->ForInStep(index);
3061 }
3062 }
3063 builder()->Bind(&subject_undefined_label);
3064}
3065
3066// Desugar a for-of statement into an application of the iteration protocol.
3067//
3068// for (EACH of SUBJECT) BODY
3069//
3070// becomes
3071//
3072// iterator = %GetIterator(SUBJECT)
3073// try {
3074//
3075// loop {
3076// // Make sure we are considered 'done' if .next(), .done or .value fail.
3077// done = true
3078// value = iterator.next()
3079// if (value.done) break;
3080// value = value.value
3081// done = false
3082//
3083// EACH = value
3084// BODY
3085// }
3086// done = true
3087//
3088// } catch(e) {
3089// iteration_continuation = RETHROW
3090// } finally {
3091// %FinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation)
3092// }
3093void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForOfStatement(ForOfStatement* stmt) {
3094 EffectResultScope effect_scope(this);
3095
3096 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->subject());
3097 VisitForAccumulatorValue(stmt->subject());
3098
3099 // Store the iterator in a dedicated register so that it can be closed on
3100 // exit, and the 'done' value in a dedicated register so that it can be
3101 // changed and accessed independently of the iteration result.
3102 IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(stmt->type());
3103 Register done = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3104 builder()->LoadFalse();
3105 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
3106
3107 BuildTryFinally(
3108 // Try block.
3109 [&]() {
3110 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
3111 feedback_spec());
3112 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
3113
3114 // This doesn't need a HoleCheckElisionScope because BuildTryFinally
3115 // already makes one for try blocks.
3116
3117 builder()->LoadTrue().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
3118
3119 {
3120 RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
3121 Register next_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3122
3123 // Call the iterator's .next() method. Break from the loop if the
3124 // `done` property is truthy, otherwise load the value from the
3125 // iterator result and append the argument.
3126 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->each());
3127 BuildIteratorNext(iterator, next_result);
3128 builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
3129 next_result, ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
3130 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
3131 loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
3132
3133 builder()
3134 // value = value.value
3135 ->LoadNamedProperty(
3136 next_result, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
3137 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
3138 // done = false, before the assignment to each happens, so that done
3139 // is false if the assignment throws.
3140 builder()
3141 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next_result)
3142 .LoadFalse()
3143 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
3144
3145 // Assign to the 'each' target.
3146 AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(stmt->each());
3147 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(next_result);
3148 BuildAssignment(lhs_data, Token::kAssign,
3149 LookupHoistingMode::kNormal);
3150 }
3151
3152 VisitIterationBody(stmt, &loop_builder);
3153 },
3154 // Finally block.
3155 [&](Register iteration_continuation_token,
3156 Register iteration_continuation_result) {
3157 // Finish the iteration in the finally block.
3158 BuildFinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation_token);
3159 },
3160 catch_prediction());
3161}
3162
3163void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTryCatchStatement(TryCatchStatement* stmt) {
3164 // Update catch prediction tracking. The updated catch_prediction value lasts
3165 // until the end of the try_block in the AST node, and does not apply to the
3166 // catch_block.
3167 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction outer_catch_prediction = catch_prediction();
3168 set_catch_prediction(stmt->GetCatchPrediction(outer_catch_prediction));
3169
3170 BuildTryCatch(
3171 // Try body.
3172 [&]() {
3173 Visit(stmt->try_block());
3174 set_catch_prediction(outer_catch_prediction);
3175 },
3176 // Catch body.
3177 [&](Register context) {
3178 if (stmt->scope()) {
3179 // Create a catch scope that binds the exception.
3180 BuildNewLocalCatchContext(stmt->scope());
3181 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(context);
3182 }
3183
3184 // If requested, clear message object as we enter the catch block.
3185 if (stmt->ShouldClearException(outer_catch_prediction)) {
3186 builder()->LoadTheHole().SetPendingMessage();
3187 }
3188
3189 // Load the catch context into the accumulator.
3190 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(context);
3191
3192 // Evaluate the catch-block.
3193 if (stmt->scope()) {
3194 VisitInScope(stmt->catch_block(), stmt->scope());
3195 } else {
3196 VisitBlock(stmt->catch_block());
3197 }
3198 },
3199 catch_prediction(), stmt);
3200}
3201
3202void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTryFinallyStatement(TryFinallyStatement* stmt) {
3203 BuildTryFinally(
3204 // Try block.
3205 [&]() { Visit(stmt->try_block()); },
3206 // Finally block.
3207 [&](Register body_continuation_token, Register body_continuation_result) {
3208 Visit(stmt->finally_block());
3209 },
3210 catch_prediction(), stmt);
3211}

3218void BytecodeGenerator::VisitFunctionLiteral(FunctionLiteral* expr) {
3219 CHECK_LT(info_->literal()->function_literal_id(),
3220 expr->function_literal_id());
3221 DCHECK_EQ(expr->scope()->outer_scope(), current_scope());
3222 uint8_t flags = CreateClosureFlags::Encode(
3223 expr->pretenure(), closure_scope()->is_function_scope(),
3224 info()->flags().might_always_turbofan());
3225 size_t entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
3226 builder()->CreateClosure(entry, GetCachedCreateClosureSlot(expr), flags);
3227 function_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr, entry));
3228 AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(expr);
3229}
3230
3231void BytecodeGenerator::AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(FunctionLiteral* literal) {
3232 // Only parallel compile when there's a script (not the case for source
3233 // position collection).
3234 if (!script_.is_null() && literal->should_parallel_compile()) {
3235 // If we should normally be eagerly compiling this function, we must be here
3236 // because of post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_eager_toplevel.
3237 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
3238 literal->ShouldEagerCompile(),
3239 info()->flags().post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_eager_toplevel());
3240 // There exists a lazy compile dispatcher.
3241 DCHECK(info()->dispatcher());
3242 // There exists a cloneable character stream.
3243 DCHECK(info()->character_stream()->can_be_cloned_for_parallel_access());
3244
3245 UnparkedScopeIfOnBackground scope(local_isolate_);
3246 // If there doesn't already exist a SharedFunctionInfo for this function,
3247 // then create one and enqueue it. Otherwise, we're reparsing (e.g. for the
3248 // debugger, source position collection, call printing, recompile after
3249 // flushing, etc.) and don't want to over-compile.
3250 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
3251 Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(literal, script_, local_isolate_);
3252 if (!shared_info->is_compiled()) {
3253 info()->dispatcher()->Enqueue(
3254 local_isolate_, indirect_handle(shared_info, local_isolate_),
3255 info()->character_stream()->Clone());
3256 }
3257 } else if (eager_inner_literals_ && literal->ShouldEagerCompile()) {
3258 DCHECK(!IsInEagerLiterals(literal, *eager_inner_literals_));
3259 DCHECK(!literal->should_parallel_compile());
3260 eager_inner_literals_->push_back(literal);
3261 }
3262}
3263
3264void BytecodeGenerator::BuildClassLiteral(ClassLiteral* expr, Register name) {
3265 size_t class_boilerplate_entry =
3266 builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
3267 class_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr, class_boilerplate_entry));
3268
3269 VisitDeclarations(expr->scope()->declarations());
3270 Register class_constructor = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3271
3272 // Create the class brand symbol and store it on the context during class
3273 // evaluation. This will be stored in the instance later in the constructor.
3274 // We do this early so that invalid access to private methods or accessors
3275 // in computed property keys throw.
3276 if (expr->scope()->brand() != nullptr) {
3277 Register brand = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3278 const AstRawString* class_name =
3279 expr->scope()->class_variable() != nullptr
3280 ? expr->scope()->class_variable()->raw_name()
3281 : ast_string_constants()->anonymous_string();
3282 builder()
3283 ->LoadLiteral(class_name)
3284 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand)
3285 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateBrandSymbol, brand);
3286 register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(brand);
3287
3288 BuildVariableAssignment(expr->scope()->brand(), Token::kInit,
3289 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3290 }
3291
3292 AccessorTable<ClassLiteral::Property> private_accessors(zone());
3293 for (int i = 0; i < expr->private_members()->length(); i++) {
3294 ClassLiteral::Property* property = expr->private_members()->at(i);
3295 DCHECK(property->is_private());
3296 switch (property->kind()) {
3297 case ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD: {
3298 // Initialize the private field variables early.
3299 // Create the private name symbols for fields during class
3300 // evaluation and store them on the context. These will be
3301 // used as keys later during instance or static initialization.
3302 RegisterAllocationScope private_name_register_scope(this);
3303 Register private_name = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3304 VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), private_name);
3305 builder()
3306 ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
3307 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(private_name)
3308 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateNameSymbol, private_name);
3309 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(property->private_name_var());
3310 BuildVariableAssignment(property->private_name_var(), Token::kInit,
3311 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3312 break;
3313 }
3314 case ClassLiteral::Property::METHOD: {
3315 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3316 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3317 BuildVariableAssignment(property->private_name_var(), Token::kInit,
3318 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3319 break;
3320 }
3321 // Collect private accessors into a table to merge the creation of
3322 // those closures later.
3323 case ClassLiteral::Property::GETTER: {
3324 Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
3325 DCHECK_NULL(private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->getter);
3326 private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->getter = property;
3327 break;
3328 }
3329 case ClassLiteral::Property::SETTER: {
3330 Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
3331 DCHECK_NULL(private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->setter);
3332 private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->setter = property;
3333 break;
3334 }
3335 case ClassLiteral::Property::AUTO_ACCESSOR: {
3336 Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
3337 RegisterAllocationScope private_name_register_scope(this);
3338 Register accessor_storage_private_name =
3339 register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3340 Variable* accessor_storage_private_name_var =
3341 property->auto_accessor_info()
3342 ->accessor_storage_name_proxy()
3343 ->var();
3344 // We reuse the already internalized
3345 // ".accessor-storage-<accessor_number>" strings that were defined in
3346 // the parser instead of the "<name>accessor storage" string from the
3347 // spec. The downsides are that is that these are the property names
3348 // that will show up in devtools and in error messages.
3349 // Additionally, a property can share a name with the corresponding
3350 // property of their parent class, i.e. for classes defined as
3351 // "class C {accessor x}" and "class D extends C {accessor y}",
3352 // if "d = new D()", then d.x and d.y will share the name
3353 // ".accessor-storage-0", (but a different private symbol).
3354 // TODO(42202709): Get to a resolution on how to handle this naming
3355 // issue before shipping the feature.
3356 builder()
3357 ->LoadLiteral(accessor_storage_private_name_var->raw_name())
3358 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(accessor_storage_private_name)
3359 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateNameSymbol,
3360 accessor_storage_private_name);
3361 BuildVariableAssignment(accessor_storage_private_name_var, Token::kInit,
3362 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3363 auto* accessor_pair = private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key);
3364 DCHECK_NULL(accessor_pair->getter);
3365 accessor_pair->getter = property;
3366 DCHECK_NULL(accessor_pair->setter);
3367 accessor_pair->setter = property;
3368 break;
3369 }
3370 default:
3371 UNREACHABLE();
3372 }
3373 }
3374
3375 {
3376 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3377 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
3378
3379 Register class_boilerplate = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3380 Register class_constructor_in_args =
3381 register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3382 Register super_class = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3383 DCHECK_EQ(ClassBoilerplate::kFirstDynamicArgumentIndex,
3384 args.register_count());
3385
3386 VisitForAccumulatorValueOrTheHole(expr->extends());
3387 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_class);
3388
3389 VisitFunctionLiteral(expr->constructor());
3390 builder()
3391 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(class_constructor)
3392 .MoveRegister(class_constructor, class_constructor_in_args)
3393 .LoadConstantPoolEntry(class_boilerplate_entry)
3394 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(class_boilerplate);
3395
3396 // Create computed names and method values nodes to store into the literal.
3397 for (int i = 0; i < expr->public_members()->length(); i++) {
3398 ClassLiteral::Property* property = expr->public_members()->at(i);
3399 if (property->is_computed_name()) {
3400 Register key = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3401
3402 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(property->key());
3403 BuildLoadPropertyKey(property, key);
3404 if (property->is_static()) {
3405 // The static prototype property is read only. We handle the non
3406 // computed property name case in the parser. Since this is the only
3407 // case where we need to check for an own read only property we
3408 // special case this so we do not need to do this for every property.
3409
3410 FeedbackSlot slot = GetDummyCompareICSlot();
3411 BytecodeLabel done;
3412 builder()
3413 ->LoadLiteral(ast_string_constants()->prototype_string())
3414 .CompareOperation(Token::kEqStrict, key, feedback_index(slot))
3415 .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &done)
3416 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStaticPrototypeError)
3417 .Bind(&done);
3418 }
3419
3420 if (property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD) {
3421 DCHECK(!property->is_private());
3422 // Initialize field's name variable with the computed name.
3423 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(property->computed_name_var());
3424 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(key);
3425 BuildVariableAssignment(property->computed_name_var(), Token::kInit,
3426 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3427 }
3428 }
3429
3430 DCHECK(!property->is_private());
3431
3432 if (property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD) {
3433 // We don't compute field's value here, but instead do it in the
3434 // initializer function.
3435 continue;
3436 }
3437
3438 if (property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::AUTO_ACCESSOR) {
3439 {
3440 RegisterAllocationScope private_name_register_scope(this);
3441 Register name_register = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3442 Variable* accessor_storage_private_name_var =
3443 property->auto_accessor_info()
3444 ->accessor_storage_name_proxy()
3445 ->var();
3446 builder()
3447 ->LoadLiteral(accessor_storage_private_name_var->raw_name())
3448 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name_register)
3449 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateNameSymbol, name_register);
3450 BuildVariableAssignment(accessor_storage_private_name_var,
3451 Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3452 }
3453
3454 Register getter = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3455 Register setter = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3456 AutoAccessorInfo* auto_accessor_info = property->auto_accessor_info();
3457 VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_getter(), getter);
3458 VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_setter(), setter);
3459 continue;
3460 }
3461
3462 Register value = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3463 VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), value);
3464 }
3465
3466 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDefineClass, args);
3467 }
3468
3469 // Assign to the home object variable. Accumulator already contains the
3470 // prototype.
3471 Variable* home_object_variable = expr->home_object();
3472 if (home_object_variable != nullptr) {
3473 DCHECK(home_object_variable->is_used());
3474 DCHECK(home_object_variable->IsContextSlot());
3475 BuildVariableAssignment(home_object_variable, Token::kInit,
3476 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3477 }
3478 Variable* static_home_object_variable = expr->static_home_object();
3479 if (static_home_object_variable != nullptr) {
3480 DCHECK(static_home_object_variable->is_used());
3481 DCHECK(static_home_object_variable->IsContextSlot());
3482 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3483 BuildVariableAssignment(static_home_object_variable, Token::kInit,
3484 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3485 }
3486
3487 // Assign to class variable.
3488 Variable* class_variable = expr->scope()->class_variable();
3489 if (class_variable != nullptr && class_variable->is_used()) {
3490 DCHECK(class_variable->IsStackLocal() || class_variable->IsContextSlot());
3491 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3492 BuildVariableAssignment(class_variable, Token::kInit,
3493 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3494 }
3495
3496 // Define private accessors, using only a single call to the runtime for
3497 // each pair of corresponding getters and setters, in the order the first
3498 // component is declared.
3499 for (auto accessors : private_accessors.ordered_accessors()) {
3500 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
3501 RegisterList accessors_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
3502 ClassLiteral::Property* getter = accessors.second->getter;
3503 ClassLiteral::Property* setter = accessors.second->setter;
3504 Variable* accessor_pair_var;
3505 if (getter && getter->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::AUTO_ACCESSOR) {
3506 DCHECK_EQ(setter, getter);
3507 AutoAccessorInfo* auto_accessor_info = getter->auto_accessor_info();
3508 VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_getter(),
3509 accessors_reg[0]);
3510 VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_setter(),
3511 accessors_reg[1]);
3512 accessor_pair_var =
3513 auto_accessor_info->property_private_name_proxy()->var();
3514 } else {
3515 VisitLiteralAccessor(getter, accessors_reg[0]);
3516 VisitLiteralAccessor(setter, accessors_reg[1]);
3517 accessor_pair_var = getter != nullptr ? getter->private_name_var()
3518 : setter->private_name_var();
3519 }
3520 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateAccessors, accessors_reg);
3521 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(accessor_pair_var);
3522 BuildVariableAssignment(accessor_pair_var, Token::kInit,
3523 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3524 }
3525
3526 if (expr->instance_members_initializer_function() != nullptr) {
3527 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->instance_members_initializer_function());
3528
3529 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddStoreICSlot(language_mode());
3530 builder()
3531 ->StoreClassFieldsInitializer(class_constructor, feedback_index(slot))
3532 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3533 }
3534
3535 if (expr->static_initializer() != nullptr) {
3536 // TODO(gsathya): This can be optimized away to be a part of the
3537 // class boilerplate in the future. The name argument can be
3538 // passed to the DefineClass runtime function and have it set
3539 // there.
3540 // TODO(v8:13451): Alternatively, port SetFunctionName to an ic so that we
3541 // can replace the runtime call to a dedicate bytecode here.
3542 if (name.is_valid()) {
3543 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
3544 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
3545 builder()
3546 ->MoveRegister(class_constructor, args[0])
3547 .MoveRegister(name, args[1])
3548 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kSetFunctionName, args);
3549 }
3550
3551 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
3552 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(1);
3553 Register initializer = VisitForRegisterValue(expr->static_initializer());
3554
3555 builder()
3556 ->MoveRegister(class_constructor, args[0])
3557 .CallProperty(initializer, args,
3558 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
3559 }
3560 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3561}
3562
3563void BytecodeGenerator::VisitClassLiteral(ClassLiteral* expr) {
3564 VisitClassLiteral(expr, Register::invalid_value());
3565}
3566
3567void BytecodeGenerator::VisitClassLiteral(ClassLiteral* expr, Register name) {
3568 CurrentScope current_scope(this, expr->scope());
3569 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(expr->scope());
3570 if (expr->scope()->NeedsContext()) {
3571 // Make sure to associate the source position for the class
3572 // after the block context is created. Otherwise we have a mismatch
3573 // between the scope and the context, where we already are in a
3574 // block context for the class, but not yet in the class scope. Only do
3575 // this if the current source position is inside the class scope though.
3576 // For example:
3577 // * `var x = class {};` will break on `class` which is inside
3578 // the class scope, so we expect the BlockContext to be pushed.
3579 //
3580 // * `new class x {};` will break on `new` which is outside the
3581 // class scope, so we expect the BlockContext to not be pushed yet.
3582 std::optional<BytecodeSourceInfo> source_info =
3583 builder()->MaybePopSourcePosition(expr->scope()->start_position());
3584 BuildNewLocalBlockContext(expr->scope());
3585 ContextScope scope(this, expr->scope());
3586 if (source_info) builder()->PushSourcePosition(*source_info);
3587 BuildClassLiteral(expr, name);
3588 } else {
3589 BuildClassLiteral(expr, name);
3590 }
3591}
3592
3593void BytecodeGenerator::BuildClassProperty(ClassLiteral::Property* property) {
3594 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3595 Register key;
3596
3597 // Private methods are not initialized in BuildClassProperty.
3598 DCHECK_IMPLIES(property->is_private(),
3599 property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD ||
3600 property->is_auto_accessor());
3601 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->key());
3602
3603 bool is_literal_store =
3604 property->key()->IsPropertyName() && !property->is_computed_name() &&
3605 !property->is_private() && !property->is_auto_accessor();
3606
3607 if (!is_literal_store) {
3608 key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3609 if (property->is_auto_accessor()) {
3610 Variable* var =
3611 property->auto_accessor_info()->accessor_storage_name_proxy()->var();
3612 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(var);
3613 BuildVariableLoad(var, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3614 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key);
3615 } else if (property->is_computed_name()) {
3616 DCHECK_EQ(property->kind(), ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD);
3617 DCHECK(!property->is_private());
3618 Variable* var = property->computed_name_var();
3619 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(var);
3620 // The computed name is already evaluated and stored in a variable at
3621 // class definition time.
3622 BuildVariableLoad(var, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3623 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key);
3624 } else if (property->is_private()) {
3625 Variable* private_name_var = property->private_name_var();
3626 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(private_name_var);
3627 BuildVariableLoad(private_name_var, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3628 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key);
3629 } else {
3630 VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), key);
3631 }
3632 }
3633
3634 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(property->value());
3635
3636 if (is_literal_store) {
3637 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3638 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineNamedOwnICSlot();
3639 builder()->DefineNamedOwnProperty(
3640 builder()->Receiver(),
3641 property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName(),
3642 feedback_index(slot));
3643 } else {
3644 DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlags flags = DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kNoFlags;
3645 if (property->NeedsSetFunctionName()) {
3646 // Static class fields require the name property to be set on
3647 // the class, meaning we can't wait until the
3648 // DefineKeyedOwnProperty call later to set the name.
3649 if (property->value()->IsClassLiteral() &&
3650 property->value()->AsClassLiteral()->static_initializer() !=
3651 nullptr) {
3652 VisitClassLiteral(property->value()->AsClassLiteral(), key);
3653 } else {
3654 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3655 flags |= DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kSetFunctionName;
3656 }
3657 } else {
3658 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3659 }
3660 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnICSlot();
3661 builder()->DefineKeyedOwnProperty(builder()->Receiver(), key, flags,
3662 feedback_index(slot));
3663 }
3664}

3668 for (int i = 0; i < stmt->fields()->length(); i++) {
3669 BuildClassProperty(stmt->fields()->at(i));

3677 switch (element->kind()) {

3683 break;

3685 }

3700 Register value = builder()->Parameter(0);

3702 BuildVariableLoad(stmt->name_proxy()->var(), HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3703
3704 builder()
3705 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key)
3706 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value)

3711void BytecodeGenerator::BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate tmpl,
3712 Property* property) {
3713 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3714 const AstRawString* name = property->key()->AsVariableProxy()->raw_name();
3715 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
3716 builder()
3717 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(tmpl))
3718 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])

3724
3725void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateBrandInitialization(Register receiver,
3726 Variable* brand) {
3727 BuildVariableLoad(brand, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3728 int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(brand->scope());
3729 ContextScope* class_context = execution_context()->Previous(depth);
3730 if (class_context) {
3731 Register brand_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3732 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnICSlot();
3733 builder()
3734 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand_reg)
3735 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_context->reg())
3736 .DefineKeyedOwnProperty(receiver, brand_reg,
3737 DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kNoFlags,
3738 feedback_index(slot));
3739 } else {
3740 // We are in the slow case where super() is called from a nested
3741 // arrow function or an eval(), so the class scope context isn't
3742 // tracked in a context register in the stack, and we have to
3743 // walk the context chain from the runtime to find it.
3744 DCHECK_NE(info()->literal()->scope()->outer_scope(), brand->scope());
3745 RegisterList brand_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
3746 builder()
3747 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand_args[1])
3748 .MoveRegister(receiver, brand_args[0])
3749 .MoveRegister(execution_context()->reg(), brand_args[2])
3750 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(depth))
3751 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand_args[3])
3752 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kAddPrivateBrand, brand_args);
3753 }
3754}
3755
3756void BytecodeGenerator::BuildInstanceMemberInitialization(Register constructor,
3757 Register instance) {
3758 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(1);
3759 Register initializer = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3760
3761 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
3762 BytecodeLabel done;
3763
3764 builder()
3765 ->LoadClassFieldsInitializer(constructor, feedback_index(slot))
3766 // TODO(gsathya): This jump can be elided for the base
3767 // constructor and derived constructor. This is only required
3768 // when called from an arrow function.
3769 .JumpIfUndefined(&done)
3770 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(initializer)
3771 .MoveRegister(instance, args[0])
3772 .CallProperty(initializer, args,
3773 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()))
3774 .Bind(&done);
3775}

3777void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNativeFunctionLiteral(
3778 NativeFunctionLiteral* expr) {
3779 size_t entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
3780 // Native functions don't use argument adaption and so have the special
3781 // kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel as their parameter count.
3782 int index = feedback_spec()->AddCreateClosureParameterCount(
3783 kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel);
3784 uint8_t flags = CreateClosureFlags::Encode(false, false, false);
3785 builder()->CreateClosure(entry, index, flags);
3786 native_function_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr, entry));
3787}
3788
3789void BytecodeGenerator::VisitConditionalChain(ConditionalChain* expr) {
3790 ConditionalChainControlFlowBuilder conditional_builder(
3791 builder(), block_coverage_builder_, expr,
3792 expr->conditional_chain_length());
3793
3794 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
3795 {
3796 bool should_visit_else_expression = true;
3797 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
3798 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->conditional_chain_length(); ++i) {
3799 if (expr->condition_at(i)->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
3800 // Generate then block unconditionally as always true.
3801 should_visit_else_expression = false;
3802 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3803 conditional_builder.ThenAt(i);
3804 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression_at(i));
3805 break;
3806 } else if (expr->condition_at(i)->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
3807 // Generate else block unconditionally by skipping the then block.
3808 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3809 conditional_builder.ElseAt(i);
3810 } else {
3811 VisitForTest(
3812 expr->condition_at(i), conditional_builder.then_labels_at(i),
3813 conditional_builder.else_labels_at(i), TestFallthrough::kThen);
3814 {
3815 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3816 conditional_builder.ThenAt(i);
3817 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression_at(i));
3818 }
3819 conditional_builder.JumpToEnd();
3820 {
3821 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3822 conditional_builder.ElseAt(i);
3823 }
3824 }
3825 }
3826
3827 if (should_visit_else_expression) {
3828 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->else_expression());
3829 }
3830 }
3831 merge_elider.Merge();
3832}
3833
3834void BytecodeGenerator::VisitConditional(Conditional* expr) {
3835 ConditionalControlFlowBuilder conditional_builder(
3836 builder(), block_coverage_builder_, expr);
3837
3838 if (expr->condition()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
3839 // Generate then block unconditionally as always true.
3840 conditional_builder.Then();
3841 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression());
3842 } else if (expr->condition()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
3843 // Generate else block unconditionally if it exists.
3844 conditional_builder.Else();
3845 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->else_expression());
3846 } else {
3847 VisitForTest(expr->condition(), conditional_builder.then_labels(),
3848 conditional_builder.else_labels(), TestFallthrough::kThen);
3849
3850 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
3851 conditional_builder.Then();
3852 {
3853 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
3854 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression());
3855 }
3856 conditional_builder.JumpToEnd();
3857
3858 conditional_builder.Else();
3859 {
3860 HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
3861 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->else_expression());
3862 }
3863
3864 merge_elider.Merge();
3865 }
3866}
3867
3868void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLiteral(Literal* expr) {
3869 if (execution_result()->IsEffect()) return;
3870 switch (expr->type()) {
3871 case Literal::kSmi:
3872 builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsSmiLiteral());
3873 break;
3874 case Literal::kHeapNumber:
3875 builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsNumber());
3876 break;
3877 case Literal::kUndefined:
3878 builder()->LoadUndefined();
3879 break;
3880 case Literal::kBoolean:
3881 builder()->LoadBoolean(expr->ToBooleanIsTrue());
3882 execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
3883 break;
3884 case Literal::kNull:
3885 builder()->LoadNull();
3886 break;
3887 case Literal::kTheHole:
3888 builder()->LoadTheHole();
3889 break;
3890 case Literal::kString:
3891 builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsRawString());
3892 execution_result()->SetResultIsInternalizedString();
3893 break;
3894 case Literal::kConsString:
3895 builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsConsString());
3896 break;
3897 case Literal::kBigInt:
3898 builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsBigInt());
3899 break;
3900 }
3901}

3903void BytecodeGenerator::VisitRegExpLiteral(RegExpLiteral* expr) {
3904 // Materialize a regular expression literal.
3905 builder()->CreateRegExpLiteral(
3906 expr->raw_pattern(), feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot()),
3907 expr->flags());
3908}
