3910void BytecodeGenerator::BuildCreateObjectLiteral(Register literal,
3911 uint8_t flags, size_t entry) {
3912 // TODO(cbruni): Directly generate runtime call for literals we cannot
3913 // optimize once the CreateShallowObjectLiteral stub is in sync with the TF
3914 // optimizations.
3915 int literal_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot());
3916 builder()
3917 ->CreateObjectLiteral(entry, literal_index, flags)
3918 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(literal);
3919}
3920
3921void BytecodeGenerator::VisitObjectLiteral(ObjectLiteral* expr) {
3922 expr->builder()->InitDepthAndFlags();
3923
3924 // Fast path for the empty object literal which doesn't need an
3925 // AllocationSite.
3926 if (expr->builder()->IsEmptyObjectLiteral()) {
3927 DCHECK(expr->builder()->IsFastCloningSupported());
3928 builder()->CreateEmptyObjectLiteral();
3929 return;
3930 }
3931
3932 Variable* home_object = expr->home_object();
3933 if (home_object != nullptr) {
3934 DCHECK(home_object->is_used());
3935 DCHECK(home_object->IsContextSlot());
3936 }
3937 MultipleEntryBlockContextScope object_literal_context_scope(
3938 this, home_object ? home_object->scope() : nullptr);
3939
3940 // Deep-copy the literal boilerplate.
3941 uint8_t flags = CreateObjectLiteralFlags::Encode(
3942 expr->builder()->ComputeFlags(),
3943 expr->builder()->IsFastCloningSupported());
3944
3945 Register literal = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3946
3947 // Create literal object.
3948 int property_index = 0;
3949 bool clone_object_spread =
3950 expr->properties()->first()->kind() == ObjectLiteral::Property::SPREAD;
3951 if (clone_object_spread) {
3952 // Avoid the slow path for spreads in the following common cases:
3953 // 1) `let obj = { ...source }`
3954 // 2) `let obj = { ...source, override: 1 }`
3955 // 3) `let obj = { ...source, ...overrides }`
3956 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3957 Expression* property = expr->properties()->first()->value();
3958 Register from_value = VisitForRegisterValue(property);
3959 int clone_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCloneObjectSlot());
3960 builder()->CloneObject(from_value, flags, clone_index);
3961 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(literal);
3962 property_index++;
3963 } else {
3964 size_t entry;
3965 // If constant properties is an empty fixed array, use a cached empty fixed
3966 // array to ensure it's only added to the constant pool once.
3967 if (expr->builder()->properties_count() == 0) {
3968 entry = builder()->EmptyObjectBoilerplateDescriptionConstantPoolEntry();
3969 } else {
3970 entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
3971 object_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr->builder(), entry));
3972 }
3973 BuildCreateObjectLiteral(literal, flags, entry);
3974 }
3975
3976 // Store computed values into the literal.
3977 AccessorTable<ObjectLiteral::Property> accessor_table(zone());
3978 for (; property_index < expr->properties()->length(); property_index++) {
3979 ObjectLiteral::Property* property = expr->properties()->at(property_index);
3980 if (property->is_computed_name()) break;
3981 if (!clone_object_spread && property->IsCompileTimeValue()) continue;
3982
3983 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
3984 Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
3985 switch (property->kind()) {
3986 case ObjectLiteral::Property::SPREAD:
3987 UNREACHABLE();
3988 case ObjectLiteral::Property::CONSTANT:
3989 case ObjectLiteral::Property::MATERIALIZED_LITERAL:
3990 DCHECK(clone_object_spread || !property->value()->IsCompileTimeValue());
3991 [[fallthrough]];
3992 case ObjectLiteral::Property::COMPUTED: {
3993 // It is safe to use [[Put]] here because the boilerplate already
3994 // contains computed properties with an uninitialized value.
3995 Register key_reg;
3996 if (key->IsStringLiteral()) {
3997 DCHECK(key->IsPropertyName());
3998 } else {
3999 key_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4000 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->key());
4001 VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), key_reg);
4002 }
4003
4004 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(
4005 property->value()->IsConciseMethodDefinition());
4006 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4007
4008 if (property->emit_store()) {
4009 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
4010 if (key->IsStringLiteral()) {
4011 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineNamedOwnICSlot();
4012 builder()->DefineNamedOwnProperty(literal, key->AsRawPropertyName(),
4013 feedback_index(slot));
4014 } else {
4015 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnICSlot();
4016 builder()->DefineKeyedOwnProperty(
4017 literal, key_reg, DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kNoFlags,
4018 feedback_index(slot));
4019 }
4020 } else {
4021 VisitForEffect(property->value());
4022 }
4023 break;
4024 }
4025 case ObjectLiteral::Property::PROTOTYPE: {
4026 // __proto__:null is handled by CreateObjectLiteral.
4027 if (property->IsNullPrototype()) break;
4028 DCHECK(property->emit_store());
4029 DCHECK(!property->NeedsSetFunctionName());
4030 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4031 builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4032 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4033 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4034 VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[1]);
4035 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInternalSetPrototype, args);
4036 break;
4037 }
4038 case ObjectLiteral::Property::GETTER:
4039 if (property->emit_store()) {
4040 accessor_table.LookupOrInsert(key)->getter = property;
4041 }
4042 break;
4043 case ObjectLiteral::Property::SETTER:
4044 if (property->emit_store()) {
4045 accessor_table.LookupOrInsert(key)->setter = property;
4046 }
4047 break;
4048 }
4049 }
4050
4051 // Define accessors, using only a single call to the runtime for each pair
4052 // of corresponding getters and setters.
4053 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(true);
4054 for (auto accessors : accessor_table.ordered_accessors()) {
4055 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
4056 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(5);
4057 builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4058 VisitForRegisterValue(accessors.first, args[1]);
4059 VisitLiteralAccessor(accessors.second->getter, args[2]);
4060 VisitLiteralAccessor(accessors.second->setter, args[3]);
4061 builder()
4062 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(NONE))
4063 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[4])
4064 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kDefineAccessorPropertyUnchecked, args);
4065 }
4066
4067 // Object literals have two parts. The "static" part on the left contains no
4068 // computed property names, and so we can compute its map ahead of time; see
4069 // Runtime_CreateObjectLiteralBoilerplate. The second "dynamic" part starts
4070 // with the first computed property name and continues with all properties to
4071 // its right. All the code from above initializes the static component of the
4072 // object literal, and arranges for the map of the result to reflect the
4073 // static order in which the keys appear. For the dynamic properties, we
4074 // compile them into a series of "SetOwnProperty" runtime calls. This will
4075 // preserve insertion order.
4076 for (; property_index < expr->properties()->length(); property_index++) {
4077 ObjectLiteral::Property* property = expr->properties()->at(property_index);
4078 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
4079
4080 bool should_be_in_object_literal_scope =
4081 (property->value()->IsConciseMethodDefinition() ||
4082 property->value()->IsAccessorFunctionDefinition());
4083
4084 if (property->IsPrototype()) {
4085 // __proto__:null is handled by CreateObjectLiteral.
4086 if (property->IsNullPrototype()) continue;
4087 DCHECK(property->emit_store());
4088 DCHECK(!property->NeedsSetFunctionName());
4089 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4090 builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4091
4092 DCHECK(!should_be_in_object_literal_scope);
4093 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4094 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4095 VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[1]);
4096 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInternalSetPrototype, args);
4097 continue;
4098 }
4099
4100 switch (property->kind()) {
4101 case ObjectLiteral::Property::CONSTANT:
4102 case ObjectLiteral::Property::COMPUTED:
4103 case ObjectLiteral::Property::MATERIALIZED_LITERAL: {
4104 // Computed property keys don't belong to the object literal scope (even
4105 // if they're syntactically inside it).
4106 if (property->is_computed_name()) {
4107 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4108 }
4109 Register key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4110 BuildLoadPropertyKey(property, key);
4111
4112 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(
4113 should_be_in_object_literal_scope);
4114 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4115
4116 DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralFlags data_property_flags =
4117 DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralFlag::kNoFlags;
4118 if (property->NeedsSetFunctionName()) {
4119 // Static class fields require the name property to be set on
4120 // the class, meaning we can't wait until the
4121 // DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral call later to set the name.
4122 if (property->value()->IsClassLiteral() &&
4123 property->value()->AsClassLiteral()->static_initializer() !=
4124 nullptr) {
4125 VisitClassLiteral(property->value()->AsClassLiteral(), key);
4126 } else {
4127 data_property_flags |=
4128 DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralFlag::kSetFunctionName;
4129 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
4130 }
4131 } else {
4132 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
4133 }
4134
4135 FeedbackSlot slot =
4136 feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralICSlot();
4137 builder()->DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral(
4138 literal, key, data_property_flags, feedback_index(slot));
4139 break;
4140 }
4141 case ObjectLiteral::Property::GETTER:
4142 case ObjectLiteral::Property::SETTER: {
4143 // Computed property keys don't belong to the object literal scope (even
4144 // if they're syntactically inside it).
4145 if (property->is_computed_name()) {
4146 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4147 }
4148 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
4149 builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4150 BuildLoadPropertyKey(property, args[1]);
4151
4152 DCHECK(should_be_in_object_literal_scope);
4153 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(true);
4154 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4155 VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[2]);
4156 builder()
4157 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(NONE))
4158 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[3]);
4159 Runtime::FunctionId function_id =
4160 property->kind() == ObjectLiteral::Property::GETTER
4161 ? Runtime::kDefineGetterPropertyUnchecked
4162 : Runtime::kDefineSetterPropertyUnchecked;
4163 builder()->CallRuntime(function_id, args);
4164 break;
4165 }
4166 case ObjectLiteral::Property::SPREAD: {
4167 // TODO(olivf, chrome:1204540) This can be slower than the Babel
4168 // translation. Should we compile this to a copying loop in bytecode?
4169 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4170 builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4171 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4172 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4173 VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[1]);
4174 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineCopyDataProperties, args);
4175 break;
4176 }
4177 case ObjectLiteral::Property::PROTOTYPE:
4178 UNREACHABLE(); // Handled specially above.
4179 }
4180 }
4181
4182 if (home_object != nullptr) {
4183 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(true);
4184 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(literal);
4185 BuildVariableAssignment(home_object, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
4186 }
4187 // Make sure to exit the scope before materialising the value into the
4188 // accumulator, to prevent the context scope from clobbering it.
4189 object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4190 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(literal);
4191}
4192
4193// Fill an array with values from an iterator, starting at a given index. It is
4194// guaranteed that the loop will only terminate if the iterator is exhausted, or
4195// if one of iterator.next(), value.done, or value.value fail.
4196//
4197// In pseudocode:
4198//
4199// loop {
4200// value = iterator.next()
4201// if (value.done) break;
4202// value = value.value
4203// array[index++] = value
4204// }
4205void BytecodeGenerator::BuildFillArrayWithIterator(
4206 IteratorRecord iterator, Register array, Register index, Register value,
4207 FeedbackSlot next_value_slot, FeedbackSlot next_done_slot,
4208 FeedbackSlot index_slot, FeedbackSlot element_slot) {
4209 DCHECK(array.is_valid());
4210 DCHECK(index.is_valid());
4211 DCHECK(value.is_valid());
4212
4213 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), nullptr, nullptr, feedback_spec());
4214 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
4215
4216 // Call the iterator's .next() method. Break from the loop if the `done`
4217 // property is truthy, otherwise load the value from the iterator result and
4218 // append the argument.
4219 BuildIteratorNext(iterator, value);
4220 builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
4221 value, ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
4222 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
4223 loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
4224
4225 loop_builder.LoopBody();
4226 builder()
4227 // value = value.value
4228 ->LoadNamedProperty(value, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
4229 feedback_index(next_value_slot))
4230 // array[index] = value
4231 .StoreInArrayLiteral(array, index, feedback_index(element_slot))
4232 // index++
4233 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(index)
4234 .UnaryOperation(Token::kInc, feedback_index(index_slot))
4235 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4236 loop_builder.BindContinueTarget();
4237}
4238
4239void BytecodeGenerator::BuildCreateArrayLiteral(
4240 const ZonePtrList<Expression>* elements, ArrayLiteral* expr) {
4241 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
4242 // Make this the first register allocated so that it has a chance of aliasing
4243 // the next register allocated after returning from this function.
4244 Register array = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4245 Register index = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4246 SharedFeedbackSlot element_slot(feedback_spec(),
4247 FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreInArrayLiteral);
4248 ZonePtrList<Expression>::const_iterator current = elements->begin();
4249 ZonePtrList<Expression>::const_iterator end = elements->end();
4250 bool is_empty = elements->is_empty();
4251
4252 if (!is_empty && (*current)->IsSpread()) {
4253 // If we have a leading spread, use CreateArrayFromIterable to create
4254 // an array from it and then add the remaining components to that array.
4255 VisitForAccumulatorValue(*current);
4256 builder()->SetExpressionPosition((*current)->AsSpread()->expression());
4257 builder()->CreateArrayFromIterable().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(array);
4258
4259 if (++current != end) {
4260 // If there are remaning elements, prepare the index register that is
4261 // used for adding those elements. The next index is the length of the
4262 // newly created array.
4263 auto length = ast_string_constants()->length_string();
4264 int length_load_slot = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot());
4265 builder()
4266 ->LoadNamedProperty(array, length, length_load_slot)
4267 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4268 }
4269 } else {
4270 // There are some elements before the first (if any) spread, and we can
4271 // use a boilerplate when creating the initial array from those elements.
4272
4273 // First, allocate a constant pool entry for the boilerplate that will
4274 // be created during finalization, and will contain all the constant
4275 // elements before the first spread. This also handle the empty array case
4276 // and one-shot optimization.
4277
4278 ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder* array_literal_builder = nullptr;
4279 if (expr != nullptr) {
4280 array_literal_builder = expr->builder();
4281 } else {
4282 DCHECK(!elements->is_empty());
4283
4284 // get first_spread_index
4285 int first_spread_index = -1;
4286 for (auto iter = elements->begin(); iter != elements->end(); iter++) {
4287 if ((*iter)->IsSpread()) {
4288 first_spread_index = static_cast<int>(iter - elements->begin());
4289 break;
4290 }
4291 }
4292
4293 array_literal_builder = zone()->New<ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder>(
4294 elements, first_spread_index);
4295 array_literal_builder->InitDepthAndFlags();
4296 }
4297
4298 DCHECK(array_literal_builder != nullptr);
4299 uint8_t flags = CreateArrayLiteralFlags::Encode(
4300 array_literal_builder->IsFastCloningSupported(),
4301 array_literal_builder->ComputeFlags());
4302 if (is_empty) {
4303 // Empty array literal fast-path.
4304 int literal_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot());
4305 DCHECK(array_literal_builder->IsFastCloningSupported());
4306 builder()->CreateEmptyArrayLiteral(literal_index);
4307 } else {
4308 // Create array literal from boilerplate.
4309 size_t entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
4310 array_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(array_literal_builder, entry));
4311 int literal_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot());
4312 builder()->CreateArrayLiteral(entry, literal_index, flags);
4313 }
4314 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(array);
4315
4316 ZonePtrList<Expression>::const_iterator first_spread_or_end =
4317 array_literal_builder->first_spread_index() >= 0
4318 ? current + array_literal_builder->first_spread_index()
4319 : end;
4320
4321 // Insert the missing non-constant elements, up until the first spread
4322 // index, into the initial array (the remaining elements will be inserted
4323 // below).
4324 DCHECK_EQ(current, elements->begin());
4325 int array_index = 0;
4326 for (; current != first_spread_or_end; ++current, array_index++) {
4327 Expression* subexpr = *current;
4328 DCHECK(!subexpr->IsSpread());
4329 // Skip the constants.
4330 if (subexpr->IsCompileTimeValue()) continue;
4331
4332 builder()
4333 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(array_index))
4334 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4335 VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr);
4336 builder()->StoreInArrayLiteral(array, index,
4337 feedback_index(element_slot.Get()));
4338 }
4339
4340 if (current != end) {
4341 // If there are remaining elements, prepare the index register
4342 // to store the next element, which comes from the first spread.
4343 builder()
4344 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(array_index))
4345 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4346 }
4347 }
4348
4349 // Now build insertions for the remaining elements from current to end.
4350 SharedFeedbackSlot index_slot(feedback_spec(), FeedbackSlotKind::kBinaryOp);
4351 SharedFeedbackSlot length_slot(
4352 feedback_spec(), feedback_spec()->GetStoreICSlot(LanguageMode::kStrict));
4353 for (; current != end; ++current) {
4354 Expression* subexpr = *current;
4355 if (subexpr->IsSpread()) {
4356 RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
4357 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(subexpr->AsSpread()->expression());
4358 VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr->AsSpread()->expression());
4359 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(subexpr->AsSpread()->expression());
4360 IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(IteratorType::kNormal);
4361
4362 Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4363 FeedbackSlot next_value_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
4364 FeedbackSlot next_done_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
4365 FeedbackSlot real_index_slot = index_slot.Get();
4366 FeedbackSlot real_element_slot = element_slot.Get();
4367 BuildFillArrayWithIterator(iterator, array, index, value,
4368 next_value_load_slot, next_done_load_slot,
4369 real_index_slot, real_element_slot);
4370 } else if (!subexpr->IsTheHoleLiteral()) {
4371 // literal[index++] = subexpr
4372 VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr);
4373 builder()
4374 ->StoreInArrayLiteral(array, index,
4375 feedback_index(element_slot.Get()))
4376 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(index);
4377 // Only increase the index if we are not the last element.
4378 if (current + 1 != end) {
4379 builder()
4380 ->UnaryOperation(Token::kInc, feedback_index(index_slot.Get()))
4381 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4382 }
4383 } else {
4384 // literal.length = ++index
4385 // length_slot is only used when there are holes.
4386 auto length = ast_string_constants()->length_string();
4387 builder()
4388 ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(index)
4389 .UnaryOperation(Token::kInc, feedback_index(index_slot.Get()))
4390 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index)
4391 .SetNamedProperty(array, length, feedback_index(length_slot.Get()),
4392 LanguageMode::kStrict);
4393 }
4394 }
4395
4396 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(array);
4397}

4401 BuildCreateArrayLiteral(expr->values(), expr);

4431
4432void BytecodeGenerator::BuildVariableLoad(Variable* variable,
4433 HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode,
4434 TypeofMode typeof_mode) {
4435 switch (variable->location()) {
4436 case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
4437 Register source(builder()->Local(variable->index()));
4438 // We need to load the variable into the accumulator, even when in a
4439 // VisitForRegisterScope, in order to avoid register aliasing if
4440 // subsequent expressions assign to the same variable.
4441 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(source);
4442 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4443 BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4444 }
4445 break;
4446 }
4447 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER: {
4448 Register source;
4449 if (variable->IsReceiver()) {
4450 source = builder()->Receiver();
4451 } else {
4452 source = builder()->Parameter(variable->index());
4453 }
4454 // We need to load the variable into the accumulator, even when in a
4455 // VisitForRegisterScope, in order to avoid register aliasing if
4456 // subsequent expressions assign to the same variable.
4457 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(source);
4458 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4459 BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4460 }
4461 break;
4462 }
4463 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED: {
4464 // The global identifier "undefined" is immutable. Everything
4465 // else could be reassigned. For performance, we do a pointer comparison
4466 // rather than checking if the raw_name is really "undefined".
4467 if (variable->raw_name() == ast_string_constants()->undefined_string()) {
4468 builder()->LoadUndefined();
4469 } else {
4470 FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadGlobalICSlot(typeof_mode, variable);
4471 builder()->LoadGlobal(variable->raw_name(), feedback_index(slot),
4472 typeof_mode);
4473 }
4474 break;
4475 }
4476 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
4477 int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4478 ContextScope* context = execution_context()->Previous(depth);
4479 Register context_reg;
4480 if (context) {
4481 context_reg = context->reg();
4482 depth = 0;
4483 } else {
4484 context_reg = execution_context()->reg();
4485 }
4486
4487 BytecodeArrayBuilder::ContextSlotMutability immutable =
4488 (variable->maybe_assigned() == kNotAssigned)
4489 ? BytecodeArrayBuilder::kImmutableSlot
4490 : BytecodeArrayBuilder::kMutableSlot;
4491 Register acc = Register::virtual_accumulator();
4492 if (immutable == BytecodeArrayBuilder::kImmutableSlot &&
4493 IsVariableInRegister(variable, acc)) {
4494 return;
4495 }
4496
4497 builder()->LoadContextSlot(context_reg, variable, depth, immutable);
4498 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4499 BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4500 }
4501 if (immutable == BytecodeArrayBuilder::kImmutableSlot) {
4502 SetVariableInRegister(variable, acc);
4503 }
4504 break;
4505 }
4506 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
4507 switch (variable->mode()) {
4508 case VariableMode::kDynamicLocal: {
4509 Variable* local_variable = variable->local_if_not_shadowed();
4510 int depth =
4511 execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(local_variable->scope());
4512 ContextKind context_kind = (local_variable->scope()->is_script_scope()
4513 ? ContextKind::kScriptContext
4514 : ContextKind::kDefault);
4515 builder()->LoadLookupContextSlot(variable->raw_name(), typeof_mode,
4516 context_kind,
4517 local_variable->index(), depth);
4518 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(local_variable,
4519 hole_check_mode)) {
4520 BuildThrowIfHole(local_variable);
4521 }
4522 break;
4523 }
4524 case VariableMode::kDynamicGlobal: {
4525 int depth =
4526 current_scope()->ContextChainLengthUntilOutermostSloppyEval();
4527 // TODO(1008414): Add back caching here when bug is fixed properly.
4528 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadGlobalICSlot(typeof_mode);
4529
4530 builder()->LoadLookupGlobalSlot(variable->raw_name(), typeof_mode,
4531 feedback_index(slot), depth);
4532 break;
4533 }
4534 default: {
4535 // Normally, private names should not be looked up dynamically,
4536 // but we make an exception in debug-evaluate, in that case the
4537 // lookup will be done in %SetPrivateMember() and %GetPrivateMember()
4538 // calls, not here.
4539 DCHECK(!variable->raw_name()->IsPrivateName());
4540 builder()->LoadLookupSlot(variable->raw_name(), typeof_mode);
4541 break;
4542 }
4543 }
4544 break;
4545 }
4546 case VariableLocation::MODULE: {
4547 int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4548 builder()->LoadModuleVariable(variable->index(), depth);
4549 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4550 BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4551 }
4552 break;
4553 }
4554 case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL: {
4555 DCHECK(variable->IsReplGlobal());
4556 FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadGlobalICSlot(typeof_mode, variable);
4557 builder()->LoadGlobal(variable->raw_name(), feedback_index(slot),
4558 typeof_mode);
4559 break;
4560 }
4561 }
4562}

4566 ValueResultScope accumulator_result(this);

4574 // Runtime returns {result} value, preserving accumulator.

4580}
4581
4582void BytecodeGenerator::BuildAsyncReturn(int source_position) {
4583 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
4584
4585 if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) {
4586 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
4587 builder()
4588 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
4589 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
4590 .LoadTrue()
4591 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2]) // done
4592 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorResolve, args);
4593 } else {
4594 DCHECK(IsAsyncFunction(info()->literal()->kind()) ||
4595 IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(info()->literal()->kind()));
4596 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4597 builder()
4598 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
4599 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
4600 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionResolve, args);
4601 }
4602
4603 BuildReturn(source_position);
4604}
4605
4606void BytecodeGenerator::BuildReThrow() { builder()->ReThrow(); }
4607
4608void BytecodeGenerator::RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(Variable* variable) {
4609 if (!v8_flags.ignition_elide_redundant_tdz_checks) return;
4610
4611 // The first N-1 variables that need hole checks may be cached in a bitmap to
4612 // elide subsequent hole checks in the same basic block, where N is
4613 // Variable::kHoleCheckBitmapBits.
4614 //
4615 // This numbering is done during bytecode generation instead of scope analysis
4616 // for 2 reasons:
4617 //
4618 // 1. There may be multiple eagerly compiled inner functions during a single
4619 // run of scope analysis, so a global numbering will result in fewer variables
4620 // with cacheable hole checks.
4621 //
4622 // 2. Compiler::CollectSourcePositions reparses functions and checks that the
4623 // recompiled bytecode is identical. Therefore the numbering must be kept
4624 // identical regardless of whether a function is eagerly compiled as part of
4625 // an outer compilation or recompiled during source position collection. The
4626 // simplest way to guarantee identical numbering is to scope it to the
4627 // compilation instead of scope analysis.
4628 variable->RememberHoleCheckInBitmap(hole_check_bitmap_,
4629 vars_in_hole_check_bitmap_);
4630}
4631
4632void BytecodeGenerator::BuildThrowIfHole(Variable* variable) {
4633 if (variable->is_this()) {
4634 DCHECK(variable->mode() == VariableMode::kConst);
4635 builder()->ThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole();
4636 } else {
4637 builder()->ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole(variable->raw_name());
4638 }
4639 RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable);
4640}
4641
4642bool BytecodeGenerator::VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(
4643 Variable* variable, HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode) {
4644 return hole_check_mode == HoleCheckMode::kRequired &&
4645 !variable->HasRememberedHoleCheck(hole_check_bitmap_);
4646}
4647
4648bool BytecodeGenerator::VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(
4649 Variable* variable, Token::Value op, HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode) {
4650 return VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode) ||
4651 (variable->is_this() && variable->mode() == VariableMode::kConst &&
4652 op == Token::kInit);
4653}
4654
4655void BytecodeGenerator::BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(Variable* variable,
4656 Token::Value op) {
4657 DCHECK(!IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(variable->mode()));
4658 DCHECK(VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(
4659 variable, op, HoleCheckMode::kRequired));
4660 if (variable->is_this()) {
4661 DCHECK(variable->mode() == VariableMode::kConst && op == Token::kInit);
4662 // Perform an initialization check for 'this'. 'this' variable is the
4663 // only variable able to trigger bind operations outside the TDZ
4664 // via 'super' calls.
4665 //
4666 // Do not remember the hole check because this bytecode throws if 'this' is
4667 // *not* the hole, i.e. the opposite of the TDZ hole check.
4668 builder()->ThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole();
4669 } else {
4670 // Perform an initialization check for let/const declared variables.
4671 // E.g. let x = (x = 20); is not allowed.
4672 DCHECK(IsLexicalVariableMode(variable->mode()));
4673 BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4674 }
4675}
4676
4677void BytecodeGenerator::BuildVariableAssignment(
4678 Variable* variable, Token::Value op, HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode,
4679 LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
4680 VariableMode mode = variable->mode();
4681 RegisterAllocationScope assignment_register_scope(this);
4682 switch (variable->location()) {
4683 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
4684 case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
4685 Register destination;
4686 if (VariableLocation::PARAMETER == variable->location()) {
4687 if (variable->IsReceiver()) {
4688 destination = builder()->Receiver();
4689 } else {
4690 destination = builder()->Parameter(variable->index());
4691 }
4692 } else {
4693 destination = builder()->Local(variable->index());
4694 }
4695
4696 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(variable, op,
4697 hole_check_mode)) {
4698 // Load destination to check for hole.
4699 Register value_temp = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4700 builder()
4701 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_temp)
4702 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(destination);
4703 BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(variable, op);
4704 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_temp);
4705 }
4706
4707 if ((mode != VariableMode::kConst && mode != VariableMode::kUsing &&
4708 mode != VariableMode::kAwaitUsing) ||
4709 op == Token::kInit) {
4710 if (op == Token::kInit) {
4711 if (variable->HasHoleCheckUseInSameClosureScope()) {
4712 // After initializing a variable it won't be the hole anymore, so
4713 // elide subsequent checks.
4714 RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable);
4715 }
4716 if (mode == VariableMode::kUsing) {
4717 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4718 builder()
4719 ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack_, args[0])
4720 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
4721 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kAddDisposableValue, args);
4722 } else if (mode == VariableMode::kAwaitUsing) {
4723 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4724 builder()
4725 ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack_, args[0])
4726 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
4727 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kAddAsyncDisposableValue, args);
4728 }
4729 }
4730 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
4731 } else if (variable->throw_on_const_assignment(language_mode()) &&
4732 mode == VariableMode::kConst) {
4733 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4734 } else if (variable->throw_on_const_assignment(language_mode()) &&
4735 mode == VariableMode::kUsing) {
4736 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowUsingAssignError);
4737 }
4738 break;
4739 }
4740 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED: {
4741 BuildStoreGlobal(variable);
4742 break;
4743 }
4744 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
4745 int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4746 ContextScope* context = execution_context()->Previous(depth);
4747 Register context_reg;
4748
4749 if (context) {
4750 context_reg = context->reg();
4751 depth = 0;
4752 } else {
4753 context_reg = execution_context()->reg();
4754 }
4755
4756 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(variable, op,
4757 hole_check_mode)) {
4758 // Load destination to check for hole.
4759 Register value_temp = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4760 builder()
4761 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_temp)
4762 .LoadContextSlot(context_reg, variable, depth,
4763 BytecodeArrayBuilder::kMutableSlot);
4764
4765 BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(variable, op);
4766 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_temp);
4767 }
4768
4769 if (mode != VariableMode::kConst || op == Token::kInit) {
4770 if (op == Token::kInit &&
4771 variable->HasHoleCheckUseInSameClosureScope()) {
4772 // After initializing a variable it won't be the hole anymore, so
4773 // elide subsequent checks.
4774 RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable);
4775 }
4776 builder()->StoreContextSlot(context_reg, variable, depth);
4777 } else if (variable->throw_on_const_assignment(language_mode())) {
4778 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4779 }
4780 break;
4781 }
4782 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
4783 builder()->StoreLookupSlot(variable->raw_name(), language_mode(),
4784 lookup_hoisting_mode);
4785 break;
4786 }
4787 case VariableLocation::MODULE: {
4788 DCHECK(IsDeclaredVariableMode(mode));
4789
4790 if (mode == VariableMode::kConst && op != Token::kInit) {
4791 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4792 break;
4793 }
4794
4795 // If we don't throw above, we know that we're dealing with an
4796 // export because imports are const and we do not generate initializing
4797 // assignments for them.
4798 DCHECK(variable->IsExport());
4799
4800 int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4801 if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(variable, op,
4802 hole_check_mode)) {
4803 Register value_temp = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4804 builder()
4805 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_temp)
4806 .LoadModuleVariable(variable->index(), depth);
4807 BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(variable, op);
4808 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_temp);
4809 }
4810 builder()->StoreModuleVariable(variable->index(), depth);
4811 break;
4812 }
4813 case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL: {
4814 // A let or const declaration like 'let x = 7' is effectively translated
4815 // to:
4816 // <top of the script>:
4817 // ScriptContext.x = TheHole;
4818 // ...
4819 // <where the actual 'let' is>:
4820 // ScriptContextTable.x = 7; // no hole check
4821 //
4822 // The ScriptContext slot for 'x' that we store to here is not
4823 // necessarily the ScriptContext of this script, but rather the
4824 // first ScriptContext that has a slot for name 'x'.
4825 DCHECK(variable->IsReplGlobal());
4826 if (op == Token::kInit) {
4827 RegisterList store_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4828 builder()
4829 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(store_args[1])
4830 .LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
4831 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(store_args[0]);
4832 builder()->CallRuntime(
4833 Runtime::kStoreGlobalNoHoleCheckForReplLetOrConst, store_args);
4834 } else {
4835 if (mode == VariableMode::kConst) {
4836 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4837 } else {
4838 BuildStoreGlobal(variable);
4839 }
4840 }
4841 break;
4842 }
4843 }
4844}

4848 const AstRawString* name) {
4849 FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadICSlot(object_expr, name);
4850 builder()->LoadNamedProperty(object, name, feedback_index(slot));
4851}
4852
4853void BytecodeGenerator::BuildSetNamedProperty(const Expression* object_expr,
4854 Register object,
4855 const AstRawString* name) {
4856 Register value;
4857 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
4858 value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4859 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
4860 }
4861
4862 FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedStoreICSlot(object_expr, name);
4863 builder()->SetNamedProperty(object, name, feedback_index(slot),
4864 language_mode());
4865
4866 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
4867 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
4868 }
4869}

4871void BytecodeGenerator::BuildStoreGlobal(Variable* variable) {
4872 Register value;
4873 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
4874 value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4875 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
4876 }
4877
4878 FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedStoreGlobalICSlot(language_mode(), variable);
4879 builder()->StoreGlobal(variable->raw_name(), feedback_index(slot));
4880
4881 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
4882 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
4883 }
4884}
4885
4886void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLoadKeyedProperty(Register object,
4887 FeedbackSlot slot) {
4888 if (v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode &&
4889 current_for_in_scope() != nullptr) {

4891 if (key != nullptr) {
4892 ForInScope* scope = current_for_in_scope()->GetForInScope(key);
4893 if (scope != nullptr) {
4894 Register enum_index = scope->enum_index();
4895 Register cache_type = scope->cache_type();
4896 builder()->LoadEnumeratedKeyedProperty(object, enum_index, cache_type,
4897 feedback_index(slot));
4898 return;
4899 }
4900 }
4901 }
4902 builder()->LoadKeyedProperty(object, feedback_index(slot));
4903}
