4955
4956BytecodeGenerator::AssignmentLhsData BytecodeGenerator::PrepareAssignmentLhs(
4957 Expression* lhs, AccumulatorPreservingMode accumulator_preserving_mode) {
4958 // Left-hand side can only be a property, a global or a variable slot.
4959 Property* property = lhs->AsProperty();
4960 AssignType assign_type = Property::GetAssignType(property);
4961
4962 // Evaluate LHS expression.
4963 switch (assign_type) {
4964 case NON_PROPERTY:
4965 return AssignmentLhsData::NonProperty(lhs);
4966 case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
4967 AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
4968 Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
4969 const AstRawString* name =
4970 property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
4971 return AssignmentLhsData::NamedProperty(property->obj(), object, name);
4972 }
4973 case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
4974 AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
4975 Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
4976 Register key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
4977 return AssignmentLhsData::KeyedProperty(object, key);
4978 }
4979 case PRIVATE_METHOD:
4980 case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
4981 case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY:
4982 case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
4983 DCHECK(!property->IsSuperAccess());
4984 AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
4985 Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
4986 Register key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
4987 return AssignmentLhsData::PrivateMethodOrAccessor(assign_type, property,
4988 object, key);
4989 }
4990 case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
4991 AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
4992 Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
4993 // Do not visit the key here, instead we will look them up at run time.
4994 return AssignmentLhsData::PrivateDebugEvaluate(assign_type, property,
4995 object);
4996 }
4997 case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
4998 AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
4999 RegisterList super_property_args =
5000 register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
5001 BuildThisVariableLoad();
5002 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[0]);
5003 BuildVariableLoad(
5004 property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
5005 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
5006 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[1]);
5007 builder()
5008 ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
5009 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[2]);
5010 return AssignmentLhsData::NamedSuperProperty(super_property_args);
5011 }
5012 case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5013 AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
5014 RegisterList super_property_args =
5015 register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
5016 BuildThisVariableLoad();
5017 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[0]);
5018 BuildVariableLoad(
5019 property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
5020 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
5021 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[1]);
5022 VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), super_property_args[2]);
5023 return AssignmentLhsData::KeyedSuperProperty(super_property_args);
5024 }
5025 }
5026 UNREACHABLE();
5027}
5028
5029// Build the iteration finalizer called in the finally block of an iteration
5030// protocol execution. This closes the iterator if needed, and suppresses any
5031// exception it throws if necessary, including the exception when the return
5032// method is not callable.
5033//
5034// In pseudo-code, this builds:
5035//
5036// if (!done) {
5037// try {
5038// let method = iterator.return
5039// if (method !== null && method !== undefined) {
5040// let return_val = method.call(iterator)
5041// if (!%IsObject(return_val)) throw TypeError
5042// }
5043// } catch (e) {
5044// if (iteration_continuation != RETHROW)
5045// rethrow e
5046// }
5047// }
5048//
5049// For async iterators, iterator.close() becomes await iterator.close().
5050void BytecodeGenerator::BuildFinalizeIteration(
5051 IteratorRecord iterator, Register done,
5052 Register iteration_continuation_token) {
5053 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5054 BytecodeLabels iterator_is_done(zone());
5055
5056 // if (!done) {
5057 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(done).JumpIfTrue(
5058 ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, iterator_is_done.New());
5059
5060 {
5061 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
5062 BuildTryCatch(
5063 // try {
5064 // let method = iterator.return
5065 // if (method !== null && method !== undefined) {
5066 // let return_val = method.call(iterator)
5067 // if (!%IsObject(return_val)) throw TypeError
5068 // }
5069 // }
5070 [&]() {
5071 Register method = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5072 builder()
5073 ->LoadNamedProperty(
5074 iterator.object(), ast_string_constants()->return_string(),
5075 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
5076 .JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(iterator_is_done.New())
5077 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method);
5078
5079 RegisterList args(iterator.object());
5080 builder()->CallProperty(
5081 method, args, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
5082 if (iterator.type() == IteratorType::kAsync) {
5083 BuildAwait();
5084 }
5085 builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(iterator_is_done.New());
5086 {
5087 // Throw this exception inside the try block so that it is
5088 // suppressed by the iteration continuation if necessary.
5089 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5090 Register return_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5091 builder()
5092 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(return_result)
5093 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject,
5094 return_result);
5095 }
5096 },
5097
5098 // catch (e) {
5099 // if (iteration_continuation != RETHROW)
5100 // rethrow e
5101 // }
5102 [&](Register context) {
5103 // Reuse context register to store the exception.
5104 Register close_exception = context;
5105 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(close_exception);
5106
5107 BytecodeLabel suppress_close_exception;
5108 builder()
5109 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(
5110 static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken)))
5111 .CompareReference(iteration_continuation_token)
5112 .JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
5113 &suppress_close_exception)
5114 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(close_exception)
5115 .ReThrow()
5116 .Bind(&suppress_close_exception);
5117 },
5118 catch_prediction());
5119 }
5120
5121 iterator_is_done.Bind(builder());
5122}
5123
5124// Get the default value of a destructuring target. Will mutate the
5125// destructuring target expression if there is a default value.
5126//
5127// For
5128// a = b
5129// in
5130// let {a = b} = c
5131// returns b and mutates the input into a.
5132Expression* BytecodeGenerator::GetDestructuringDefaultValue(
5133 Expression** target) {
5134 Expression* default_value = nullptr;
5135 if ((*target)->IsAssignment()) {
5136 Assignment* default_init = (*target)->AsAssignment();
5137 DCHECK_EQ(default_init->op(), Token::kAssign);
5138 default_value = default_init->value();
5139 *target = default_init->target();
5140 DCHECK((*target)->IsValidReferenceExpression() || (*target)->IsPattern());
5141 }
5142 return default_value;
5143}
5144
5145// Convert a destructuring assignment to an array literal into a sequence of
5146// iterator accesses into the value being assigned (in the accumulator).
5147//
5148// [a().x, ...b] = accumulator
5149//
5150// becomes
5151//
5152// iterator = %GetIterator(accumulator)
5153// try {
5154//
5155// // Individual assignments read off the value from iterator.next() This gets
5156// // repeated per destructuring element.
5157// if (!done) {
5158// // Make sure we are considered 'done' if .next(), .done or .value fail.
5159// done = true
5160// var next_result = iterator.next()
5161// var tmp_done = next_result.done
5162// if (!tmp_done) {
5163// value = next_result.value
5164// done = false
5165// }
5166// }
5167// if (done)
5168// value = undefined
5169// a().x = value
5170//
5171// // A spread receives the remaining items in the iterator.
5172// var array = []
5173// var index = 0
5174// %FillArrayWithIterator(iterator, array, index, done)
5175// done = true
5176// b = array
5177//
5178// } catch(e) {
5179// iteration_continuation = RETHROW
5180// } finally {
5181// %FinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation)
5182// }
5183void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDestructuringArrayAssignment(
5184 ArrayLiteral* pattern, Token::Value op,
5185 LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
5186 RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
5187
5188 Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5189 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5190
5191 // Store the iterator in a dedicated register so that it can be closed on
5192 // exit, and the 'done' value in a dedicated register so that it can be
5193 // changed and accessed independently of the iteration result.
5194 IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(IteratorType::kNormal);
5195 Register done = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5196 builder()->LoadFalse();
5197 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5198
5199 BuildTryFinally(
5200 // Try block.
5201 [&]() {
5202 Register next_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5203 FeedbackSlot next_value_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
5204 FeedbackSlot next_done_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
5205
5206 Spread* spread = nullptr;
5207 for (Expression* target : *pattern->values()) {
5208 if (target->IsSpread()) {
5209 spread = target->AsSpread();
5210 break;
5211 }
5212
5213 Expression* default_value = GetDestructuringDefaultValue(&target);
5214 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(target);
5215
5216 AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(target);
5217
5218 // if (!done) {
5219 // // Make sure we are considered done if .next(), .done or .value
5220 // // fail.
5221 // done = true
5222 // var next_result = iterator.next()
5223 // var tmp_done = next_result.done
5224 // if (!tmp_done) {
5225 // value = next_result.value
5226 // done = false
5227 // }
5228 // }
5229 // if (done)
5230 // value = undefined
5231 BytecodeLabels is_done(zone());
5232
5233 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(done);
5234 builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean,
5235 is_done.New());
5236
5237 builder()->LoadTrue().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5238 BuildIteratorNext(iterator, next_result);
5239 builder()
5240 ->LoadNamedProperty(next_result,
5241 ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
5242 feedback_index(next_done_load_slot))
5243 .JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, is_done.New());
5244
5245 // Only do the assignment if this is not a hole (i.e. 'elided').
5246 if (!target->IsTheHoleLiteral()) {
5247 builder()
5248 ->LoadNamedProperty(next_result,
5249 ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
5250 feedback_index(next_value_load_slot))
5251 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next_result)
5252 .LoadFalse()
5253 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done)
5254 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(next_result);
5255
5256 // [<pattern> = <init>] = <value>
5257 // becomes (roughly)
5258 // temp = <value>.next();
5259 // <pattern> = temp === undefined ? <init> : temp;
5260 BytecodeLabel do_assignment;
5261 if (default_value) {
5262 builder()->JumpIfNotUndefined(&do_assignment);
5263 // Since done == true => temp == undefined, jump directly to using
5264 // the default value for that case.
5265 is_done.Bind(builder());
5266 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(default_value);
5267 } else {
5268 builder()->Jump(&do_assignment);
5269 is_done.Bind(builder());
5270 builder()->LoadUndefined();
5271 }
5272 builder()->Bind(&do_assignment);
5273
5274 BuildAssignment(lhs_data, op, lookup_hoisting_mode);
5275 } else {
5276 builder()->LoadFalse().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5277 DCHECK_EQ(lhs_data.assign_type(), NON_PROPERTY);
5278 is_done.Bind(builder());
5279 }
5280 }
5281
5282 if (spread) {
5283 RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
5284 BytecodeLabel is_done;
5285
5286 // A spread is turned into a loop over the remainer of the iterator.
5287 Expression* target = spread->expression();
5288 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(spread);
5289
5290 AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(target);
5291
5292 // var array = [];
5293 Register array = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5294 builder()->CreateEmptyArrayLiteral(
5295 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot()));
5296 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(array);
5297
5298 // If done, jump to assigning empty array
5299 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(done);
5300 builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, &is_done);
5301
5302 // var index = 0;
5303 Register index = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5304 builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::zero());
5305 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
5306
5307 // Set done to true, since it's guaranteed to be true by the time the
5308 // array fill completes.
5309 builder()->LoadTrue().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5310
5311 // Fill the array with the iterator.
5312 FeedbackSlot element_slot =
5313 feedback_spec()->AddStoreInArrayLiteralICSlot();
5314 FeedbackSlot index_slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
5315 BuildFillArrayWithIterator(iterator, array, index, next_result,
5316 next_value_load_slot, next_done_load_slot,
5317 index_slot, element_slot);
5318
5319 builder()->Bind(&is_done);
5320 // Assign the array to the LHS.
5321 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(array);
5322 BuildAssignment(lhs_data, op, lookup_hoisting_mode);
5323 }
5324 },
5325 // Finally block.
5326 [&](Register iteration_continuation_token,
5327 Register iteration_continuation_result) {
5328 // Finish the iteration in the finally block.
5329 BuildFinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation_token);
5330 },
5331 HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT);
5332
5333 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5334 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5335 }
5336}
5337
5338// Convert a destructuring assignment to an object literal into a sequence of
5339// property accesses into the value being assigned (in the accumulator).
5340//
5341// { y, [x++]: a(), ...b.c } = value
5342//
5343// becomes
5344//
5345// var rest_runtime_callargs = new Array(3);
5346// rest_runtime_callargs[0] = value;
5347//
5348// rest_runtime_callargs[1] = "y";
5349// y = value.y;
5350//
5351// var temp1 = %ToName(x++);
5352// rest_runtime_callargs[2] = temp1;
5353// a() = value[temp1];
5354//
5355// b.c =
5356// %CopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedPropertiesOnStack.call(rest_runtime_callargs);
5357void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDestructuringObjectAssignment(
5358 ObjectLiteral* pattern, Token::Value op,
5359 LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
5360 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5361
5362 // Store the assignment value in a register.
5363 Register value;
5364 RegisterList rest_runtime_callargs;
5365 if (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property()) {
5366 rest_runtime_callargs =
5367 register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(pattern->properties()->length());
5368 value = rest_runtime_callargs[0];
5369 } else {
5370 value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5371 }
5372 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5373
5374 // if (value === null || value === undefined)
5375 // throw new TypeError(kNonCoercible);
5376 //
5377 // Since the first property access on null/undefined will also trigger a
5378 // TypeError, we can elide this check. The exception is when there are no
5379 // properties and no rest property (this is an empty literal), or when the
5380 // first property is a computed name and accessing it can have side effects.
5381 //
5382 // TODO(leszeks): Also eliminate this check if the value is known to be
5383 // non-null (e.g. an object literal).
5384 if (pattern->properties()->is_empty() ||
5385 (pattern->properties()->at(0)->is_computed_name() &&
5386 pattern->properties()->at(0)->kind() != ObjectLiteralProperty::SPREAD)) {
5387 BytecodeLabel is_null_or_undefined, not_null_or_undefined;
5388 builder()
5389 ->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&is_null_or_undefined)
5390 .Jump(&not_null_or_undefined);
5391
5392 {
5393 builder()->Bind(&is_null_or_undefined);
5394 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(pattern);
5395 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowPatternAssignmentNonCoercible,
5396 value);
5397 }
5398 builder()->Bind(&not_null_or_undefined);
5399 }
5400
5401 int i = 0;
5402 for (ObjectLiteralProperty* pattern_property : *pattern->properties()) {
5403 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
5404
5405 // The key of the pattern becomes the key into the RHS value, and the value
5406 // of the pattern becomes the target of the assignment.
5407 //
5408 // e.g. { a: b } = o becomes b = o.a
5409 Expression* pattern_key = pattern_property->key();
5410 Expression* target = pattern_property->value();
5411 Expression* default_value = GetDestructuringDefaultValue(&target);
5412 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(target);
5413
5414 // Calculate this property's key into the assignment RHS value, additionally
5415 // storing the key for rest_runtime_callargs if needed.
5416 //
5417 // The RHS is accessed using the key either by LoadNamedProperty (if
5418 // value_name is valid) or by LoadKeyedProperty (otherwise).
5419 const AstRawString* value_name = nullptr;
5420 Register value_key;
5421
5422 if (pattern_property->kind() != ObjectLiteralProperty::Kind::SPREAD) {
5423 if (pattern_key->IsPropertyName()) {
5424 value_name = pattern_key->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
5425 }
5426 if (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property() || !value_name) {
5427 if (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property()) {
5428 value_key = rest_runtime_callargs[i + 1];
5429 } else {
5430 value_key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5431 }
5432 if (pattern_property->is_computed_name()) {
5433 // { [a()]: b().x } = c
5434 // becomes
5435 // var tmp = a()
5436 // b().x = c[tmp]
5437 DCHECK(!pattern_key->IsPropertyName() ||
5438 !pattern_key->IsNumberLiteral());
5439 VisitForAccumulatorValue(pattern_key);
5440 builder()->ToName().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_key);
5441 } else {
5442 // We only need the key for non-computed properties when it is numeric
5443 // or is being saved for the rest_runtime_callargs.
5444 DCHECK(pattern_key->IsNumberLiteral() ||
5445 (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property() &&
5446 pattern_key->IsPropertyName()));
5447 VisitForRegisterValue(pattern_key, value_key);
5448 }
5449 }
5450 }
5451
5452 AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(target);
5453
5454 // Get the value from the RHS.
5455 if (pattern_property->kind() == ObjectLiteralProperty::Kind::SPREAD) {
5456 DCHECK_EQ(i, pattern->properties()->length() - 1);
5457 DCHECK(!value_key.is_valid());
5458 DCHECK_NULL(value_name);
5459 builder()->CallRuntime(
5460 Runtime::kInlineCopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedPropertiesOnStack,
5461 rest_runtime_callargs);
5462 } else if (value_name) {
5463 builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
5464 value, value_name, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
5465 } else {
5466 DCHECK(value_key.is_valid());
5467 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_key).LoadKeyedProperty(
5468 value, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot()));
5469 }
5470
5471 // {<pattern> = <init>} = <value>
5472 // becomes
5473 // temp = <value>;
5474 // <pattern> = temp === undefined ? <init> : temp;
5475 if (default_value) {
5476 BytecodeLabel value_not_undefined;
5477 builder()->JumpIfNotUndefined(&value_not_undefined);
5478 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(default_value);
5479 builder()->Bind(&value_not_undefined);
5480 }
5481
5482 BuildAssignment(lhs_data, op, lookup_hoisting_mode);
5483
5484 i++;
5485 }
5486
5487 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5488 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5489 }
5490}
5491
5492void BytecodeGenerator::BuildAssignment(
5493 const AssignmentLhsData& lhs_data, Token::Value op,
5494 LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
5495 // Assign the value to the LHS.
5496 switch (lhs_data.assign_type()) {
5497 case NON_PROPERTY: {
5498 if (ObjectLiteral* pattern_as_object =
5499 lhs_data.expr()->AsObjectLiteral()) {
5500 // Split object literals into destructuring.
5501 BuildDestructuringObjectAssignment(pattern_as_object, op,
5502 lookup_hoisting_mode);
5503 } else if (ArrayLiteral* pattern_as_array =
5504 lhs_data.expr()->AsArrayLiteral()) {
5505 // Split object literals into destructuring.
5506 BuildDestructuringArrayAssignment(pattern_as_array, op,
5507 lookup_hoisting_mode);
5508 } else {
5509 DCHECK(lhs_data.expr()->IsVariableProxy());
5510 VariableProxy* proxy = lhs_data.expr()->AsVariableProxy();
5511 BuildVariableAssignment(proxy->var(), op, proxy->hole_check_mode(),
5512 lookup_hoisting_mode);
5513 }
5514 break;
5515 }
5516 case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
5517 BuildSetNamedProperty(lhs_data.object_expr(), lhs_data.object(),
5518 lhs_data.name());
5519 break;
5520 }
5521 case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
5522 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedStoreICSlot(language_mode());
5523 Register value;
5524 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5525 value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5526 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5527 }
5528 builder()->SetKeyedProperty(lhs_data.object(), lhs_data.key(),
5529 feedback_index(slot), language_mode());
5530 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5531 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5532 }
5533 break;
5534 }
5535 case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5536 builder()
5537 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs_data.super_property_args()[3])
5538 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreToSuper, lhs_data.super_property_args());
5539 break;
5540 }
5541 case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5542 builder()
5543 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs_data.super_property_args()[3])
5544 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreKeyedToSuper,
5545 lhs_data.super_property_args());
5546 break;
5547 }
5548 case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
5549 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5550 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5551 BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMethodWrite,
5552 lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty());
5553 break;
5554 }
5555 case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY: {
5556 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5557 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5558 BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateSetterAccess,
5559 lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty());
5560 break;
5561 }
5562 case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY:
5563 case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
5564 Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5565 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5566 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5567 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5568 BuildPrivateSetterAccess(lhs_data.object(), lhs_data.key(), value);
5569 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5570 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5571 }
5572 break;
5573 }
5574 case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
5575 Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5576 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5577 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5578 BuildPrivateDebugDynamicSet(property, lhs_data.object(), value);
5579 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5580 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5581 }
5582 break;
5583 }
5584 }
5585}
5586
5587void BytecodeGenerator::VisitAssignment(Assignment* expr) {
5588 AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(expr->target());
5589
5590 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5591
5592 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5593 BuildAssignment(lhs_data, expr->op(), expr->lookup_hoisting_mode());
5594}
5595
5596void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCompoundAssignment(CompoundAssignment* expr) {
5597 AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(expr->target());
5598
5599 // Evaluate the value and potentially handle compound assignments by loading
5600 // the left-hand side value and performing a binary operation.
5601 switch (lhs_data.assign_type()) {
5602 case NON_PROPERTY: {
5603 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->target()->AsVariableProxy();
5604 BuildVariableLoad(proxy->var(), proxy->hole_check_mode());
5605 break;
5606 }
5607 case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
5608 BuildLoadNamedProperty(lhs_data.object_expr(), lhs_data.object(),
5609 lhs_data.name());
5610 break;
5611 }
5612 case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
5613 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot();
5614 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(lhs_data.key());
5615 BuildLoadKeyedProperty(lhs_data.object(), slot);
5616 break;
5617 }
5618 case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5619 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadFromSuper,
5620 lhs_data.super_property_args().Truncate(3));
5621 break;
5622 }
5623 case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5624 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadKeyedFromSuper,
5625 lhs_data.super_property_args().Truncate(3));
5626 break;
5627 }
5628 // BuildAssignment() will throw an error about the private method being
5629 // read-only.
5630 case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
5631 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5632 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5633 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(lhs_data.key());
5634 break;
5635 }
5636 // For read-only properties, BuildAssignment() will throw an error about
5637 // the missing setter.
5638 case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
5639 case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
5640 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5641 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5642 BuildPrivateGetterAccess(lhs_data.object(), lhs_data.key());
5643 break;
5644 }
5645 case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY: {
5646 // The property access is invalid, but if the brand check fails too, we
5647 // need to return the error from the brand check.
5648 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5649 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5650 BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateGetterAccess,
5651 lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty());
5652 break;
5653 }
5654 case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
5655 Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5656 BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(property, lhs_data.object());
5657 break;
5658 }
5659 }
5660
5661 BinaryOperation* binop = expr->binary_operation();
5662 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
5663 BytecodeLabel short_circuit;
5664 if (binop->op() == Token::kNullish) {
5665 BytecodeLabel nullish;
5666 builder()
5667 ->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&nullish)
5668 .Jump(&short_circuit)
5669 .Bind(&nullish);
5670 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5671 } else if (binop->op() == Token::kOr) {
5672 builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, &short_circuit);
5673 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5674 } else if (binop->op() == Token::kAnd) {
5675 builder()->JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, &short_circuit);
5676 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5677 } else if (expr->value()->IsSmiLiteral()) {
5678 builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(
5679 binop->op(), expr->value()->AsLiteral()->AsSmiLiteral(),
5680 feedback_index(slot));
5681 } else {
5682 Register old_value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5683 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(old_value);
5684 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5685 builder()->BinaryOperation(binop->op(), old_value, feedback_index(slot));
5686 }
5687 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5688
5689 BuildAssignment(lhs_data, expr->op(), expr->lookup_hoisting_mode());
5690 builder()->Bind(&short_circuit);
5691}
5692
5693// Suspends the generator to resume at the next suspend_id, with output stored
5694// in the accumulator. When the generator is resumed, the sent value is loaded
5695// in the accumulator.
5696void BytecodeGenerator::BuildSuspendPoint(int position) {
5697 // Because we eliminate jump targets in dead code, we also eliminate resumes
5698 // when the suspend is not emitted because otherwise the below call to Bind
5699 // would start a new basic block and the code would be considered alive.
5700 if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
5701 return;
5702 }
5703 const int suspend_id = suspend_count_++;
5704
5705 RegisterList registers = register_allocator()->AllLiveRegisters();
5706
5707 // Save context, registers, and state. This bytecode then returns the value
5708 // in the accumulator.
5709 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(position);
5710 builder()->SuspendGenerator(generator_object(), registers, suspend_id);
5711
5712 // Upon resume, we continue here.
5713 builder()->Bind(generator_jump_table_, suspend_id);
5714
5715 // Clobbers all registers and sets the accumulator to the
5716 // [[input_or_debug_pos]] slot of the generator object.
5717 builder()->ResumeGenerator(generator_object(), registers);
5718}
5719
5720void BytecodeGenerator::VisitYield(Yield* expr) {
5721 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5722 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
5723
5724 bool is_async = IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind());
5725 // If this is not the first yield
5726 if (suspend_count_ > 0) {
5727 if (is_async) {
5728 // AsyncGenerator yields (with the exception of the initial yield)
5729 // delegate work to the AsyncGeneratorYieldWithAwait stub, which Awaits
5730 // the operand and on success, wraps the value in an IteratorResult.
5731 //
5732 // In the spec the Await is a separate operation, but they are combined
5733 // here to reduce bytecode size.
5734 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5735 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
5736 builder()
5737 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
5738 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
5739 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorYieldWithAwait, args);
5740 } else {
5741 // Generator yields (with the exception of the initial yield) wrap the
5742 // value into IteratorResult.
5743 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5744 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
5745 builder()
5746 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]) // value
5747 .LoadFalse()
5748 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // done
5749 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineCreateIterResultObject, args);
5750 }
5751 }
5752
5753 BuildSuspendPoint(expr->position());
5754 // At this point, the generator has been resumed, with the received value in
5755 // the accumulator.
5756
5757 // TODO(caitp): remove once yield* desugaring for async generators is handled
5758 // in BytecodeGenerator.
5759 if (expr->on_abrupt_resume() == Yield::kNoControl) {
5760 DCHECK(is_async);
5761 return;
5762 }
5763
5764 Register input = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5765 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input).CallRuntime(
5766 Runtime::kInlineGeneratorGetResumeMode, generator_object());
5767
5768 // Now dispatch on resume mode.
5769 static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kNext + 1 == JSGeneratorObject::kReturn);
5770 static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kReturn + 1 == JSGeneratorObject::kThrow);
5771 BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table =
5772 builder()->AllocateJumpTable(is_async ? 3 : 2, JSGeneratorObject::kNext);
5773
5774 builder()->SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback(jump_table);
5775
5776 if (is_async) {
5777 // Resume with rethrow (switch fallthrough).
5778 // This case is only necessary in async generators.
5779 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5780 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5781 builder()->ReThrow();
5782
5783 // Add label for kThrow (next case).
5784 builder()->Bind(jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kThrow);
5785 }
5786
5787 {
5788 // Resume with throw (switch fallthrough in sync case).
5789 // TODO(leszeks): Add a debug-only check that the accumulator is
5790 // JSGeneratorObject::kThrow.
5791 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5792 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5793 builder()->Throw();
5794 }
5795
5796 {
5797 // Resume with return.
5798 builder()->Bind(jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kReturn);
5799 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5800 if (is_async) {
5801 execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
5802 } else {
5803 execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
5804 }
5805 }
5806
5807 {
5808 // Resume with next.
5809 builder()->Bind(jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kNext);
5810 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(expr,
5811 SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
5812 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5813 }
5814}
5815
5816// Desugaring of (yield* iterable)
5817//
5818// do {
5819// const kNext = 0;
5820// const kReturn = 1;
5821// const kThrow = 2;
5822//
5823// let output; // uninitialized
5824//
5825// let iteratorRecord = GetIterator(iterable);
5826// let iterator = iteratorRecord.[[Iterator]];
5827// let next = iteratorRecord.[[NextMethod]];
5828// let input = undefined;
5829// let resumeMode = kNext;
5830//
5831// while (true) {
5832// // From the generator to the iterator:
5833// // Forward input according to resumeMode and obtain output.
5834// switch (resumeMode) {
5835// case kNext:
5836// output = next.[[Call]](iterator, Â« Â»);;
5837// break;
5838// case kReturn:
5839// let iteratorReturn = iterator.return;
5840// if (IS_NULL_OR_UNDEFINED(iteratorReturn)) {
5841// if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) input = await input;
5842// return input;
5843// }
5844// output = iteratorReturn.[[Call]](iterator, Â«inputÂ»);
5845// break;
5846// case kThrow:
5847// let iteratorThrow = iterator.throw;
5848// if (IS_NULL_OR_UNDEFINED(iteratorThrow)) {
5849// let iteratorReturn = iterator.return;
5850// if (!IS_NULL_OR_UNDEFINED(iteratorReturn)) {
5851// output = iteratorReturn.[[Call]](iterator, Â« Â»);
5852// if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) output = await output;
5853// if (!IS_RECEIVER(output)) %ThrowIterResultNotAnObject(output);
5854// }
5855// throw MakeTypeError(kThrowMethodMissing);
5856// }
5857// output = iteratorThrow.[[Call]](iterator, Â«inputÂ»);
5858// break;
5859// }
5860//
5861// if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) output = await output;
5862// if (!IS_RECEIVER(output)) %ThrowIterResultNotAnObject(output);
5863// if (output.done) break;
5864//
5865// // From the generator to its user:
5866// // Forward output, receive new input, and determine resume mode.
5867// if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) {
5868// // Resolve the promise for the current AsyncGeneratorRequest.
5869// %_AsyncGeneratorResolve(output.value, /* done = */ false)
5870// }
5871// input = Suspend(output);
5872// resumeMode = %GeneratorGetResumeMode();
5873// }
5874//
5875// if (resumeMode === kReturn) {
5876// return output.value;
5877// }
5878// output.value
5879// }
5880void BytecodeGenerator::VisitYieldStar(YieldStar* expr) {
5881 Register output = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5882 Register resume_mode = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5883 IteratorType iterator_type = IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())
5884 ? IteratorType::kAsync
5885 : IteratorType::kNormal;
5886
5887 {
5888 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5889 RegisterList iterator_and_input = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
5890 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
5891 IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(
5892 register_allocator()->NewRegister() /* next method */,
5893 iterator_and_input[0], iterator_type);
5894
5895 Register input = iterator_and_input[1];
5896 builder()->LoadUndefined().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input);
5897 builder()
5898 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(JSGeneratorObject::kNext))
5899 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(resume_mode);
5900
5901 {
5902 // This loop builder does not construct counters as the loop is not
5903 // visible to the user, and we therefore neither pass the block coverage
5904 // builder nor the expression.
5905 //
5906 // In addition to the normal suspend for yield*, a yield* in an async
5907 // generator has 2 additional suspends:
5908 // - One for awaiting the iterator result of closing the generator when
5909 // resumed with a "throw" completion, and a throw method is not
5910 // present on the delegated iterator
5911 // - One for awaiting the iterator result yielded by the delegated
5912 // iterator
5913
5914 LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), nullptr, nullptr, feedback_spec());
5915 LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
5916
5917 {
5918 BytecodeLabels after_switch(zone());
5919 BytecodeJumpTable* switch_jump_table =
5920 builder()->AllocateJumpTable(2, 1);
5921
5922 builder()
5923 ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(resume_mode)
5924 .SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback(switch_jump_table);
5925
5926 // Fallthrough to default case.
5927 // TODO(ignition): Add debug code to check that {resume_mode} really is
5928 // {JSGeneratorObject::kNext} in this case.
5929 static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kNext == 0);
5930 {
5931 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot();
5932 builder()->CallProperty(iterator.next(), iterator_and_input,
5933 feedback_index(slot));
5934 builder()->Jump(after_switch.New());
5935 }
5936
5937 static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kReturn == 1);
5938 builder()->Bind(switch_jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kReturn);
5939 {
5940 const AstRawString* return_string =
5941 ast_string_constants()->return_string();
5942 BytecodeLabels no_return_method(zone());
5943
5944 BuildCallIteratorMethod(iterator.object(), return_string,
5945 iterator_and_input, after_switch.New(),
5946 &no_return_method);
5947 no_return_method.Bind(builder());
5948 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5949 if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kAsync) {
5950 // Await input.
5951 BuildAwait(expr->position());
5952 execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
5953 } else {
5954 execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
5955 }
5956 }
5957
5958 static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kThrow == 2);
5959 builder()->Bind(switch_jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kThrow);
5960 {
5961 const AstRawString* throw_string =
5962 ast_string_constants()->throw_string();
5963 BytecodeLabels no_throw_method(zone());
5964 BuildCallIteratorMethod(iterator.object(), throw_string,
5965 iterator_and_input, after_switch.New(),
5966 &no_throw_method);
5967
5968 // If there is no "throw" method, perform IteratorClose, and finally
5969 // throw a TypeError.
5970 no_throw_method.Bind(builder());
5971 BuildIteratorClose(iterator, expr);
5972 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowThrowMethodMissing);
5973 }
5974
5975 after_switch.Bind(builder());
5976 }
5977
5978 if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kAsync) {
5979 // Await the result of the method invocation.
5980 BuildAwait(expr->position());
5981 }
5982
5983 // Check that output is an object.
5984 BytecodeLabel check_if_done;
5985 builder()
5986 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(output)
5987 .JumpIfJSReceiver(&check_if_done)
5988 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject, output);
5989
5990 builder()->Bind(&check_if_done);
5991 // Break once output.done is true.
5992 builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
5993 output, ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
5994 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
5995
5996 loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
5997
5998 // Suspend the current generator.
5999 if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kNormal) {
6000 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output);
6001 } else {
6002 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6003 DCHECK_EQ(iterator_type, IteratorType::kAsync);
6004 // If generatorKind is async, perform
6005 // AsyncGeneratorResolve(output.value, /* done = */ false), which will
6006 // resolve the current AsyncGeneratorRequest's promise with
6007 // output.value.
6008 builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
6009 output, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
6010 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
6011
6012 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6013 builder()
6014 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
6015 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
6016 .LoadFalse()
6017 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2]) // done
6018 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorResolve, args);
6019 }
6020
6021 BuildSuspendPoint(expr->position());
6022 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input);
6023 builder()
6024 ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineGeneratorGetResumeMode,
6025 generator_object())
6026 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(resume_mode);
6027
6028 loop_builder.BindContinueTarget();
6029 }
6030 }
6031
6032 // Decide if we trigger a return or if the yield* expression should just
6033 // produce a value.
6034 BytecodeLabel completion_is_output_value;
6035 Register output_value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6036 builder()
6037 ->LoadNamedProperty(output, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
6038 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
6039 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(output_value)
6040 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(JSGeneratorObject::kReturn))
6041 .CompareReference(resume_mode)
6042 .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &completion_is_output_value)
6043 .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output_value);
6044 if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kAsync) {
6045 execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
6046 } else {
6047 execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
6048 }
6049
6050 builder()->Bind(&completion_is_output_value);
6051 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(expr,
6052 SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
6053 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output_value);
6054}
6055
6056void BytecodeGenerator::BuildAwait(int position) {
6057 // Rather than HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT, async functions use
6058 // HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT to communicate that top-level exceptions are
6059 // transformed into promise rejections. This is necessary to prevent emitting
6060 // multiple debug events for the same uncaught exception. There is no point
6061 // in the body of an async function where catch prediction is
6062 // HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT.
6063 DCHECK(catch_prediction() != HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT ||
6064 info()->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope());
6065
6066 {
6067 // Await(operand) and suspend.
6068 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6069
6070 Runtime::FunctionId await_intrinsic_id;
6071 if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())) {
6072 await_intrinsic_id = Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorAwait;
6073 } else {
6074 await_intrinsic_id = Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionAwait;
6075 }
6076 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6077 builder()
6078 ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0])
6079 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6080 .CallRuntime(await_intrinsic_id, args);
6081 }
6082
6083 BuildSuspendPoint(position);
6084
6085 Register input = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6086 Register resume_mode = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6087
6088 // Now dispatch on resume mode.
6089 BytecodeLabel resume_next;
6090 builder()
6091 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input)
6092 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineGeneratorGetResumeMode, generator_object())
6093 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(resume_mode)
6094 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(JSGeneratorObject::kNext))
6095 .CompareReference(resume_mode)
6096 .JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &resume_next);
6097
6098 // Resume with "throw" completion (rethrow the received value).
6099 // TODO(leszeks): Add a debug-only check that the accumulator is
6100 // JSGeneratorObject::kThrow.
6101 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input).ReThrow();
6102
6103 // Resume with next.
6104 builder()->Bind(&resume_next);
6105 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
6106}
6107
6108void BytecodeGenerator::VisitAwait(Await* expr) {
6109 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6110 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
6111 BuildAwait(expr->position());
6112 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(expr,
6113 SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
6114}
6115
6116void BytecodeGenerator::VisitThrow(Throw* expr) {
6117 AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(expr, SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
6118 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->exception());
6119 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6120 builder()->Throw();
6121}
6122
6123void BytecodeGenerator::VisitPropertyLoad(Register obj, Property* property) {
6124 if (property->is_optional_chain_link()) {
6125 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(optional_chaining_null_labels_);
6126 int right_range =
6127 AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(property, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
6128 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(obj).JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(
6129 optional_chaining_null_labels_->New());
6130 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_range);
6131 }
6132
6133 AssignType property_kind = Property::GetAssignType(property);
6134
6135 switch (property_kind) {
6136 case NON_PROPERTY:
6137 UNREACHABLE();
6138 case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
6139 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6140 const AstRawString* name =
6141 property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
6142 BuildLoadNamedProperty(property->obj(), obj, name);
6143 break;
6144 }
6145 case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
6146 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
6147 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6148 BuildLoadKeyedProperty(obj, feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot());
6149 break;
6150 }
6151 case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY:
6152 VisitNamedSuperPropertyLoad(property, Register::invalid_value());
6153 break;
6154 case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY:
6155 VisitKeyedSuperPropertyLoad(property, Register::invalid_value());
6156 break;
6157 case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY: {
6158 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, obj);
6159 BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateGetterAccess,
6160 property);
6161 break;
6162 }
6163 case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
6164 case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
6165 Register key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
6166 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, obj);
6167 BuildPrivateGetterAccess(obj, key);
6168 break;
6169 }
6170 case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
6171 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, obj);
6172 // In the case of private methods, property->key() is the function to be
6173 // loaded (stored in a context slot), so load this directly.
6174 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
6175 break;
6176 }
6177 case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
6178 BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(property, obj);
6179 break;
6180 }
6181 }
6182}
6183
6184void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(Property* property,
6185 Register obj) {
6186 RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
6187 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6188
6189 Variable* private_name = property->key()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6190 builder()
6191 ->MoveRegister(obj, args[0])
6192 .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6193 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6194 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kGetPrivateMember, args);
6195}

6197void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateDebugDynamicSet(Property* property,
6198 Register obj,
6199 Register value) {
6200 RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
6201 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6202
6203 Variable* private_name = property->key()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6204 builder()
6205 ->MoveRegister(obj, args[0])
6206 .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6207 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6208 .MoveRegister(value, args[2])
6209 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kSetPrivateMember, args);
6210}

6213 Register accessor_pair) {

6216 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(1);
6217

6219 ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadPrivateGetter, accessor_pair)
6220 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(accessor)
6221 .MoveRegister(object, args[0])
6222 .CallProperty(accessor, args,
6223 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6224}

6232
6233 builder()
6234 ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadPrivateSetter, accessor_pair)
6235 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(accessor)
6236 .MoveRegister(object, args[0])
6237 .MoveRegister(value, args[1])
6238 .CallProperty(accessor, args,
6239 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6240}
6241
6242void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateMethodIn(Variable* private_name,
6243 Expression* object_expression) {
6244 DCHECK(IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(private_name->mode()));
6245 ClassScope* scope = private_name->scope()->AsClassScope();
6246 if (private_name->is_static()) {
6247 // For static private methods, "#privatemethod in ..." only returns true for
6248 // the class constructor.
6249 if (scope->class_variable() == nullptr) {
6250 // Can only happen via the debugger. See comment in
6251 // BuildPrivateBrandCheck.
6252 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6253 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6254 builder()
6255 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(
6256 MessageTemplate::
6257 kInvalidUnusedPrivateStaticMethodAccessedByDebugger))
6258 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6259 .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6260 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6261 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewError, args)
6262 .Throw();
6263 } else {
6264 VisitForAccumulatorValue(object_expression);
6265 Register object = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6266 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(object);
6267
6268 BytecodeLabel is_object;
6269 builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(&is_object);
6270
6271 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6272 builder()
6273 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2])
6274 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(MessageTemplate::kInvalidInOperatorUse))
6275 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6276 .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6277 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6278 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewTypeError, args)
6279 .Throw();
6280
6281 builder()->Bind(&is_object);
6282 BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->class_variable(),
6283 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6284 builder()->CompareReference(object);
6285 }
6286 } else {
6287 BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->brand(),
6288 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6289 Register brand = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6290 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand);
6291
6292 VisitForAccumulatorValue(object_expression);
6293 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(object_expression);
6294
6295 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedHasICSlot();
6296 builder()->CompareOperation(Token::kIn, brand, feedback_index(slot));
6297 execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
6298 }
6299}
6300
6301void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateBrandCheck(Property* property,
6302 Register object) {
6303 Variable* private_name = property->key()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6304 DCHECK(IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(private_name->mode()));
6305 ClassScope* scope = private_name->scope()->AsClassScope();
6306 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6307 if (private_name->is_static()) {
6308 // For static private methods, the only valid receiver is the class.
6309 // Load the class constructor.
6310 if (scope->class_variable() == nullptr) {
6311 // If the static private method has not been used used in source
6312 // code (either explicitly or through the presence of eval), but is
6313 // accessed by the debugger at runtime, reference to the class variable
6314 // is not available since it was not be context-allocated. Therefore we
6315 // can't build a branch check, and throw an ReferenceError as if the
6316 // method was optimized away.
6317 // TODO(joyee): get a reference to the class constructor through
6318 // something other than scope->class_variable() in this scenario.
6319 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6320 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6321 builder()
6322 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(
6323 MessageTemplate::
6324 kInvalidUnusedPrivateStaticMethodAccessedByDebugger))
6325 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6326 .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6327 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6328 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewError, args)
6329 .Throw();
6330 } else {
6331 BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->class_variable(),
6332 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6333 BytecodeLabel return_check;
6334 builder()->CompareReference(object).JumpIfTrue(
6335 ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &return_check);
6336 const AstRawString* name = scope->class_variable()->raw_name();
6337 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6338 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6339 builder()
6340 ->LoadLiteral(
6341 Smi::FromEnum(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateBrandStatic))
6342 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6343 .LoadLiteral(name)
6344 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6345 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewTypeError, args)
6346 .Throw();
6347 builder()->Bind(&return_check);
6348 }
6349 } else {
6350 BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->brand(),
6351 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6352 builder()->LoadKeyedProperty(
6353 object, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot()));
6354 }
6355}

6357void BytecodeGenerator::VisitPropertyLoadForRegister(Register obj,
6358 Property* expr,
6359 Register destination) {
6360 ValueResultScope result_scope(this);
6361 VisitPropertyLoad(obj, expr);
6362 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
6363}

6365void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNamedSuperPropertyLoad(Property* property,
6366 Register opt_receiver_out) {
6367 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6368 if (v8_flags.super_ic) {
6369 Register receiver = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6370 BuildThisVariableLoad();
6371 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(receiver);
6372 BuildVariableLoad(
6373 property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
6374 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6375 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6376 auto name = property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
6377 FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadSuperICSlot(name);
6378 builder()->LoadNamedPropertyFromSuper(receiver, name, feedback_index(slot));
6379 if (opt_receiver_out.is_valid()) {
6380 builder()->MoveRegister(receiver, opt_receiver_out);
6381 }
6382 } else {
6383 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6384 BuildThisVariableLoad();
6385 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]);
6386 BuildVariableLoad(
6387 property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
6388 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6389 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]);
6390 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6391 builder()
6392 ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
6393 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2])
6394 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadFromSuper, args);
6395
6396 if (opt_receiver_out.is_valid()) {
6397 builder()->MoveRegister(args[0], opt_receiver_out);
6398 }
6399 }
6400}
6401
6402void BytecodeGenerator::VisitKeyedSuperPropertyLoad(Property* property,
6403 Register opt_receiver_out) {
6404 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6405 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6406 BuildThisVariableLoad();
6407 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]);
6408 BuildVariableLoad(
6409 property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
6410 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6411 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]);
6412 VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), args[2]);
6413
6414 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6415 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadKeyedFromSuper, args);
6416
6417 if (opt_receiver_out.is_valid()) {
6418 builder()->MoveRegister(args[0], opt_receiver_out);
6419 }
6420}
