6422template <typename ExpressionFunc>
6423void BytecodeGenerator::BuildOptionalChain(ExpressionFunc expression_func) {
6424 BytecodeLabel done;
6425 OptionalChainNullLabelScope label_scope(this);
6426 // Use the same scope for the entire optional chain, as links earlier in the
6427 // chain dominate later links, linearly.
6428 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
6429 expression_func();
6430 builder()->Jump(&done);
6431 label_scope.labels()->Bind(builder());
6432 builder()->LoadUndefined();
6433 builder()->Bind(&done);
6434}
6435
6436void BytecodeGenerator::VisitOptionalChain(OptionalChain* expr) {
6437 BuildOptionalChain([&]() { VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression()); });
6438}
6439
6440void BytecodeGenerator::VisitProperty(Property* expr) {
6441 AssignType property_kind = Property::GetAssignType(expr);
6442 if (property_kind != NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY &&
6443 property_kind != KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY) {
6444 Register obj = VisitForRegisterValue(expr->obj());
6445 VisitPropertyLoad(obj, expr);
6446 } else {
6447 VisitPropertyLoad(Register::invalid_value(), expr);
6448 }
6449}
6450
6451void BytecodeGenerator::VisitArguments(const ZonePtrList<Expression>* args,
6452 RegisterList* arg_regs) {
6453 // Visit arguments.
6454 builder()->UpdateMaxArguments(static_cast<uint16_t>(args->length()));
6455 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args->length()); i++) {
6456 VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(args->at(i), arg_regs);
6457 }
6458}
6459
6460void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCall(Call* expr) {
6461 Expression* callee_expr = expr->expression();
6462 Call::CallType call_type = expr->GetCallType();
6463
6464 if (call_type == Call::SUPER_CALL) {
6465 return VisitCallSuper(expr);
6466 }
6467
6468 // We compile the call differently depending on the presence of spreads and
6469 // their positions.
6470 //
6471 // If there is only one spread and it is the final argument, there is a
6472 // special CallWithSpread bytecode.
6473 //
6474 // If there is a non-final spread, we rewrite calls like
6475 // callee(1, ...x, 2)
6476 // to
6477 // %reflect_apply(callee, receiver, [1, ...x, 2])
6478 const Call::SpreadPosition spread_position = expr->spread_position();
6479
6480 // Grow the args list as we visit receiver / arguments to avoid allocating all
6481 // the registers up-front. Otherwise these registers are unavailable during
6482 // receiver / argument visiting and we can end up with memory leaks due to
6483 // registers keeping objects alive.
6484 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
6485
6486 // The callee is the first register in args for ease of calling %reflect_apply
6487 // if we have a non-final spread. For all other cases it is popped from args
6488 // before emitting the call below.
6489 Register callee = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6490
6491 bool implicit_undefined_receiver = false;
6492
6493 // TODO(petermarshall): We have a lot of call bytecodes that are very similar,
6494 // see if we can reduce the number by adding a separate argument which
6495 // specifies the call type (e.g., property, spread, tailcall, etc.).
6496
6497 // Prepare the callee and the receiver to the function call. This depends on
6498 // the semantics of the underlying call type.
6499 switch (call_type) {
6500 case Call::NAMED_PROPERTY_CALL:
6501 case Call::KEYED_PROPERTY_CALL:
6502 case Call::PRIVATE_CALL: {
6503 Property* property = callee_expr->AsProperty();
6504 VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(property->obj(), &args);
6505 VisitPropertyLoadForRegister(args.last_register(), property, callee);
6506 break;
6507 }
6508 case Call::GLOBAL_CALL: {
6509 // Receiver is undefined for global calls.
6510 if (spread_position == Call::kNoSpread) {
6511 implicit_undefined_receiver = true;
6512 } else {
6513 // TODO(leszeks): There's no special bytecode for tail calls or spread
6514 // calls with an undefined receiver, so just push undefined ourselves.
6515 BuildPushUndefinedIntoRegisterList(&args);
6516 }
6517 // Load callee as a global variable.
6518 VariableProxy* proxy = callee_expr->AsVariableProxy();
6519 BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(proxy->var(),
6520 proxy->hole_check_mode());
6521 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6522 break;
6523 }
6524 case Call::WITH_CALL: {
6525 Register receiver = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6526 DCHECK(callee_expr->AsVariableProxy()->var()->IsLookupSlot());
6527 {
6528 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6529 Register name = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6530
6531 // Call %LoadLookupSlotForCall to get the callee and receiver.
6532 RegisterList result_pair = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6533 Variable* variable = callee_expr->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6534 builder()
6535 ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
6536 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name)
6537 .CallRuntimeForPair(Runtime::kLoadLookupSlotForCall, name,
6538 result_pair)
6539 .MoveRegister(result_pair[0], callee)
6540 .MoveRegister(result_pair[1], receiver);
6541 }
6542 break;
6543 }
6544 case Call::OTHER_CALL: {
6545 // Receiver is undefined for other calls.
6546 if (spread_position == Call::kNoSpread) {
6547 implicit_undefined_receiver = true;
6548 } else {
6549 // TODO(leszeks): There's no special bytecode for tail calls or spread
6550 // calls with an undefined receiver, so just push undefined ourselves.
6551 BuildPushUndefinedIntoRegisterList(&args);
6552 }
6553 VisitForRegisterValue(callee_expr, callee);
6554 break;
6555 }
6556 case Call::NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY_CALL: {
6557 Register receiver = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6558 Property* property = callee_expr->AsProperty();
6559 VisitNamedSuperPropertyLoad(property, receiver);
6560 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6561 break;
6562 }
6563 case Call::KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY_CALL: {
6564 Register receiver = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6565 Property* property = callee_expr->AsProperty();
6566 VisitKeyedSuperPropertyLoad(property, receiver);
6567 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6568 break;
6569 }
6570 case Call::NAMED_OPTIONAL_CHAIN_PROPERTY_CALL:
6571 case Call::KEYED_OPTIONAL_CHAIN_PROPERTY_CALL:
6572 case Call::PRIVATE_OPTIONAL_CHAIN_CALL: {
6573 OptionalChain* chain = callee_expr->AsOptionalChain();
6574 Property* property = chain->expression()->AsProperty();
6575 BuildOptionalChain([&]() {
6576 VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(property->obj(), &args);
6577 VisitPropertyLoad(args.last_register(), property);
6578 });
6579 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6580 break;
6581 }
6582 case Call::SUPER_CALL:
6583 UNREACHABLE();
6584 }
6585
6586 if (expr->is_optional_chain_link()) {
6587 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(optional_chaining_null_labels_);
6588 int right_range =
6589 AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(expr, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
6590 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(callee).JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(
6591 optional_chaining_null_labels_->New());
6592 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_range);
6593 }
6594
6595 int receiver_arg_count = -1;
6596 if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6597 // If we're building %reflect_apply, build the array literal and put it in
6598 // the 3rd argument.
6599 DCHECK(!implicit_undefined_receiver);
6600 DCHECK_EQ(args.register_count(), 2);
6601 BuildCreateArrayLiteral(expr->arguments(), nullptr);
6602 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
6603 register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args));
6604 } else {
6605 // If we're not building %reflect_apply and don't need to build an array
6606 // literal, pop the callee and evaluate all arguments to the function call
6607 // and store in sequential args registers.
6608 args = args.PopLeft();
6609 VisitArguments(expr->arguments(), &args);
6610 receiver_arg_count = implicit_undefined_receiver ? 0 : 1;
6611 CHECK_EQ(receiver_arg_count + expr->arguments()->length(),
6612 args.register_count());
6613 }
6614
6615 // Resolve callee for a potential direct eval call. This block will mutate the
6616 // callee value.
6617 if (expr->is_possibly_eval() && expr->arguments()->length() > 0) {
6618 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6619 RegisterList runtime_call_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(6);
6620 // Set up arguments for ResolvePossiblyDirectEval by copying callee, source
6621 // strings and function closure, and loading language and
6622 // position.
6623
6624 // Move the first arg.
6625 if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6626 int feedback_slot_index =
6627 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot());
6628 Register args_array = args[2];
6629 builder()
6630 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(0))
6631 .LoadKeyedProperty(args_array, feedback_slot_index)
6632 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[1]);
6633 } else {
6634 // FIXME(v8:5690): Support final spreads for eval.
6635 DCHECK_GE(receiver_arg_count, 0);
6636 builder()->MoveRegister(args[receiver_arg_count], runtime_call_args[1]);
6637 }
6638 builder()
6639 ->MoveRegister(callee, runtime_call_args[0])
6640 .MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), runtime_call_args[2])
6641 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(language_mode()))
6642 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[3])
6643 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(expr->eval_scope_info_index()))
6644 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[4])
6645 .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(expr->position()))
6646 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[5]);
6647
6648 // Call ResolvePossiblyDirectEval and modify the callee.
6649 builder()
6650 ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kResolvePossiblyDirectEval, runtime_call_args)
6651 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6652 }
6653
6654 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6655
6656 if (spread_position == Call::kHasFinalSpread) {
6657 DCHECK(!implicit_undefined_receiver);
6658 builder()->CallWithSpread(callee, args,
6659 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6660 } else if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6661 builder()->CallJSRuntime(Context::REFLECT_APPLY_INDEX, args);
6662 } else if (call_type == Call::NAMED_PROPERTY_CALL ||
6663 call_type == Call::KEYED_PROPERTY_CALL) {
6664 DCHECK(!implicit_undefined_receiver);
6665 builder()->CallProperty(callee, args,
6666 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6667 } else if (implicit_undefined_receiver) {
6668 builder()->CallUndefinedReceiver(
6669 callee, args, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6670 } else {
6671 builder()->CallAnyReceiver(
6672 callee, args, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6673 }
6674}
6675
6676void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCallSuper(Call* expr) {
6677 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6678 SuperCallReference* super = expr->expression()->AsSuperCallReference();
6679 const ZonePtrList<Expression>* args = expr->arguments();
6680
6681 // We compile the super call differently depending on the presence of spreads
6682 // and their positions.
6683 //
6684 // If there is only one spread and it is the final argument, there is a
6685 // special ConstructWithSpread bytecode.
6686 //
6687 // It there is a non-final spread, we rewrite something like
6688 // super(1, ...x, 2)
6689 // to
6690 // %reflect_construct(constructor, [1, ...x, 2], new_target)
6691 //
6692 // That is, we implement (non-last-arg) spreads in super calls via our
6693 // mechanism for spreads in array literals.
6694 const Call::SpreadPosition spread_position = expr->spread_position();
6695
6696 // Prepare the constructor to the super call.
6697 Register this_function = VisitForRegisterValue(super->this_function_var());
6698 // This register will initially hold the constructor, then afterward it will
6699 // hold the instance -- the lifetimes of the two don't need to overlap, and
6700 // this way FindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct can choose to write either
6701 // the instance or the constructor into the same register.
6702 Register constructor_then_instance = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6703
6704 BytecodeLabel super_ctor_call_done;
6705
6706 if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6707 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6708 RegisterList construct_args(constructor_then_instance);
6709 const Register& constructor = constructor_then_instance;
6710
6711 // Generate the array containing all arguments.
6712 BuildCreateArrayLiteral(args, nullptr);
6713 Register args_array =
6714 register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&construct_args);
6715 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args_array);
6716
6717 Register new_target =
6718 register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&construct_args);
6719 VisitForRegisterValue(super->new_target_var(), new_target);
6720
6721 BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6722 &super_ctor_call_done);
6723
6724 // Now pass that array to %reflect_construct.
6725 builder()->CallJSRuntime(Context::REFLECT_CONSTRUCT_INDEX, construct_args);
6726 } else {
6727 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6728 RegisterList args_regs = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
6729 VisitArguments(args, &args_regs);
6730
6731 // The new target is loaded into the new_target register from the
6732 // {new.target} variable.
6733 Register new_target = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6734 VisitForRegisterValue(super->new_target_var(), new_target);
6735
6736 const Register& constructor = constructor_then_instance;
6737 BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6738 &super_ctor_call_done);
6739
6740 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(new_target);
6741 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6742
6743 int feedback_slot_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
6744
6745 if (spread_position == Call::kHasFinalSpread) {
6746 builder()->ConstructWithSpread(constructor, args_regs,
6747 feedback_slot_index);
6748 } else {
6749 DCHECK_EQ(spread_position, Call::kNoSpread);
6750 // Call construct.
6751 // TODO(turbofan): For now we do gather feedback on super constructor
6752 // calls, utilizing the existing machinery to inline the actual call
6753 // target and the JSCreate for the implicit receiver allocation. This
6754 // is not an ideal solution for super constructor calls, but it gets
6755 // the job done for now. In the long run we might want to revisit this
6756 // and come up with a better way.
6757 builder()->Construct(constructor, args_regs, feedback_slot_index);
6758 }
6759 }
6760
6761 // From here onwards, constructor_then_instance will hold the instance.
6762 const Register& instance = constructor_then_instance;
6763 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(instance);
6764 builder()->Bind(&super_ctor_call_done);
6765
6766 BuildInstanceInitializationAfterSuperCall(this_function, instance);
6767 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(instance);
6768}
6769
6770void BytecodeGenerator::BuildInstanceInitializationAfterSuperCall(
6771 Register this_function, Register instance) {
6772 // Explicit calls to the super constructor using super() perform an
6773 // implicit binding assignment to the 'this' variable.
6774 //
6775 // Default constructors don't need have to do the assignment because
6776 // 'this' isn't accessed in default constructors.
6777 if (!IsDefaultConstructor(info()->literal()->kind())) {
6778 Variable* var = closure_scope()->GetReceiverScope()->receiver();
6779 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(instance);
6780 BuildVariableAssignment(var, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kRequired);
6781 }
6782
6783 // The constructor scope always needs ScopeInfo, so we are certain that
6784 // the first constructor scope found in the outer scope chain is the
6785 // scope that we are looking for for this super() call.
6786 // Note that this doesn't necessarily mean that the constructor needs
6787 // a context, if it doesn't this would get handled specially in
6788 // BuildPrivateBrandInitialization().
6789 DeclarationScope* constructor_scope = info()->scope()->GetConstructorScope();
6790
6791 // We can rely on the class_scope_has_private_brand bit to tell if the
6792 // constructor needs private brand initialization, and if that's
6793 // the case we are certain that its outer class scope requires a context to
6794 // keep the brand variable, so we can just get the brand variable
6795 // from the outer scope.
6796 if (constructor_scope->class_scope_has_private_brand()) {
6797 DCHECK(constructor_scope->outer_scope()->is_class_scope());
6798 ClassScope* class_scope = constructor_scope->outer_scope()->AsClassScope();
6799 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(class_scope->brand());
6800 Variable* brand = class_scope->brand();
6801 BuildPrivateBrandInitialization(instance, brand);
6802 }
6803
6804 // The derived constructor has the correct bit set always, so we
6805 // don't emit code to load and call the initializer if not
6806 // required.
6807 //
6808 // For the arrow function or eval case, we always emit code to load
6809 // and call the initializer.
6810 //
6811 // TODO(gsathya): In the future, we could tag nested arrow functions
6812 // or eval with the correct bit so that we do the load conditionally
6813 // if required.
6814 if (info()->literal()->requires_instance_members_initializer() ||
6815 !IsDerivedConstructor(info()->literal()->kind())) {
6816 BuildInstanceMemberInitialization(this_function, instance);
6817 }
6818}
6819
6820void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(
6821 Register this_function, Register new_target, Register constructor,
6822 BytecodeLabel* super_ctor_call_done) {
6823 bool omit_super_ctor = v8_flags.omit_default_ctors &&
6824 IsDerivedConstructor(info()->literal()->kind());
6825
6826 if (omit_super_ctor) {
6827 BuildSuperCallOptimization(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6828 super_ctor_call_done);
6829 } else {
6830 builder()
6831 ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(this_function)
6832 .GetSuperConstructor(constructor);
6833 }
6834
6835 // Check if the constructor is in fact a constructor.
6836 builder()->ThrowIfNotSuperConstructor(constructor);
6837}
6838
6839void BytecodeGenerator::BuildSuperCallOptimization(
6840 Register this_function, Register new_target,
6841 Register constructor_then_instance, BytecodeLabel* super_ctor_call_done) {
6842 DCHECK(v8_flags.omit_default_ctors);
6843 RegisterList output = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6844 builder()->FindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(this_function, new_target,
6845 output);
6846 builder()->MoveRegister(output[1], constructor_then_instance);
6847 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output[0]).JumpIfTrue(
6848 ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, super_ctor_call_done);
6849}
6850
6851void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCallNew(CallNew* expr) {
6852 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
6853
6854 // Load the constructor. It's in the first register in args for ease of
6855 // calling %reflect_construct if we have a non-final spread. For all other
6856 // cases it is popped before emitting the construct below.
6857 VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(expr->expression(), &args);
6858
6859 // We compile the new differently depending on the presence of spreads and
6860 // their positions.
6861 //
6862 // If there is only one spread and it is the final argument, there is a
6863 // special ConstructWithSpread bytecode.
6864 //
6865 // If there is a non-final spread, we rewrite calls like
6866 // new ctor(1, ...x, 2)
6867 // to
6868 // %reflect_construct(ctor, [1, ...x, 2])
6869 const CallNew::SpreadPosition spread_position = expr->spread_position();
6870
6871 if (spread_position == CallNew::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6872 BuildCreateArrayLiteral(expr->arguments(), nullptr);
6873 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6874 builder()
6875 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
6876 register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args))
6877 .CallJSRuntime(Context::REFLECT_CONSTRUCT_INDEX, args);
6878 return;
6879 }
6880
6881 Register constructor = args.first_register();
6882 args = args.PopLeft();
6883 VisitArguments(expr->arguments(), &args);
6884
6885 // The accumulator holds new target which is the same as the
6886 // constructor for CallNew.
6887 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6888 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(constructor);
6889
6890 int feedback_slot_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
6891 if (spread_position == CallNew::kHasFinalSpread) {
6892 builder()->ConstructWithSpread(constructor, args, feedback_slot_index);
6893 } else {
6894 DCHECK_EQ(spread_position, CallNew::kNoSpread);
6895 builder()->Construct(constructor, args, feedback_slot_index);
6896 }
6897}
6898
6899void BytecodeGenerator::VisitSuperCallForwardArgs(SuperCallForwardArgs* expr) {
6900 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6901
6902 SuperCallReference* super = expr->expression();
6903 Register this_function = VisitForRegisterValue(super->this_function_var());
6904 Register new_target = VisitForRegisterValue(super->new_target_var());
6905
6906 // This register initially holds the constructor, then the instance.
6907 Register constructor_then_instance = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6908
6909 BytecodeLabel super_ctor_call_done;
6910
6911 {
6912 const Register& constructor = constructor_then_instance;
6913 BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6914 &super_ctor_call_done);
6915
6916 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(new_target);
6917 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6918 int feedback_slot_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
6919
6920 builder()->ConstructForwardAllArgs(constructor, feedback_slot_index);
6921 }
6922
6923 // From here onwards, constructor_then_instance holds the instance.
6924 const Register& instance = constructor_then_instance;
6925 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(instance);
6926 builder()->Bind(&super_ctor_call_done);
6927
6928 BuildInstanceInitializationAfterSuperCall(this_function, instance);
6929 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(instance);
6930}
6931
6932void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCallRuntime(CallRuntime* expr) {
6933 // Evaluate all arguments to the runtime call.
6934 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
6935 VisitArguments(expr->arguments(), &args);
6936 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = expr->function()->function_id;
6937 builder()->CallRuntime(function_id, args);
6938}
6939
6940void BytecodeGenerator::VisitVoid(UnaryOperation* expr) {
6941 VisitForEffect(expr->expression());
6942 builder()->LoadUndefined();
6943}
6944
6945void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForTypeOfValue(Expression* expr) {
6946 if (expr->IsVariableProxy()) {
6947 // Typeof does not throw a reference error on global variables, hence we
6948 // perform a non-contextual load in case the operand is a variable proxy.
6949 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->AsVariableProxy();
6950 BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(proxy->var(), proxy->hole_check_mode(),
6951 TypeofMode::kInside);
6952 } else {
6953 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
6954 }
6955}
6956
6957void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTypeOf(UnaryOperation* expr) {
6958 VisitForTypeOfValue(expr->expression());
6959 builder()->TypeOf(feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddTypeOfSlot()));
6960 execution_result()->SetResultIsInternalizedString();
6961}
6962
6963void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNot(UnaryOperation* expr) {
6964 if (execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
6965 VisitForEffect(expr->expression());
6966 } else if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
6967 // No actual logical negation happening, we just swap the control flow, by
6968 // swapping the target labels and the fallthrough branch, and visit in the
6969 // same test result context.
6970 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
6971 test_result->InvertControlFlow();
6972 VisitInSameTestExecutionScope(expr->expression());
6973 } else {
6974 UnaryOperation* unary_op = expr->expression()->AsUnaryOperation();
6975 if (unary_op && unary_op->op() == Token::kNot) {
6976 // Shortcut repeated nots, to capture the `!!foo` pattern for converting
6977 // expressions to booleans.
6978 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(unary_op->expression());
6979 builder()->ToBoolean(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint));
6980 } else {
6981 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
6982 builder()->LogicalNot(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint));
6983 }
6984 // Always returns a boolean value.
6985 execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
6986 }
6987}
6988
6989void BytecodeGenerator::VisitUnaryOperation(UnaryOperation* expr) {
6990 switch (expr->op()) {
6991 case Token::kNot:
6992 VisitNot(expr);
6993 break;
6994 case Token::kTypeOf:
6995 VisitTypeOf(expr);
6996 break;
6997 case Token::kVoid:
6998 VisitVoid(expr);
6999 break;
7000 case Token::kDelete:
7001 VisitDelete(expr);
7002 break;
7003 case Token::kAdd:
7004 case Token::kSub:
7005 case Token::kBitNot:
7006 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
7007 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7008 builder()->UnaryOperation(
7009 expr->op(), feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
7010 break;
7011 default:
7012 UNREACHABLE();
7013 }
7014}
7015
7016void BytecodeGenerator::VisitDelete(UnaryOperation* unary) {
7017 Expression* expr = unary->expression();
7018 if (expr->IsProperty()) {
7019 // Delete of an object property is allowed both in sloppy
7020 // and strict modes.
7021 Property* property = expr->AsProperty();
7022 DCHECK(!property->IsPrivateReference());
7023 if (property->IsSuperAccess()) {
7024 // Delete of super access is not allowed.
7025 VisitForEffect(property->key());
7026 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowUnsupportedSuperError);
7027 } else {
7028 Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7029 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7030 builder()->Delete(object, language_mode());
7031 }
7032 } else if (expr->IsOptionalChain()) {
7033 Expression* expr_inner = expr->AsOptionalChain()->expression();
7034 if (expr_inner->IsProperty()) {
7035 Property* property = expr_inner->AsProperty();
7036 DCHECK(!property->IsPrivateReference());
7037 BytecodeLabel done;
7038 OptionalChainNullLabelScope label_scope(this);
7039 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->obj());
7040 if (property->is_optional_chain_link()) {
7041 int right_range = AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(
7042 property, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
7043 builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(label_scope.labels()->New());
7044 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_range);
7045 }
7046 Register object = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7047 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(object);
7048 if (property->is_optional_chain_link()) {
7049 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7050 } else {
7051 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7052 }
7053 builder()->Delete(object, language_mode());
7054 builder()->Jump(&done);
7055 label_scope.labels()->Bind(builder());
7056 builder()->LoadTrue();
7057 builder()->Bind(&done);
7058 } else {
7059 VisitForEffect(expr);
7060 builder()->LoadTrue();
7061 }
7062 } else if (expr->IsVariableProxy() &&
7063 !expr->AsVariableProxy()->is_new_target()) {
7064 // Delete of an unqualified identifier is allowed in sloppy mode but is
7065 // not allowed in strict mode.
7066 DCHECK(is_sloppy(language_mode()));
7067 Variable* variable = expr->AsVariableProxy()->var();
7068 switch (variable->location()) {
7069 case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
7070 case VariableLocation::LOCAL:
7071 case VariableLocation::CONTEXT:
7072 case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL: {
7073 // Deleting local var/let/const, context variables, and arguments
7074 // does not have any effect.
7075 builder()->LoadFalse();
7076 break;
7077 }
7078 case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
7079 // TODO(adamk): Falling through to the runtime results in correct
7080 // behavior, but does unnecessary context-walking (since scope
7081 // analysis has already proven that the variable doesn't exist in
7082 // any non-global scope). Consider adding a DeleteGlobal bytecode
7083 // that knows how to deal with ScriptContexts as well as global
7084 // object properties.
7085 case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
7086 Register name_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7087 builder()
7088 ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
7089 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name_reg)
7090 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kDeleteLookupSlot, name_reg);
7091 break;
7092 }
7093 case VariableLocation::MODULE:
7094 // Modules are always in strict mode and unqualified identifers are not
7095 // allowed in strict mode.
7096 UNREACHABLE();
7097 }
7098 } else {
7099 // Delete of an unresolvable reference, new.target, and this returns true.
7100 VisitForEffect(expr);
7101 builder()->LoadTrue();
7102 }
7103}
7104
7105void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCountOperation(CountOperation* expr) {
7106 DCHECK(expr->expression()->IsValidReferenceExpression());
7107
7108 // Left-hand side can only be a property, a global or a variable slot.
7109 Property* property = expr->expression()->AsProperty();
7110 AssignType assign_type = Property::GetAssignType(property);
7111
7112 bool is_postfix = expr->is_postfix() && !execution_result()->IsEffect();
7113
7114 // Evaluate LHS expression and get old value.
7115 Register object, key, old_value;
7116 RegisterList super_property_args;
7117 const AstRawString* name;
7118 switch (assign_type) {
7119 case NON_PROPERTY: {
7120 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->expression()->AsVariableProxy();
7121 BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(proxy->var(),
7122 proxy->hole_check_mode());
7123 break;
7124 }
7125 case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
7126 object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7127 name = property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
7128 builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
7129 object, name,
7130 feedback_index(GetCachedLoadICSlot(property->obj(), name)));
7131 break;
7132 }
7133 case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
7134 object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7135 // Use visit for accumulator here since we need the key in the accumulator
7136 // for the LoadKeyedProperty.
7137 key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7138 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7139 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key).LoadKeyedProperty(
7140 object, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot()));
7141 break;
7142 }
7143 case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7144 super_property_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
7145 RegisterList load_super_args = super_property_args.Truncate(3);
7146 BuildThisVariableLoad();
7147 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[0]);
7148 BuildVariableLoad(
7149 property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
7150 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
7151 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[1]);
7152 builder()
7153 ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
7154 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[2])
7155 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadFromSuper, load_super_args);
7156 break;
7157 }
7158 case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7159 super_property_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
7160 RegisterList load_super_args = super_property_args.Truncate(3);
7161 BuildThisVariableLoad();
7162 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[0]);
7163 BuildVariableLoad(
7164 property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
7165 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
7166 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[1]);
7167 VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), load_super_args[2]);
7168 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadKeyedFromSuper, load_super_args);
7169 break;
7170 }
7171 case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
7172 object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7173 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7174 BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMethodWrite,
7175 property);
7176 return;
7177 }
7178 case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY: {
7179 object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7180 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7181 BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateSetterAccess,
7182 property);
7183 return;
7184 }
7185 case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY: {
7186 object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7187 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7188 BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateGetterAccess,
7189 property);
7190 return;
7191 }
7192 case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
7193 object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7194 key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
7195 BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7196 BuildPrivateGetterAccess(object, key);
7197 break;
7198 }
7199 case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
7200 object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7201 BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(property, object);
7202 break;
7203 }
7204 }
7205
7206 // Save result for postfix expressions.
7207 FeedbackSlot count_slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
7208 if (is_postfix) {
7209 old_value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7210 // Convert old value into a number before saving it.
7211 // TODO(ignition): Think about adding proper PostInc/PostDec bytecodes
7212 // instead of this ToNumeric + Inc/Dec dance.
7213 builder()
7214 ->ToNumeric(feedback_index(count_slot))
7215 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(old_value);
7216 }
7217
7218 // Perform +1/-1 operation.
7219 builder()->UnaryOperation(expr->op(), feedback_index(count_slot));
7220
7221 // Store the value.
7222 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7223 switch (assign_type) {
7224 case NON_PROPERTY: {
7225 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->expression()->AsVariableProxy();
7226 BuildVariableAssignment(proxy->var(), expr->op(),
7227 proxy->hole_check_mode());
7228 break;
7229 }
7230 case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
7231 FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedStoreICSlot(property->obj(), name);
7232 Register value;
7233 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7234 value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7235 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7236 }
7237 builder()->SetNamedProperty(object, name, feedback_index(slot),
7238 language_mode());
7239 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7240 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
7241 }
7242 break;
7243 }
7244 case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
7245 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedStoreICSlot(language_mode());
7246 Register value;
7247 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7248 value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7249 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7250 }
7251 builder()->SetKeyedProperty(object, key, feedback_index(slot),
7252 language_mode());
7253 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7254 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
7255 }
7256 break;
7257 }
7258 case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7259 builder()
7260 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[3])
7261 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreToSuper, super_property_args);
7262 break;
7263 }
7264 case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7265 builder()
7266 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[3])
7267 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreKeyedToSuper, super_property_args);
7268 break;
7269 }
7270 case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY:
7271 case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
7272 case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
7273 UNREACHABLE();
7274 }
7275 case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
7276 Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7277 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7278 BuildPrivateSetterAccess(object, key, value);
7279 if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7280 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
7281 }
7282 break;
7283 }
7284 case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
7285 Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7286 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7287 BuildPrivateDebugDynamicSet(property, object, value);
7288 break;
7289 }
7290 }
7291
7292 // Restore old value for postfix expressions.
7293 if (is_postfix) {
7294 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(old_value);
7295 }
7296}
7297
7298void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBinaryOperation(BinaryOperation* binop) {
7299 switch (binop->op()) {
7300 case Token::kComma:
7301 VisitCommaExpression(binop);
7302 break;
7303 case Token::kOr:
7304 VisitLogicalOrExpression(binop);
7305 break;
7306 case Token::kAnd:
7307 VisitLogicalAndExpression(binop);
7308 break;
7309 case Token::kNullish:
7310 VisitNullishExpression(binop);
7311 break;
7312 default:
7313 VisitArithmeticExpression(binop);
7314 break;
7315 }
7316}
7317
7318void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryOperation(NaryOperation* expr) {
7319 switch (expr->op()) {
7320 case Token::kComma:
7321 VisitNaryCommaExpression(expr);
7322 break;
7323 case Token::kOr:
7324 VisitNaryLogicalOrExpression(expr);
7325 break;
7326 case Token::kAnd:
7327 VisitNaryLogicalAndExpression(expr);
7328 break;
7329 case Token::kNullish:
7330 VisitNaryNullishExpression(expr);
7331 break;
7332 default:
7333 VisitNaryArithmeticExpression(expr);
7334 break;
7335 }
7336}
7337
7338void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLiteralCompareNil(
7339 Token::Value op, BytecodeArrayBuilder::NilValue nil) {
7340 if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
7341 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7342 switch (test_result->fallthrough()) {
7343 case TestFallthrough::kThen:
7344 builder()->JumpIfNotNil(test_result->NewElseLabel(), op, nil);
7345 break;
7346 case TestFallthrough::kElse:
7347 builder()->JumpIfNil(test_result->NewThenLabel(), op, nil);
7348 break;
7349 case TestFallthrough::kNone:
7350 builder()
7351 ->JumpIfNil(test_result->NewThenLabel(), op, nil)
7352 .Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
7353 }
7354 test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
7355 } else {
7356 builder()->CompareNil(op, nil);
7357 }
7358}
7359
7360void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLiteralStrictCompareBoolean(Literal* literal) {
7361 DCHECK(literal->IsBooleanLiteral());
7362 Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7363 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result);
7364 builder()->LoadBoolean(literal->AsBooleanLiteral());
7365 builder()->CompareReference(result);
7366}
7367
7368bool BytecodeGenerator::IsLocalVariableWithInternalizedStringHint(
7369 Expression* expr) {
7370 VariableProxy* proxy = expr->AsVariableProxy();
7371 return proxy != nullptr && proxy->is_resolved() &&
7372 proxy->var()->IsStackLocal() &&
7373 GetTypeHintForLocalVariable(proxy->var()) ==
7374 TypeHint::kInternalizedString;
7375}
7376
7377static bool IsTypeof(Expression* expr) {
7378 UnaryOperation* maybe_unary = expr->AsUnaryOperation();
7379 return maybe_unary != nullptr && maybe_unary->op() == Token::kTypeOf;
7380}
7381
7382static bool IsCharU(const AstRawString* str) {
7383 return str->length() == 1 && str->FirstCharacter() == 'u';
7384}
7385
7386static bool IsLiteralCompareTypeof(CompareOperation* expr,
7387 Expression** sub_expr,
7388 TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag* flag,
7389 const AstStringConstants* ast_constants) {
7390 if (IsTypeof(expr->left()) && expr->right()->IsStringLiteral()) {
7391 Literal* right_lit = expr->right()->AsLiteral();
7392
7393 if (Token::IsEqualityOp(expr->op())) {
7394 // typeof(x) === 'string'
7395 *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::GetFlagForLiteral(ast_constants, right_lit);
7396 } else if (expr->op() == Token::kGreaterThan &&
7397 IsCharU(right_lit->AsRawString())) {
7398 // typeof(x) > 'u'
7399 // Minifier may convert `typeof(x) === 'undefined'` to this form,
7400 // since `undefined` is the only valid value that is greater than 'u'.
7401 // Check the test OnlyUndefinedGreaterThanU in bytecodes-unittest.cc
7402 *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kUndefined;
7403 } else {
7404 return false;
7405 }
7406
7407 *sub_expr = expr->left()->AsUnaryOperation()->expression();
7408 return true;
7409 }
7410
7411 if (IsTypeof(expr->right()) && expr->left()->IsStringLiteral()) {
7412 Literal* left_lit = expr->left()->AsLiteral();
7413
7414 if (Token::IsEqualityOp(expr->op())) {
7415 // 'string' === typeof(x)
7416 *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::GetFlagForLiteral(ast_constants, left_lit);
7417 } else if (expr->op() == Token::kLessThan &&
7418 IsCharU(left_lit->AsRawString())) {
7419 // 'u' < typeof(x)
7420 *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kUndefined;
7421 } else {
7422 return false;
7423 }
7424
7425 *sub_expr = expr->right()->AsUnaryOperation()->expression();
7426 return true;
7427 }
7428
7429 return false;
7430}
7431
7432void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCompareOperation(CompareOperation* expr) {
7433 Expression* sub_expr;
7434 Literal* literal;
7435 TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag flag;
7436 if (IsLiteralCompareTypeof(expr, &sub_expr, &flag, ast_string_constants())) {
7437 // Emit a fast literal comparion for expressions of the form:
7438 // typeof(x) === 'string'.
7439 VisitForTypeOfValue(sub_expr);
7440 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7441 if (flag == TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kOther) {
7442 builder()->LoadFalse();
7443 } else {
7444 builder()->CompareTypeOf(flag);
7445 }
7446 } else if (expr->IsLiteralStrictCompareBoolean(&sub_expr, &literal)) {
7447 DCHECK(expr->op() == Token::kEqStrict);
7448 VisitForAccumulatorValue(sub_expr);
7449 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7450 BuildLiteralStrictCompareBoolean(literal);
7451 } else if (expr->IsLiteralCompareUndefined(&sub_expr)) {
7452 VisitForAccumulatorValue(sub_expr);
7453 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7454 BuildLiteralCompareNil(expr->op(), BytecodeArrayBuilder::kUndefinedValue);
7455 } else if (expr->IsLiteralCompareNull(&sub_expr)) {
7456 VisitForAccumulatorValue(sub_expr);
7457 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7458 BuildLiteralCompareNil(expr->op(), BytecodeArrayBuilder::kNullValue);
7459 } else if (expr->IsLiteralCompareEqualVariable(&sub_expr, &literal) &&
7460 IsLocalVariableWithInternalizedStringHint(sub_expr)) {
7461 builder()->LoadLiteral(literal->AsRawString());
7462 builder()->CompareReference(
7463 GetRegisterForLocalVariable(sub_expr->AsVariableProxy()->var()));
7464 } else {
7465 if (expr->op() == Token::kIn && expr->left()->IsPrivateName()) {
7466 Variable* var = expr->left()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
7467 if (IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(var->mode())) {
7468 BuildPrivateMethodIn(var, expr->right());
7469 return;
7470 }
7471 // For private fields, the code below does the right thing.
7472 }
7473
7474 Register lhs = VisitForRegisterValue(expr->left());
7475 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->right());
7476 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7477 FeedbackSlot slot;
7478 if (expr->op() == Token::kIn) {
7479 slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedHasICSlot();
7480 } else if (expr->op() == Token::kInstanceOf) {
7481 slot = feedback_spec()->AddInstanceOfSlot();
7482 } else {
7483 slot = feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot();
7484 }
7485 builder()->CompareOperation(expr->op(), lhs, feedback_index(slot));
7486 }
7487 // Always returns a boolean value.
7488 execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
7489}
7490
7491void BytecodeGenerator::VisitArithmeticExpression(BinaryOperation* expr) {
7492 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
7493 Expression* subexpr;
7494 Tagged<Smi> literal;
7495 if (expr->IsSmiLiteralOperation(&subexpr, &literal)) {
7496 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr);
7497 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7498 builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(expr->op(), literal,
7499 feedback_index(slot));
7500 if (expr->op() == Token::kAdd && IsStringTypeHint(type_hint)) {
7501 execution_result()->SetResultIsString();
7502 }
7503 } else {
7504 TypeHint lhs_type = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->left());
7505 Register lhs = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7506 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs);
7507 TypeHint rhs_type = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->right());
7508 if (expr->op() == Token::kAdd &&
7509 (IsStringTypeHint(lhs_type) || IsStringTypeHint(rhs_type))) {
7510 execution_result()->SetResultIsString();
7511 }
7512
7513 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7514 builder()->BinaryOperation(expr->op(), lhs, feedback_index(slot));
7515 }
7516}
7517
7518void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryArithmeticExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
7519 // TODO(leszeks): Add support for lhs smi in commutative ops.
7520 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->first());
7521
7522 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length(); ++i) {
7523 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
7524 if (expr->subsequent(i)->IsSmiLiteral()) {
7525 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr->subsequent_op_position(i));
7526 builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(
7527 expr->op(), expr->subsequent(i)->AsLiteral()->AsSmiLiteral(),
7528 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
7529 } else {
7530 Register lhs = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7531 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs);
7532 TypeHint rhs_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(i));
7533 if (IsStringTypeHint(rhs_hint)) type_hint = TypeHint::kString;
7534 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr->subsequent_op_position(i));
7535 builder()->BinaryOperation(
7536 expr->op(), lhs,
7537 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
7538 }
7539 }
7540
7541 if (IsStringTypeHint(type_hint) && expr->op() == Token::kAdd) {
7542 // If any operand of an ADD is a String, a String is produced.
7543 execution_result()->SetResultIsString();
7544 }
7545}
7546
7547// Note: the actual spreading is performed by the surrounding expression's
7548// visitor.
7549void BytecodeGenerator::VisitSpread(Spread* expr) { Visit(expr->expression()); }
7550
7551void BytecodeGenerator::VisitEmptyParentheses(EmptyParentheses* expr) {
7552 UNREACHABLE();
7553}
7554
7555void BytecodeGenerator::VisitImportCallExpression(ImportCallExpression* expr) {
7556 const int register_count = expr->import_options() ? 4 : 3;
7557 // args is a list of [ function_closure, specifier, phase, import_options ].
7558 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(register_count);
7559
7560 builder()->MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), args[0]);
7561 VisitForRegisterValue(expr->specifier(), args[1]);
7562 builder()
7563 ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(expr->phase())))
7564 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2]);
7565
7566 if (expr->import_options()) {
7567 VisitForRegisterValue(expr->import_options(), args[3]);
7568 }
7569
7570 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDynamicImportCall, args);
7571}
7572
7573void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetIterator(IteratorType hint) {
7574 if (hint == IteratorType::kAsync) {
7575 RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
7576
7577 Register obj = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7578 Register method = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7579
7580 // Set method to GetMethod(obj, @@asyncIterator)
7581 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(obj).LoadAsyncIteratorProperty(
7582 obj, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
7583
7584 BytecodeLabel async_iterator_undefined, done;
7585 builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&async_iterator_undefined);
7586
7587 // Let iterator be Call(method, obj)
7588 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method).CallProperty(
7589 method, RegisterList(obj),
7590 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
7591
7592 // If Type(iterator) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
7593 builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(&done);
7594 builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSymbolAsyncIteratorInvalid);
7595
7596 builder()->Bind(&async_iterator_undefined);
7597 // If method is undefined,
7598 // Let syncMethod be GetMethod(obj, @@iterator)
7599 builder()
7600 ->LoadIteratorProperty(obj,
7601 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
7602 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method);
7603
7604 // Let syncIterator be Call(syncMethod, obj)
7605 builder()->CallProperty(method, RegisterList(obj),
7606 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
7607
7608 // Return CreateAsyncFromSyncIterator(syncIterator)
7609 // alias `method` register as it's no longer used
7610 Register sync_iter = method;
7611 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(sync_iter).CallRuntime(
7612 Runtime::kInlineCreateAsyncFromSyncIterator, sync_iter);
7613
7614 builder()->Bind(&done);
7615 } else {
7616 {
7617 RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
7618
7619 Register obj = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7620 int load_feedback_index =
7621 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot());
7622 int call_feedback_index =
7623 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
7624
7625 // Let method be GetMethod(obj, @@iterator) and
7626 // iterator be Call(method, obj). If iterator is
7627 // not JSReceiver, then throw TypeError.
7628 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(obj).GetIterator(
7629 obj, load_feedback_index, call_feedback_index);
7630 }
7631 }
7632}
7633
7634// Returns an IteratorRecord which is valid for the lifetime of the current
7635// register_allocation_scope.
7636BytecodeGenerator::IteratorRecord BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetIteratorRecord(
7637 Register next, Register object, IteratorType hint) {
7638 DCHECK(next.is_valid() && object.is_valid());
7639 BuildGetIterator(hint);
7640
7641 builder()
7642 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(object)
7643 .LoadNamedProperty(object, ast_string_constants()->next_string(),
7644 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
7645 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next);
7646 return IteratorRecord(object, next, hint);
7647}
7648
7649BytecodeGenerator::IteratorRecord BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetIteratorRecord(
7650 IteratorType hint) {
7651 Register next = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7652 Register object = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7653 return BuildGetIteratorRecord(next, object, hint);
7654}
7655
7656void BytecodeGenerator::BuildIteratorNext(const IteratorRecord& iterator,
7657 Register next_result) {
7658 DCHECK(next_result.is_valid());
7659 builder()->CallProperty(iterator.next(), RegisterList(iterator.object()),
7660 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
7661
7662 if (iterator.type() == IteratorType::kAsync) {
7663 BuildAwait();
7664 }
7665
7666 BytecodeLabel is_object;
7667 builder()
7668 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next_result)
7669 .JumpIfJSReceiver(&is_object)
7670 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject, next_result)
7671 .Bind(&is_object);
7672}
7673
7674void BytecodeGenerator::BuildCallIteratorMethod(Register iterator,
7675 const AstRawString* method_name,
7676 RegisterList receiver_and_args,
7677 BytecodeLabel* if_called,
7678 BytecodeLabels* if_notcalled) {
7679 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
7680
7681 Register method = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7682 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
7683 builder()
7684 ->LoadNamedProperty(iterator, method_name, feedback_index(slot))
7685 .JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(if_notcalled->New())
7686 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method)
7687 .CallProperty(method, receiver_and_args,
7688 feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()))
7689 .Jump(if_called);
7690}
7691
7692void BytecodeGenerator::BuildIteratorClose(const IteratorRecord& iterator,
7693 Expression* expr) {
7694 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
7695 BytecodeLabels done(zone());
7696 BytecodeLabel if_called;
7697 RegisterList args = RegisterList(iterator.object());
7698 BuildCallIteratorMethod(iterator.object(),
7699 ast_string_constants()->return_string(), args,
7700 &if_called, &done);
7701 builder()->Bind(&if_called);
7702
7703 if (iterator.type() == IteratorType::kAsync) {
7704 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(expr);
7705 BuildAwait(expr->position());
7706 }
7707
7708 builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(done.New());
7709 {
7710 RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
7711 Register return_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7712 builder()
7713 ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(return_result)
7714 .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject, return_result);
7715 }
7716
7717 done.Bind(builder());
7718}
7719
7720void BytecodeGenerator::VisitGetTemplateObject(GetTemplateObject* expr) {
7721 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7722 size_t entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
7723 template_objects_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr, entry));
7724 FeedbackSlot literal_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot();
7725 builder()->GetTemplateObject(entry, feedback_index(literal_slot));
7726}
7727
7728void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTemplateLiteral(TemplateLiteral* expr) {
7729 const ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>& parts = *expr->string_parts();
7730 const ZonePtrList<Expression>& substitutions = *expr->substitutions();
7731 // Template strings with no substitutions are turned into StringLiterals.
7732 DCHECK_GT(substitutions.length(), 0);
7733 DCHECK_EQ(parts.length(), substitutions.length() + 1);
7734
7735 // Generate string concatenation
7736 // TODO(caitp): Don't generate feedback slot if it's not used --- introduce
7737 // a simple, concise, reusable mechanism to lazily create reusable slots.
7738 FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
7739 Register last_part = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7740 bool last_part_valid = false;
7741
7742 builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7743 for (int i = 0; i < substitutions.length(); ++i) {
7744 if (i != 0) {
7745 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(last_part);
7746 last_part_valid = true;
7747 }
7748
7749 if (!parts[i]->IsEmpty()) {
7750 builder()->LoadLiteral(parts[i]);
7751 if (last_part_valid) {
7752 builder()->BinaryOperation(Token::kAdd, last_part,
7753 feedback_index(slot));
7754 }
7755 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(last_part);
7756 last_part_valid = true;
7757 }
7758
7759 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(substitutions[i]);
7760 if (!IsStringTypeHint(type_hint)) {
7761 builder()->ToString();
7762 }
7763 if (last_part_valid) {
7764 builder()->BinaryOperation(Token::kAdd, last_part, feedback_index(slot));
7765 }
7766 last_part_valid = false;
7767 }
7768
7769 if (!parts.last()->IsEmpty()) {
7770 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(last_part);
7771 builder()->LoadLiteral(parts.last());
7772 builder()->BinaryOperation(Token::kAdd, last_part, feedback_index(slot));
7773 }
7774}
7775
7776void BytecodeGenerator::BuildThisVariableLoad() {
7777 DeclarationScope* receiver_scope = closure_scope()->GetReceiverScope();
7778 Variable* var = receiver_scope->receiver();
7779 // TODO(littledan): implement 'this' hole check elimination.
7780 HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode =
7781 IsDerivedConstructor(receiver_scope->function_kind())
7782 ? HoleCheckMode::kRequired
7783 : HoleCheckMode::kElided;
7784 BuildVariableLoad(var, hole_check_mode);
7785}
7786
7787void BytecodeGenerator::VisitThisExpression(ThisExpression* expr) {
7788 BuildThisVariableLoad();
7789}

7792 // Handled by VisitCall().
7793 UNREACHABLE();
7794}
7795
7796void BytecodeGenerator::VisitSuperPropertyReference(
7797 SuperPropertyReference* expr) {
7798 // Handled by VisitAssignment(), VisitCall(), VisitDelete() and
7799 // VisitPropertyLoad().
7800 UNREACHABLE();
7801}
7802
7803void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCommaExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
7804 VisitForEffect(binop->left());
7805 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(binop->right());
7806 Visit(binop->right());
7807}
7808
7809void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryCommaExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
7810 DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
7811
7812 VisitForEffect(expr->first());
7813 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
7814 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(expr->subsequent(i));
7815 VisitForEffect(expr->subsequent(i));
7816 }
7817 builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(
7818 expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
7819 Visit(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
7820}
7821
7822void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(
7823 Token::Value token, Expression* expr, BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
7824 BytecodeLabels* else_labels, int coverage_slot) {
7825 DCHECK(token == Token::kOr || token == Token::kAnd ||
7826 token == Token::kNullish);
7827
7828 BytecodeLabels test_next(zone());
7829 if (token == Token::kOr) {
7830 VisitForTest(expr, then_labels, &test_next, TestFallthrough::kElse);
7831 } else if (token == Token::kAnd) {
7832 VisitForTest(expr, &test_next, else_labels, TestFallthrough::kThen);
7833 } else {
7834 DCHECK_EQ(Token::kNullish, token);
7835 VisitForNullishTest(expr, then_labels, &test_next, else_labels);
7836 }
7837 test_next.Bind(builder());
7838
7839 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
7840}
7841
7842void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalTest(Token::Value token, Expression* left,
7843 Expression* right,
7844 int right_coverage_slot) {
7845 DCHECK(token == Token::kOr || token == Token::kAnd ||
7846 token == Token::kNullish);
7847 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7848 BytecodeLabels* then_labels = test_result->then_labels();
7849 BytecodeLabels* else_labels = test_result->else_labels();
7850 TestFallthrough fallthrough = test_result->fallthrough();
7851
7852 VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(token, left, then_labels, else_labels,
7853 right_coverage_slot);
7854 // The last test has the same then, else and fallthrough as the parent test.
7855 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
7856 VisitForTest(right, then_labels, else_labels, fallthrough);
7857}
7858
7859void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryLogicalTest(
7860 Token::Value token, NaryOperation* expr,
7861 const NaryCodeCoverageSlots* coverage_slots) {
7862 DCHECK(token == Token::kOr || token == Token::kAnd ||
7863 token == Token::kNullish);
7864 DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
7865
7866 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7867 BytecodeLabels* then_labels = test_result->then_labels();
7868 BytecodeLabels* else_labels = test_result->else_labels();
7869 TestFallthrough fallthrough = test_result->fallthrough();
7870
7871 VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(token, expr->first(), then_labels, else_labels,
7872 coverage_slots->GetSlotFor(0));
7873 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
7874 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
7875 VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(token, expr->subsequent(i), then_labels,
7876 else_labels,
7877 coverage_slots->GetSlotFor(i + 1));
7878 }
7879 // The last test has the same then, else and fallthrough as the parent test.
7880 VisitForTest(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1), then_labels,
7881 else_labels, fallthrough);
7882}
7883
7884bool BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(Expression* expr,
7885 BytecodeLabels* end_labels,
7886 int coverage_slot) {
7887 if (expr->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
7888 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
7889 end_labels->Bind(builder());
7890 return true;
7891 } else if (!expr->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
7892 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
7893 builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint),
7894 end_labels->New());
7895 }
7896
7897 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
7898
7899 return false;
7900}
7901
7902bool BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(Expression* expr,
7903 BytecodeLabels* end_labels,
7904 int coverage_slot) {
7905 if (expr->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
7906 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
7907 end_labels->Bind(builder());
7908 return true;
7909 } else if (!expr->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
7910 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
7911 builder()->JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint),
7912 end_labels->New());
7913 }
7914
7915 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
7916
7917 return false;
7918}
7919
7920bool BytecodeGenerator::VisitNullishSubExpression(Expression* expr,
7921 BytecodeLabels* end_labels,
7922 int coverage_slot) {
7923 if (expr->IsLiteralButNotNullOrUndefined()) {
7924 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
7925 end_labels->Bind(builder());
7926 return true;
7927 } else if (!expr->IsNullOrUndefinedLiteral()) {
7928 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
7929 BytecodeLabel is_null_or_undefined;
7930 builder()
7931 ->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&is_null_or_undefined)
7932 .Jump(end_labels->New());
7933 builder()->Bind(&is_null_or_undefined);
7934 }
7935
7936 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
7937
7938 return false;
7939}
7940
7941void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalOrExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
7942 Expression* left = binop->left();
7943 Expression* right = binop->right();
7944
7945 int right_coverage_slot =
7946 AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(binop, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
7947
7948 if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
7949 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7950 if (left->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
7951 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
7952 } else if (left->ToBooleanIsFalse() && right->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
7953 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_coverage_slot);
7954 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
7955 } else {
7956 VisitLogicalTest(Token::kOr, left, right, right_coverage_slot);
7957 }
7958 test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
7959 } else {
7960 BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
7961 if (VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(left, &end_labels, right_coverage_slot)) {
7962 return;
7963 }
7964 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(right);
7965 end_labels.Bind(builder());
7966 }
7967}
7968
7969void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryLogicalOrExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
7970 Expression* first = expr->first();
7971 DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
7972
7973 NaryCodeCoverageSlots coverage_slots(this, expr);
7974
7975 if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
7976 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7977 if (first->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
7978 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
7979 } else {
7980 VisitNaryLogicalTest(Token::kOr, expr, &coverage_slots);
7981 }
7982 test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
7983 } else {
7984 BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
7985 if (VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(first, &end_labels,
7986 coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(0))) {
7987 return;
7988 }
7989
7990 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
7991 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
7992 if (VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(expr->subsequent(i), &end_labels,
7993 coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(i + 1))) {
7994 return;
7995 }
7996 }
7997 // We have to visit the last value even if it's true, because we need its
7998 // actual value.
7999 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
8000 end_labels.Bind(builder());
8001 }
8002}
8003
8004void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalAndExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
8005 Expression* left = binop->left();
8006 Expression* right = binop->right();
8007
8008 int right_coverage_slot =
8009 AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(binop, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
8010
8011 if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8012 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8013 if (left->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
8014 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
8015 } else if (left->ToBooleanIsTrue() && right->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8016 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_coverage_slot);
8017 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8018 } else {
8019 VisitLogicalTest(Token::kAnd, left, right, right_coverage_slot);
8020 }
8021 test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8022 } else {
8023 BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8024 if (VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(left, &end_labels, right_coverage_slot)) {
8025 return;
8026 }
8027 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(right);
8028 end_labels.Bind(builder());
8029 }
8030}
8031
8032void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryLogicalAndExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
8033 Expression* first = expr->first();
8034 DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
8035
8036 NaryCodeCoverageSlots coverage_slots(this, expr);
8037
8038 if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8039 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8040 if (first->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
8041 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
8042 } else {
8043 VisitNaryLogicalTest(Token::kAnd, expr, &coverage_slots);
8044 }
8045 test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8046 } else {
8047 BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8048 if (VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(first, &end_labels,
8049 coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(0))) {
8050 return;
8051 }
8052 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
8053 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
8054 if (VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(expr->subsequent(i), &end_labels,
8055 coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(i + 1))) {
8056 return;
8057 }
8058 }
8059 // We have to visit the last value even if it's false, because we need its
8060 // actual value.
8061 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
8062 end_labels.Bind(builder());
8063 }
8064}
8065
8066void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNullishExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
8067 Expression* left = binop->left();
8068 Expression* right = binop->right();
8069
8070 int right_coverage_slot =
8071 AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(binop, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
8072
8073 if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8074 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8075 if (left->IsLiteralButNotNullOrUndefined() && left->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8076 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8077 } else if (left->IsNullOrUndefinedLiteral() &&
8078 right->IsNullOrUndefinedLiteral()) {
8079 BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_coverage_slot);
8080 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
8081 } else {
8082 VisitLogicalTest(Token::kNullish, left, right, right_coverage_slot);
8083 }
8084 test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8085 } else {
8086 BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8087 if (VisitNullishSubExpression(left, &end_labels, right_coverage_slot)) {
8088 return;
8089 }
8090 VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(right);
8091 end_labels.Bind(builder());
8092 }
8093}
8094
8095void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryNullishExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
8096 Expression* first = expr->first();
8097 DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
8098
8099 NaryCodeCoverageSlots coverage_slots(this, expr);
8100
8101 if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8102 TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8103 if (first->IsLiteralButNotNullOrUndefined() && first->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8104 builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8105 } else {
8106 VisitNaryLogicalTest(Token::kNullish, expr, &coverage_slots);
8107 }
8108 test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8109 } else {
8110 BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8111 if (VisitNullishSubExpression(first, &end_labels,
8112 coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(0))) {
8113 return;
8114 }
8115 HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
8116 for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
8117 if (VisitNullishSubExpression(expr->subsequent(i), &end_labels,
8118 coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(i + 1))) {
8119 return;
8120 }
8121 }
8122 // We have to visit the last value even if it's nullish, because we need its
8123 // actual value.
8124 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
8125 end_labels.Bind(builder());
8126 }
8127}
8128
8129void BytecodeGenerator::BuildNewLocalActivationContext() {
8130 ValueResultScope value_execution_result(this);
8131 Scope* scope = closure_scope();
8132 DCHECK_EQ(current_scope(), closure_scope());
8133
8134 // Create the appropriate context.
8135 DCHECK(scope->is_function_scope() || scope->is_eval_scope());
8136 int slot_count = scope->num_heap_slots() - Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS;
8137 if (slot_count <= ConstructorBuiltins::MaximumFunctionContextSlots()) {
8138 switch (scope->scope_type()) {
8139 case EVAL_SCOPE:
8140 builder()->CreateEvalContext(scope, slot_count);
8141 break;
8142 case FUNCTION_SCOPE:
8143 builder()->CreateFunctionContext(scope, slot_count);
8144 break;
8145 default:
8146 UNREACHABLE();
8147 }
8148 } else {
8149 Register arg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
8150 builder()->LoadLiteral(scope).StoreAccumulatorInRegister(arg).CallRuntime(
8151 Runtime::kNewFunctionContext, arg);
8152 register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(arg);
8153 }
8154}
8155
8156void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLocalActivationContextInitialization() {
8157 DeclarationScope* scope = closure_scope();
8158
8159 if (scope->has_this_declaration() && scope->receiver()->IsContextSlot()) {
8160 Variable* variable = scope->receiver();
8161 Register receiver(builder()->Receiver());
8162 // Context variable (at bottom of the context chain).
8163 DCHECK_EQ(0, scope->ContextChainLength(variable->scope()));
8164 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(receiver).StoreContextSlot(
8165 execution_context()->reg(), variable, 0);
8166 }
8167
8168 // Copy parameters into context if necessary.
8169 int num_parameters = scope->num_parameters();
8170 for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters; i++) {
8171 Variable* variable = scope->parameter(i);
8172 if (!variable->IsContextSlot()) continue;
8173
8174 Register parameter(builder()->Parameter(i));
8175 // Context variable (at bottom of the context chain).
8176 DCHECK_EQ(0, scope->ContextChainLength(variable->scope()));
8177 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(parameter).StoreContextSlot(
8178 execution_context()->reg(), variable, 0);
8179 }
8180}
8181
8182void BytecodeGenerator::BuildNewLocalBlockContext(Scope* scope) {
8183 ValueResultScope value_execution_result(this);
8184 DCHECK(scope->is_block_scope());
8185
8186 builder()->CreateBlockContext(scope);
8187}

8189void BytecodeGenerator::BuildNewLocalWithContext(Scope* scope) {
8190 ValueResultScope value_execution_result(this);
8191
8192 Register extension_object = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
8193
8194 builder()->ToObject(extension_object);
8195 builder()->CreateWithContext(extension_object, scope);
8196
8197 register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(extension_object);
8198}

8200void BytecodeGenerator::BuildNewLocalCatchContext(Scope* scope) {

8202 DCHECK(scope->catch_variable()->IsContextSlot());

8204 Register exception = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
8205 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(exception);
8206 builder()->CreateCatchContext(exception, scope);
8207 register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(exception);
8208}

8219void BytecodeGenerator::VisitArgumentsObject(Variable* variable) {
8220 if (variable == nullptr) return;
8221
8222 DCHECK(variable->IsContextSlot() || variable->IsStackAllocated());
8223
8224 // Allocate and initialize a new arguments object and assign to the
8225 // {arguments} variable.
8226 builder()->CreateArguments(closure_scope()->GetArgumentsType());
8227 BuildVariableAssignment(variable, Token::kAssign, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
8228}

8230void BytecodeGenerator::VisitRestArgumentsArray(Variable* rest) {
8231 if (rest == nullptr) return;
8232
8233 // Allocate and initialize a new rest parameter and assign to the {rest}
8234 // variable.
8235 builder()->CreateArguments(CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter);
8236 DCHECK(rest->IsContextSlot() || rest->IsStackAllocated());
8237 BuildVariableAssignment(rest, Token::kAssign, HoleCheckMode::kElided);

8239
8240void BytecodeGenerator::VisitThisFunctionVariable(Variable* variable) {
8241 if (variable == nullptr) return;
8242
8243 // Store the closure we were called with in the given variable.
8244 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(Register::function_closure());
8245 BuildVariableAssignment(variable, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
8246}
8247
8248void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNewTargetVariable(Variable* variable) {
8249 if (variable == nullptr) return;
8250
8251 // The generator resume trampoline abuses the new.target register
8252 // to pass in the generator object. In ordinary calls, new.target is always
8253 // undefined because generator functions are non-constructible, so don't
8254 // assign anything to the new.target variable.
8255 if (IsResumableFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) return;
8256
8257 if (variable->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
8258 // The new.target register was already assigned by entry trampoline.
8259 DCHECK_EQ(incoming_new_target_or_generator_.index(),
8260 GetRegisterForLocalVariable(variable).index());
8261 return;
8262 }
8263
8264 // Store the new target we were called with in the given variable.
8265 builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(incoming_new_target_or_generator_);
8266 BuildVariableAssignment(variable, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
8267}
8268
8269void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGeneratorObjectVariableInitialization() {
8270 DCHECK(IsResumableFunction(info()->literal()->kind()));
8271
8272 Variable* generator_object_var = closure_scope()->generator_object_var();
8273 RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
8274 RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
8275 Runtime::FunctionId function_id =
8276 ((IsAsyncFunction(info()->literal()->kind()) &&
8277 !IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) ||
8278 IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(info()->literal()->kind()))
8279 ? Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionEnter
8280 : Runtime::kInlineCreateJSGeneratorObject;
8281 builder()
8282 ->MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), args[0])
8283 .MoveRegister(builder()->Receiver(), args[1])
8284 .CallRuntime(function_id, args)
8285 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(generator_object());
8286
8287 if (generator_object_var->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
8288 // The generator object register is already set to the variable's local
8289 // register.
8290 DCHECK_EQ(generator_object().index(),
8291 GetRegisterForLocalVariable(generator_object_var).index());
8292 } else {
8293 BuildVariableAssignment(generator_object_var, Token::kInit,
8294 HoleCheckMode::kElided);
8295 }
8296}
8297
8298void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPushUndefinedIntoRegisterList(
8299 RegisterList* reg_list) {
8300 Register reg = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(reg_list);
8301 builder()->LoadUndefined().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(reg);
8302}
8303
8304void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLoadPropertyKey(LiteralProperty* property,
8305 Register out_reg) {
8306 if (property->key()->IsStringLiteral()) {
8307 builder()
8308 ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawString())
8309 .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(out_reg);
8310 } else {
8311 VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
8312 builder()->ToName().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(out_reg);
8313 }
8314}

8353// Visits the expression |expr| and places the result in the accumulator.
8354BytecodeGenerator::TypeHint BytecodeGenerator::VisitForAccumulatorValue(
8355 Expression* expr) {
8356 ValueResultScope accumulator_scope(this);
8357 Visit(expr);
8358 // Record the type hint for the result of current expression in accumulator.
8359 const TypeHint type_hint = accumulator_scope.type_hint();
8360 BytecodeRegisterOptimizer* optimizer = builder()->GetRegisterOptimizer();
8361 if (optimizer && type_hint != TypeHint::kUnknown) {
8362 optimizer->SetTypeHintForAccumulator(type_hint);
8363 }
8364 return type_hint;
8365}
8366
8367void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForAccumulatorValueOrTheHole(Expression* expr) {
8368 if (expr == nullptr) {
8369 builder()->LoadTheHole();
8370 } else {
8371 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8372 }
8373}
8374
8375// Visits the expression |expr| and discards the result.
8376void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForEffect(Expression* expr) {
8377 EffectResultScope effect_scope(this);
8378 Visit(expr);
8379}
8380
8381// Visits the expression |expr| and returns the register containing
8382// the expression result.
8383Register BytecodeGenerator::VisitForRegisterValue(Expression* expr) {
8384 VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8385 Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
8386 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result);
8387 return result;
8388}
8389
8390// Visits the expression |expr| and stores the expression result in
8391// |destination|.
8392void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForRegisterValue(Expression* expr,
8393 Register destination) {
8394 ValueResultScope register_scope(this);
8395 Visit(expr);
8396 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
8397}

8399// Visits the expression |expr| and pushes the result into a new register
8400// added to the end of |reg_list|.
8401void BytecodeGenerator::VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(Expression* expr,
8402 RegisterList* reg_list) {
8403 {
8404 ValueResultScope register_scope(this);
8405 Visit(expr);
8406 }
8407 // Grow the register list after visiting the expression to avoid reserving
8408 // the register across the expression evaluation, which could cause memory
8409 // leaks for deep expressions due to dead objects being kept alive by pointers
8410 // in registers.
8411 Register destination = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(reg_list);
8412 builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
8413}
8414
8415void BytecodeGenerator::BuildTest(ToBooleanMode mode,
8416 BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
8417 BytecodeLabels* else_labels,
8418 TestFallthrough fallthrough) {
8419 switch (fallthrough) {
8420 case TestFallthrough::kThen:
8421 builder()->JumpIfFalse(mode, else_labels->New());
8422 break;
8423 case TestFallthrough::kElse:
8424 builder()->JumpIfTrue(mode, then_labels->New());
8425 break;
8426 case TestFallthrough::kNone:
8427 builder()->JumpIfTrue(mode, then_labels->New());
8428 builder()->Jump(else_labels->New());
8429 break;
8430 }
8431}
8432
8433// Visits the expression |expr| for testing its boolean value and jumping to the
8434// |then| or |other| label depending on value and short-circuit semantics
8435void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForTest(Expression* expr,
8436 BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
8437 BytecodeLabels* else_labels,
8438 TestFallthrough fallthrough) {
8439 bool result_consumed;
8440 TypeHint type_hint;
8441 {
8442 // To make sure that all temporary registers are returned before generating
8443 // jumps below, we ensure that the result scope is deleted before doing so.
8444 // Dead registers might be materialized otherwise.
8445 TestResultScope test_result(this, then_labels, else_labels, fallthrough);
8446 Visit(expr);
8447 result_consumed = test_result.result_consumed_by_test();
8448 type_hint = test_result.type_hint();
8449 // Labels and fallthrough might have been mutated, so update based on
8450 // TestResultScope.
8451 then_labels = test_result.then_labels();
8452 else_labels = test_result.else_labels();
8453 fallthrough = test_result.fallthrough();
8454 }
8455 if (!result_consumed) {
8456 BuildTest(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint), then_labels, else_labels,
8457 fallthrough);
8458 }
8459}
8460
8461// Visits the expression |expr| for testing its nullish value and jumping to the
8462// |then| or |other| label depending on value and short-circuit semantics
8463void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForNullishTest(Expression* expr,
8464 BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
8465 BytecodeLabels* test_next_labels,
8466 BytecodeLabels* else_labels) {
8467 // Nullish short circuits on undefined or null, otherwise we fall back to
8468 // BuildTest with no fallthrough.
8469 // TODO(joshualitt): We should do this in a TestResultScope.
8470 TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8471 ToBooleanMode mode = ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint);
8472
8473 // Skip the nullish shortcircuit if we already have a boolean.
8474 if (mode != ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean) {
8475 builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(test_next_labels->New());
8476 }
8477 BuildTest(mode, then_labels, else_labels, TestFallthrough::kNone);
8478}
8479
8480void BytecodeGenerator::VisitInSameTestExecutionScope(Expression* expr) {
8481 DCHECK(execution_result()->IsTest());
8482 {
8483 RegisterAllocationScope reg_scope(this);
8484 Visit(expr);
8485 }
8486 if (!execution_result()->AsTest()->result_consumed_by_test()) {
8487 TestResultScope* result_scope = execution_result()->AsTest();
8488 BuildTest(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(result_scope->type_hint()),
8489 result_scope->then_labels(), result_scope->else_labels(),
8490 result_scope->fallthrough());
8491 result_scope->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8492 }
8493}

8495void BytecodeGenerator::VisitInScope(Statement* stmt, Scope* scope) {
8496 DCHECK(scope->declarations()->is_empty());
8497 CurrentScope current_scope(this, scope);
8498 ContextScope context_scope(this, scope);
8499 Visit(stmt);
8500}
